title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, brown sugar, salt and soda.
Add shortening, egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir with wooden spoon until well mixed.
Mix in oats and chocolate chips or raisins.
Drop dough from teaspoon about 2 inches apart onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Yield: 50 cookies.

title: pink arctic freeze
directions: Soften the cheese, then blend in the mayonnaise and sugar. Add fruits and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into square pan.
Freeze firm, 6 hours or overnight.
To serve, let stand at room temperature 15 minutes.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy chocolate syrup
directions: Combine
sugar,
cocoa,
salt
and 1/2 cup hot water in three quart
saucepan and stir until smooth.
Add remaining 1 1/2
cups water
and stir.
Bring to boil.
Boil 2 minutes on medium	heat. Cool.
Add vanilla.
Put in jar with tight lid. Keep in refrigerator for ice cream topping or chocolate milk.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix soups, tomatoes, cheese and onions.
In casserole dish, place layer of Doritos in bottom.
Put half of chicken on Doritos and half of soup mixture on chicken.
Repeat layers.
Top with Doritos.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy chocolate almond mousse pie
directions: Beat mousse mix with the milk until thick (about 3 minutes). Stir in sour cream. Turn mixture into pie shell. Sprinkle with toasted almonds.
Chill until set, at least 2 hours, before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix tuna, soup and milk.
Cook noodles.
Put broccoli in strainer and drain noodles on top of broccoli.
Mix with tuna mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Mix oil, dill weed, garlic powder and Hidden Valley Ranch dressing.
Mix together half of the oyster crackers and half of the dressing mixture.
Put in a plastic bag.
Repeat with remaining half.
Store in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream shortening, lemon extract and sugar well.
Add eggs, pumpkin, salt and spices.
Sift flour and baking powder together. Blend into creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: carrots with hazelnut butter(10 servings)
directions: Use white and tender green parts only; wash, cut in 2-inch pieces in large pot (or pressure cooker) and brown 2 slices of bacon per person.
Cover with leeks (2 leeks per person minimum). Cover with peeled, diced 1 x 1-inch potatoes.
Add enough water to keep some juice when cooked; salt and pepper.
Cover and let simmer until potatoes are cooked.
In pressure cooker, 1/2-inch of water (or more depending on quantity being cooked) and pressure cook for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: chili bean dip
directions: Mash beans with tomato sauce.
Add spices and cheese.
Serve with vegetables or corn chips.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar, egg and molasses. Blend in remaining ingredients, except granulated sugar.
Cover and chill 1 hour.

title: honey krispies
directions: Heat honey and peanut butter well and mix.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.

title: german pizza
directions: Grease pan very well, leaving quite a little bit covering the bottom.

title: coconut pecan cake filling and frosting
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter or margarine and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until cool and of spreading consistency. Makes enough to cover tops of three 8 or 9-inch layers or about 2 2/3 cups frosting and filling.

title: kool-aid pie
directions: Chill evaporated milk.
Then beat with mixer until nearly doubled.
Add sugar and Kool-Aid.
Mix real well.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Hard boil eggs and peel.
Mix one egg, sausage and 1/4 c corn flake crumbs together.
Divide into 4 patties.
With hands, wrap a patty around each hard boiled egg.
Blend 2 more eggs and dip each molded egg into the blended eggs to coat.
Roll in cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 350 degrees for half an hour.
Serve hot or cold, sliced or quartered.
It is a nice appetizer or can be topped with soup or sauce for a brunch.

title: carrot coin casserole
directions: Place carrots and a small amount of water in a saucepan; cook over medium heat until crisp-tender, about 6 minutes.
Add onion; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 4-6 minutes or until onion is crisp-tender.
Drain.
Add peas and toss.
Place 4 cups in greased shallow 3 quart baking dish; sprinkle with cheese. Top with remaining vegetables.
In a saucepan over medium heat, melt 1 Tbsp. butter.
Stir in flour, salt, pepper and nutmeg until smooth.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil; Boil and stir for 2 minutes.
Pour over the vegetables.
In a small saucepan or skillet, combine cracker crumbs and remaining butter; cook and stir over medium heat until toasted.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered, at 350 degrees for 30-40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: matzo ball soup
directions: Cover chicken with water in large stock pan. Add salt and peppercorns. Simmer for several hours on low heat. Saut sliced mushrooms in butter until golden brown. When chicken is cooked, remove it from the pot and reserve for another dish. Cool broth in refrigerator and skim fat. Add mushrooms to defatted broth.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add the Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan; let cool.
(Grease bottom of pan with butter.)

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crackers.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: southern fried bananas
directions: Slice bananas in half lengthwise.
Place in melted butter in skillet and brown lightly, handling carefully to avoid breaking into pieces.
Remove. Roll in powdered sugar and serve immediately. Excellent with fried chicken.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine the milk and water.
Add pudding mix.
Beat until well blended.
Chill 5 to 10 minutes.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: strawberry frost
directions: Crush strawberries; add sugar and 1 cup of milk.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually add remaining ingredients except ice cream, beating well.
Put 1 or 2 scoops ice cream into each chilled glass.
Fill with strawberry mixture.
If desired, garnish with strawberries.
Makes 5 cups.

title: super duper(hot noodle dish)
directions: Brown
hamburger
and
onion while noodles are cooking. Mix all ingredients and add hamburger and noodles last.
Place in
a greased
casserole.
Cover	with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: pineapple nut cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, soda and salt.
Beat until fluffy the shortening, sugar and brown sugar; add pineapple, vanilla, eggs and nuts.
Add dry ingredients and blend well.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil five minutes; remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda.
Beat down.
Pour over popcorn that is on a sprayed large cookie sheet.
Bake in 200° oven for 1 hour.
Store in plastic bags or Tupperware dish.

title: mott street meat patties
directions: Form ground beef into 6 oval patties. Cook with oil in skillet until browned. Do not drain. Meanwhile, combine water, soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch and sugar in a bowl and set aside. Place strips of green pepper on patties. Pour sauce mixture over green peppers and patties. Cover and simmer for 10-15 minutes. Serve over cooked rice or noodles.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes or until firm. Cool before serving.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco, then add beaten eggs and mix well. Sift flour with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture and knead smooth.
Pick about a teaspoon of dough and roll between palms of hands, about the size of your little finger.
Roll in the sesame seed, pressing seeds a little into dough.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet 1 inch apart.
Bake for 15 minutes on upper rack of oven at 400°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Then add eggs and other ingredients. Pour into pie pans and cook at 350° until brown on top for 35 minutes.
Grease and flour pans.
Makes 2 pies.

title: oven roasted vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In plastic bag or bowl, shake or toss all ingredients until vegetables are coated.
Empty into 13 x 9-inch baking or roasting pan.
Discard bag.
Bake for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender; stir once.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop frozen cranberries. Add sugar and let stand for 30 minutes. Dissolve lemon and raspberry Jell-O in 2 cups hot water. Add pineapple, nuts and cranberries.
Put in Jell-O mold and cool overnight.

title: chocolate scotchroos
directions: Combine sugar and syrup in a large heavy saucepan and cook over medium heat until it boils, stirring often.
Remove from heat and mix in peanut butter.
Add cereal; pat into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chips together in double boiler and spread over bars.
Cut into bars and cool in fridge.

title: blackberry dumplings
directions: Cook berries, 1/4 cup flour, sugar and butter until thickened. Sift remaining flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend in the shortening.
Add milk.
Mix quickly.
Drop by teaspoon into slowly boiling blackberry mixture.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.

title: beef, pepper and mushroom kabobs
directions: Trim excess fat from steak; cut steak into 1 1/4-inch pieces. Whisk together oil, lemon juice, water, mustard, honey, oregano and pepper in large bowl.
Add beef, bell pepper and mushrooms, turning to coat.
Alternately thread beef, bell pepper and mushrooms on each of four 12-inch metal skewers.
Place kabobs on rack in broiler pan so surface of meat is 3 to 4 inches from heat. Broil 9 to 12 minutes for rare to medium, turning occasionally. Season with salt, if desired.

title: cheese soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook potatoes, celery and onions in salted water for about 15 minutes until tender.
Set aside.

title: quick easy cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl; cut together with a pastry blender until fine crumbs.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake until golden brown.

title: dill dip
directions: Great on vegetables and baked potatoes.

title: just marvelous chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°; combine crumbs, cheese, nuts and salt. Coat chicken parts; in a bowl, beat eggs with buttermilk just to blend.
Dip coated chicken parts again in crumb mixture.
Place chicken in a lightly greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch baking pan.
Drizzle melted butter over chicken.
Bake 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Whisk first 5 ingredients in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, 10 minutes.
Heat gelatin and water over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Stir into cooled lemon mix.
Whip heavy cream and fold into mixture.
Pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.
Decorate with crystallized pansies.

title: strawberry walnut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans. Combine flour, granulated sugar, cinnamon, baking soda and salt in a large bowl and mix well. Whisk eggs in a small bowl until blended. Add the eggs and oil to the flour mixture and stir just until blended. Fold in undrained strawberries and walnuts. Spoon equal portions of the batter into the prepared loaf pans. Bake until a toothpick inserted in centers of loaves comes out clean, about 70 minutes. Cool loaves in pans for 5 to 10 minutes. Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: french dressing
directions: Heat to dissolve sugars and vinegar.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Store in refrigerator with tight lid.
Mix before serving.

title: "starter" and friendship cake
directions: Mix until smooth the cake mix and pudding mix.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Store in freezer, the longer, the better.

title: chocolate mousse pie
directions: Heat chocolate with water in top of double boiler, stirring until smooth.
Stir in egg yolks; add vanilla.
Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until foamy throughout.
Gradually beat in sugar until stiff peaks form, about 8 minutes.
Stir a small amount into chocolate mixture to lighten; fold chocolate mixture into remaining whites.
Pour 4 cups into a buttered 9-inch pie pan sprinkled with sugar.
Chill remaining mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or just until set.
Cool slightly, then chill 1 hour. Center will fall, forming shell.
Spoon chilled chocolate mixture into chilled shell.
Chill 3 hours or overnight.
Garnish with chocolate curls and whipped cream.

title: piglet's pizza muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°.
Split the muffins in half by piercing them around the edges with the tines of a fork and prying them apart gently.
Place them, split sides up, in a shallow baking dish.
Spoon the spaghetti sauce onto the muffins, spreading it to the edges.
Top each muffin with a slice of cheese.
(Trim the cheese slices so they're the same size as the muffins, otherwise cheese will melt all over and make a mess.)
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until the cheese is browned slightly at the edges.

title: oatmeal crunchies
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in rolled oats and walnuts.
Form dough into small balls.
Dip in a little sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: sweet and sour cabbage
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp and golden brown, stirring often.
Remove with slotted spoon to paper toweling to drain.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons of the bacon fat.
Add onion and garlic to skillet.
Saute until softened, about 2 minutes.
Add cabbage.
Cook, uncovered, over low heat, stirring often, for 15 minutes.
Add half the bacon.
Cook 15 minutes longer or until cabbage is tender.
Stir in sugar, vinegar, salt and pepper. Transfer cabbage to serving plate.
Sprinkle with remaining bacon.

title: oriental pork casserole
directions: Roll pork in flour and brown in oil over low to medium heat. Drain.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and add to pork. Pour into greased long casserole dish and bake, covered with aluminum foil, for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: spareribs
directions: Put into boiler and pour Coca-Cola over.
Cook until done and be sure to cool down.

title: ultimate pancakes
directions: Stir all together until well blended. Cook on hot griddle until edges are dry. Flip; cook other side to a golden brown.

title: bacon swiss bread
directions: Cut bread into 1-inch thick slices, leaving slices attached at the bottom.
In a bowl, combine butter, onions and mustard; spread on both sides of each slice of bread.
Cut each cheese slice diagonally into four triangles; place between the slices of bread.
Cut bacon in half width-wise and then lengthwise; drape a piece over each slice.
Place the loaf on a double thickness of heavy-duty foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Yields 10 servings.

title: oven caramel popcorn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Use 2 ungreased baking pans (9 x 13-inch). Heat sugar, margarine, syrup and salt, stirring occasionally until bubbly around edges.
Continue cooking over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda until foamy. Pour on popped corn.
Stir to coat well.
Put half in each pan. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken, cheese, vegetable chowder
directions: Cook together in broth, the chicken and vegetables until tender.
Add noodles; do not overcook.
Season.
On low heat, add cheese last until it melts.
Do not cook with cheese or cheese will stick to pan.

title: old-fashioned stack cake
directions: Cook dried apples until tender.
Cool and run through a colander.
Sweeten and
spice to taste.
Set aside.

title: my mother's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Heat butter and brown sugar together in heavy skillet until brown sugar is melted.
Cool.
Arrange pineapple slices with cherry in center of each over mixture.
Beat eggs until frothy; beat in sugar gradually.
Add sifted dry ingredients and water alternately.
Pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until done.
While still hot, turn out (upside down) on serving plate.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: In small bowl, combine cream cheese, scallions, dill, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, garlic and red pepper until well blended.
Cover and refrigerate about 20 minutes.
Spread 1 teaspoon of cream cheese mixture on each slice of bread.
Top each with 2 to 3 cucumber slices and garnish with dill sprigs.
Arrange on platter.
Keep refrigerated up to 8 hours before use.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: sugar crisp cookies
directions: Mix together and make small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350 for 15-17 minutes until light brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix first five ingredients and spread into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and shape into balls.
Fry until brown.

title: sour cream dutch apple pie
directions: Mix all pie ingredients.
Lay sliced apples in pie crust until full.
Pour mixture over apples (do not mix).

title: apple pie filling
directions: Fill 7 quart jars with diced apples.
Combine all other ingredients and boil until thickened, then add lemon juice. Pour over diced apples.
Allow 1-inch headspace.
Process in hot water bath for 20 minutes.

title: mandarin spinach salad
directions: Cook almonds and sugar over low heat, stirring constantly. Cool on wax paper and break apart.	Store at room temperature. Combine remaining ingredients.
Toss with Sweet and Sour Dressing.

title: blue box blues macaroni and cheese dinner
directions: Following box directions, boil water in saucepan. Add uncooked macaroni and broccoli. Wait 9 to 12 minutes (as directed on box). Drain macaroni and broccoli. Add cheese from box; stir until well blended. Add olives and stir. Serve immediately. Makes 2 1/2 servings.

title: tumis sayur buncis daging(skillet beef and beans)
directions: Cut beef in strips; brown in cooking oil.
Add onion, beans, celery and mushrooms.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes, stirring constantly or until beans are crisp-tender.
Combine soy sauce and cornstarch with liquid.
Add to skillet mixture; cook and stir until liquid has thickened and is shiny.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 4.

title: company's coming squash
directions: Simmer the first 4 ingredients in small amount of water for 8 to 10 minutes.
Line casserole dish with stuffing mix which has been combined with margarine.
Save enough for topping.
Mix soup into squash mixture and blend in 1 cup sour cream.
Pour into casserole; sprinkle with stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until brown.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or celery

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Transfer to an 11 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° (glass pan at 350°) for 35 minutes or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: five layer dinner
directions: Cook chopped onion in fat until tender.
Add meat, 1 teaspoon salt, pepper and chili powder; blend.
Place in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place potatoes over meat.
Add a layer of string beans, then corn, sprinkling each layer with salt.
Place sliced tomatoes in layer over corn.
Top with cheese and parsley. Cover; bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: yum yum dessert
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and margarine.
Reserve 1/3 cup crumb mixture.
Press remaining crumbs into the bottom of a 13x9x2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: grandma's chess tarts
directions: Mix together and make little pie crusts (use round cookie cutter).
Put into cupcake pan.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and blend well.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown chuck. Add other ingredients. Roll in tortillas and bake at 300° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven. Pour sauce over enchiladas. Sprinkle cheese on top and return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Have margarine, Crisco and eggs at room temperature.
Cream margarine, Crisco and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix after each addition.
Sift baking powder and salt with flour.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk to sugar mixture. Add flavorings and nuts.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Pour batter into pan; bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: turtle cookies
directions: Melt together the chocolate and butter.
Pour into bowl and add remaining ingredients.
Preheat waffle iron.
Drop 1 tablespoon in each section of waffle iron.
Cook 50 to 60 seconds. Frost.

title: gingerbread
directions: Add beaten eggs to sugar, molasses and melted shortening.
Add flour, sifted with other dry ingredients. Add hot water last. Bake in greased and floured pan at 350°. Serve with Cool Whip if desired.

title: party mix
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 275° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ice cream punch
directions: Take ice cream and juice out of freezer about 1/2 hour before preparing.
(This will make it easier to mix, but it is not necessary.)
The 7-Up need not be chilled.
Mix all ingredients in a large container with a mixer for several minutes.
Makes 2 large punch bowls of punch.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil, strawberries and pecans.
Stir just until all the ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into a well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until bread tests done.

title: pilaf stuffed chicken legs
directions: Saute onion and uncooked rice in mayonnaise until onion is tender.
Blend in the curry powder and currants.
Stir in broth. Cover and cook about 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let cool.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil margarine, water and cocoa.
Put flour, sugar and salt in a big bowl.
Add hot cocoa mixture to flour and beat well.
Add eggs, sour cream, baking soda and vanilla.
Beat until nice and smooth.
Bake in a greased jelly roll pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: baby food gellies
directions: In a small pan, sprinkle gelatine over baby juice; let stand 1 minute.
Stir until gelatine is dissolved, about 3 minutes.
Pour into small loaf pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares or fancy shape for finger eating.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Melt together caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven
to
In
medium bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugars
until
light
and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Beat
in dry ingredients until blended.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto 2 ungreased cookie
sheets.
Bake 12 minutes until golden brown. Cool on wire rack.	Makes 6 dozen.

title: orange mandarin salad
directions: Mix together orange jello, water, orange juice and mandarin oranges.
Mix well and let congeal.
Mix together vanilla instant pudding and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread this over congealed salad.

title: salmon stew
directions: Heat milk; add salmon and rest of ingredients.
Simmer for a few minutes.

title: grandma's low-fat casserole
directions: Saute margarine, onions, pepper and celery.
Then add turkey, salt, pepper, oregano, garlic salt, sugar, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, water, mushrooms and olives.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate or rice potatoes.
Pat dry with a paper towel.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Heat skillet to medium-high heat; add oil to coat.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful.
Cook 1 to 2 minutes. Turn and cook 1 minute longer.
Serve immediately.

title: eggs benedict
directions: Mix egg yolks mixture with 1/2 stick butter.
Add another 1/2 stick butter.
Serve egg topped with sauce immediately.

title: better breakfast rolls
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add egg, slightly beaten. Mix in milk and oil gently until flour disappears.
Put in greased muffin pan.
Makes 12 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 22 minutes.
Goes great with a main meal.
Next day butter and put under broiler to toast.

title: canning string beans
directions: Cover string beans with water.
Add vinegar, sugar and salt. Boil 20 minutes.
Pack into sterilized hot jars.
Put lids on tight.
Keep out of drafts.
Bottles will seal.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, soda and brown sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour, soda and cream of tartar.
Add vanilla, coconut and peanuts.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 11 minutes being sure not to overbake.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Sprinkle salt and pepper over chicken. Place oil in pan and heat.
Add chicken and saute slowly 6 minutes or until opaque white.
Remove and drain.
Cook broccoli and drain.
Place in bottom of a 9 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Place chicken over broccoli. Mix soup, mayo and lemon juice. Pour over chicken and broccoli. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cinnamon dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.
Serve with apple slices or cookies.
Makes 1 cup.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Mix together flour, soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, apples, dates and nuts.
Add to other mixture.
Grease and flour pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours in a tube or Bundt pan. If you freeze cake, use only 1 1/4 cups oil.

title: amish chicken corn soup
directions: Cook chicken in slow cooker or crock-pot until tender. Remove meat from bone and shred. Cut corn off from a half dozen large ears of fresh corn. Make Noodles. Cook corn and Noodles in chicken broth. If you need more broth, add a can of chicken broth. Add chicken, parsley and hard-boiled eggs.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Cook pineapple for 15 minutes on low.
Remove from heat.
Add jello.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip and mix with mixer until well blended.
Add pecans.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat.
Add ground beef to other ingredients.
Cover and let simmer for 10 minutes.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients; add remaining ingredients. Drop on greased cookie sheet (approximately 1 teaspoon size) and bake at 300°.
Remove from oven and place 3 to 4 M&M's on each cookie.
Seasonal M&M's add to the cookies; i.e., for Christmas use red and green M&M's; Easter use pastel M&M's.

title: rainbow pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta per package.
Rinse with cold water; toss ingredients.
Chill at least 4 hours before serving, preferably overnight.
Serves 18.

title: chews me!
directions: Place 36 vanilla caramels (10 ounces) and 3 tablespoons light cream in top of a double boiler over simmering water.
Beat until caramels melt.
Stir occasionally.
Toss together 1 cup corn flakes, 2 cups crisp rice cereal, 1 cup flaked coconut, 1/2 cup chopped California walnuts, and 1/2 cup raisins.
Pour caramel mixture over dry mixture and mix thoroughly.
With buttered fingers, press rounded tablespoons of mixture lightly into balls. Place on waxed paper.
Makes about 4 dozen confection cookies.

title: a girl scout
directions: Take friendship and loyalty; mix thoroughly with blended caring and sharing.
Add forgiveness with respect.
Mix in honesty; sprinkle with spoonfuls of fun, laughter and fresh air from outdoors.
Bake with sunshine.
Should serve everyone you meet and last a lifetime.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Boil sugar and coffee 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add cinnamon and vanilla.
Stir well; add nuts.
Stir until coated.

title: old fruit
directions: Mix banana and apple together.
Combine and add sugar, honey and water to fruit.
Simmer fruit and syrup mixture over low heat, stirring often until thickened, about 15 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 teaspoon lemon.
Serve over pound cake or ice cream.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Cover and simmer.
If on dry side, add a small amount of water.
Split hamburger buns and butter.
Add meat on bottom half of bun, topping with Mozzarella cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts and top of plain buttered bun is browned.

title: granny's mandarin orange pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; fill pie crusts and refrigerate several hours or overnight before serving.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt margarine and Velveeta cheese together.
Add cocoa, powdered sugar, vanilla and nuts.
Spread in a greased pan. Chill and cut into squares.

title: a good rice pudding
directions: Boil the rice for half an hour in four times its bulk of water.
If raisins are used, boil them with the rice.
Add the milk, sugar, spice, salt and the whole of one egg and yolks of the other two, saving the whites for frosting.
Bake about an hour or until done, then beat the whites to a froth.
Add half a cup of sugar.
Spread over top.
Return to the oven a few minutes to brown.

title: apple coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples.
Add apples; spread in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: creamy curry pork chops
directions: Puree water, Ricotta, 1 tablespoon flour, chutney, curry and salt in food processor until smooth.
Dredge chops in remaining flour.
Heat oil in nonstick over medium heat.
Add chops.
Cook 4 to 6 minutes or until no longer pink.
Transfer to serving dish. Pour off fat from skillet.
Add curry-Ricotta mixture and raisins to skillet; boil, stirring 2 minutes.
Serve with chops.

title: s'mores bars
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Blend in eggs and vanilla; stir in graham cracker crumbs, salt and flour. Set 2 1/2 cups aside. Press remainder into greased 9 x 13 pan. Lay Hershey bars on top. Sprinkle on marshmallows and top with remaining crumb mixture. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mushroom spread
directions: Spray medium size skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Saute mushrooms and onion in skillet until tender.
Add hard-cooked egg whites.
Moisten with stock; season with tamari and a dash of Tabasco sauce.
Makes 1 cup.

title: strawberry cooler
directions: Mix in blender until smooth and serve.
Serves 3.

title: baked catfish
directions: Dip fillets in salad dressing and place in a single layer, skin side down, in a baking dish.
Combine chips and cheese and sprinkle over fillets.
Bake at 500° for 10 to 15 minutes or until fish flakes easily.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegies, soup, 1/2 cup of the cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can of the onions.
Pour into a 1-quart baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: grandma's superb dressing
directions: Mix and set aside in refrigerator for a few days; the longer, the better!
Use on cole slaw, fruit or on tossed salad.
Also good on carrot raisin salad.

title: yam and apple casserole
directions: Combine yams and apple together in casserole dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out and add marshmallows.
Place back in oven for 5 to 10 minutes, or until brown.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Mix in egg and vanilla.
Add all dry ingredients and bananas.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Drop by spoon on greased baking sheet and bake for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil broccoli in salt water. Mix with next 5 ingredients. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Put bread crumbs on last 10 minutes of baking.

title: crab cakes
directions: Combine crackers and melted butter.
Add crab meat and remaining ingredients, being careful not to break up lumps of crab meat.
Shape into "cakes" and bake in a 350° oven until brown. Serves 4 to 6.

title: golden dream punch
directions: In punch bowl, mix juice concentrates with water as directed on cans.
Add apricot nectar and lemon juice.
Pour in ginger ale. Blend and add 1 tray of ice cubes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place sugar in top of double boiler.
Butter the bread, then dice and sprinkle buttered bread over the brown sugar in double boiler.
Add raisins.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and vanilla together. Pour over bread.
Do not stir.
Place over simmering water and cook for 1 hour; the brown sugar will form a sauce.
Serve warm or cold.
Turn onto serving plate to serve.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar and cocoa and mash together.
Add milk.
Stir well, then bring to a rolling boil for
1 minute. Take off stove and add remaining ingredients.
Stir as you add this last group of ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: seafood and peppers salad
directions: *Or use 2 red peppers.

title: old fashioned chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine, Wesson oil and sugar. Beat eggs and add to this mixture.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Mix.
Pour in 4 (8-inch) pans.
When cool, split layers crosswise and frost with Chocolate Frosting.

title: chocolate meringue pie
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Heat in double boiler.
Cook until thick; stir often.
Add beaten egg yolks. Cook 2 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla. Pour into baked 9-inch pie shell.

title: pizza macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown ground beef and onions; drain. Add tomato sauce and 1/2 teaspoon salt, Italian seasoning, oregano, pepper, garlic and ketchup.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Beat milk, egg and 1/2 teaspoon salt together.
Blend into macaroni and spread on greased jelly roll pan.
Cover with meat mixture; top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable stir-fry
directions: Combine oil, garlic, onion and mushrooms in a microwave-safe casserole.
Microwave on High, uncovered, for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Stir in cauliflower, carrots and pepper.
Cover with lid and microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes.
Stir once.

title: streusel-topped sweet potato custards
directions: Pour batter over nuts.
Bake at 325 degrees for 60-70 min. until wooden pick inserted in cake comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: dirt(dessert)
directions: Mix milk and pudding.
Add cream cheese and mix, then add Cool Whip, beating thoroughly.
Smash Oreo cookies and mix in by hand.

title: coconut cake
directions: Combine 1st 3 ingredients and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Mixture should be well chilled.
Next day, prepare cake mix according to directions.
Cut cake into 4 layers.
Turn, cut side up, and slice off brown layer to leave cake porous to allow topping to soak in.
Spread coconut mixture between layers and on top.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 3 days.

title: meringue
directions: Combine ingredients; beat until stiff.
Top pie and bake at 250° until meringue is brown, about 20 minutes.

title: crazy cake
directions: Put flour, white sugar, cocoa, soda and salt in an 8 x 8-inch cake tin (greasing not necessary).
Make 3 holes and put vanilla in one hole, Wesson oil in another hole and vinegar in the third hole.
Pour cold water over the top and stir complete mixture until smooth with a fork.
Bake at 320° for 40 minutes.

title: apple relish
directions: Grind 2 hot peppers and 5 onions.
Add salt.
Add boiling water.
Let it stand 15 minutes; drain.
Add apples that have been chopped with the skins left on and cores removed, vinegar, sugar and a cloth bag with whole spice, cloves and cinnamon inside.
Cook 10 or 15 minutes.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: frozen banana split salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce, if desired.

title: cajun spice(prudhomme)
directions: Mix and blend well.
Store in container.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Mix together cabbage, chicken, onion, almonds and sunflower seeds.
Mix together oil, water, uncooked Ramen noodles and seasonings, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Pour over chicken mixture; toss lightly.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Melt butter in large skillet.
Saute chicken until opaque but not brown.
Add salt and pepper.
Remove chicken.
Mix 1/2 wine and flour together.
Simmer until light golden brown (quick). Stir in oregano and rest of wine, chicken broth, oil and garlic. Mix well.
Put chicken in a dish.
Pour mixture over top.
In small bowl mix grated Parmesan cheese, bread crumbs and parsley. Sprinkle over top of chicken.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese. Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and place 1/2 mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix chicken or turkey, chopped onion and mayonnaise together and place on top of dressing.
Put remaining dressing on top. Beat eggs and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour over mixture.
Cover with foil.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking mix cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup and 3/4 cup milk.
Pour over mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: penne with plum tomatoes and cucumbers in basil vinaigrette
directions: Combine the tomatoes, oil, basil, vinegar and salt in a large bowl.
Cook the pasta in plenty of boiling salted water until firm to the bite, about 10 minutes; drain.
Combine the pasta, tomato mixture, cucumber, red onion and red peppers; toss to blend. Serve at room temperature.

title: caramel
directions: Put sugar, syrup, butter and 1 cup cream on fire; stir until the mass boils thoroughly.
Then stir in gradually so as not to stop the boiling.
Add second cup of cream.
Cook until thermometer reads 260° or hard ball stage.
Add vanilla and pour into 8-inch square pan.
Cool, cut and wrap.

title: hot potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; cool and cube them.
Set aside.
Cook bacon and crumble.
Mix all ingredients together except olives and bacon. Put in baking dish.
Top with olives and bacon.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add vanilla.
Add eggs and sour cream.
Mix until moist.
On stove, heat to boiling point the margarine, cocoa and water.
When mixture starts to bubble, take off stove and pour into first ingredients while stirring.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pineapple upside-down gouda cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line the bottom of a round 8 x 2-inch cake pan with parchment or waxed paper.
Combine melted butter, brown sugar and 1/4 cup pineapple sauce.
Pour into the prepared cake pan.
Arrange pineapple slices over mixture.
Set aside. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar with an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture and beat on low speed until well combined.
Stir in remaining pineapple sauce and cheese.
Pour batter over pineapple slices in cake pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes. Carefully invert onto serving platter.
Remove pan and paper. Serve warm with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken cacciatore with noodles
directions: Sprinkle chicken with seasoning mix, salt (if using) and pepper.
Brown chicken on all sides in 1 tablespoon of the oil in a large skillet.
As pieces brown, remove to plate.
Set aside. Saute onion and garlic in same skillet, adding the remaining oil, if necessary, until softened, about 3 minutes.
Pour in stewed and whole tomatoes with their liquid and the wine, breaking up tomatoes with wooden spoon.
Bring to boiling.
Add chicken. Lower heat and cover. Simmer for 25
to 30 minutes or until chicken is tender and no longer pink near bones.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve as a dip with chips, cucumbers, carrots, bell pepper, celery seed, squash and cauliflower.

title: orange slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender container.
Process until thick and smooth.
Pour into glasses.
Garnish with orange slices and mint.
Serve with straws.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix well.
Press mixture into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Beat cream cheese at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Gradually add powdered sugar, beating well.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over first layer, spreading evenly.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: pork chops willie
directions: Brown pork chops in a large skillet.
Add onion and mushrooms while browning.
Add paprika, dill, caraway seed and garlic.
Add water and lower heat to simmer.
Cover pan and simmer 10 minutes. Make egg noodles per directions on package.
Remove pork chops from pan.
Add yogurt to simmered spices in pan; mix thoroughly. Add yogurt mixture to egg noodles.
Serve as a side dish with pork chops.

title: apalachee bay crab quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a large bowl, gently combine crab, cheese, cream cheese, onions, peppers and mushrooms.
In a separate bowl, combine milk, baking mix, eggs, salt, cayenne pepper and nutmeg.
Using a mixer, blend 1 minute.
Pour crab mixture into a greased quiche pan.
Pour milk mixture over crab and bake 35 to 40 minutes or until
a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: pumpkin scones(diabetic)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a nonstick baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.
On wax paper, combine flour, baking powder, sugar, cinnamon, salt and cloves.
In large bowl, combine pumpkin and melted margarine.
Stir flour mixture into pumpkin mixture to combine.
Spray a work surface with nonstick cooking spray; roll pumpkin dough to 1/2-inch thick.
With fluted 2-inch cookie cutter, cut out 10 scones, re-rolling if necessary.
Place scones 1 1/2 inches apart on prepared baking sheet.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, or until lightly browned.
One scone = 60 cal., 1 gr. fat and 0 choles.
Makes 10 servings.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat together egg yolks, sugar and cornstarch.
Add corn and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Pour mixture into a buttered casserole dish and dot top with butter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve hot or cold.

title: crusty cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 325°. Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed of an electric mixer about 2 minutes or until creamy. Gradually add sugar, beating 5 to 7 minutes. Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears. Gradually add flour and salt, mixing at low speed just until blended; stir in vanilla. Pour into a greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan, and cool completely on wire rack.

title: date roll
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and cook slowly until it forms very soft ball.
Add chopped dates and continue cooking until mixture forms soft ball as for fudge.
Remove from fire and cool; add nuts and vanilla and beat.
When almost firm, form into rolls on wet cloth.
Roll in cloth and leave until cool.
Keep rolls in waxed paper until ready to cut.
Slice to serve.

title: cordon bleu
directions: Pound the chicken breasts with a meat pounder until they are flattened.
Layer each piece of chicken with a piece of ham, then sprinkle cheese on them.
Roll them up and put a toothpick in each of them to make sure they stay rolled up.
Place them in a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour the cream of chicken soup over them.
Bake in the oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: quick chicken dressing casserole
directions: Put chicken in baking dish.
Pour the soup over chicken.
Mix the stuffing mix as directions say, just until moistened.
Put over top of chicken.
Cook in the oven, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until chicken soup bubbles up through the dressing. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: spicy half-hour apple butter
directions: Put all the ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil.
Cook for 1/2 hour; stir often.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: elephant ear crispies
directions: Combine milk, butter, sugar and salt.
Allow to cool before adding yeast dissolved in water.
Add beaten egg and flour gradually.
Turn onto floured surface and cover with bowl for 15 minutes.
Divide dough into 2 parts and roll each out to about 10 x 12-inches.
Brush generously with softened butter.
Sprinkle with 1/3 cup sugar and 2 teaspoonfuls of cinnamon.
Roll like a jelly roll and slice about 1/2 inch thick.
Place slices on buttered cookie sheets and flatten with bottom of glass as flat as possible. Sprinkle with more cinnamon-sugar and let rise 20 minutes.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix all together. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving. Very good with all raw vegetables.

title: salsa delights
directions: Mix together and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up and refrigerate.
Slice when ready to serve and serve with salsa.

title: cilantro chili salsa
directions: Wash cilantro leaves and pull off stems.
Put peppers, onion and cilantro in blender and pulse to small chunks.
Pulse tomatoes a little and pour in a bowl.
Add salt and Accent.

title: carol's cookies
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add all ingredients, from top of list down.
Do not mix.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast in water until tender, cool and cut in bite size pieces; set aside.
Saute onion in butter and add remaining ingredients, except asparagus and almonds.
Simmer until cheese melts.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt margarine.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half. Stir until thickened.
Add Parmesan cheese; cook and stir until smooth.

title: meat casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper.
Add salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Add water and tomato paste to meat and cook 2 hours.
Mix together cream cheese, sour cream and cottage cheese and add a little salt.
Put half of noodles in casserole.
Cover with cheese mixture, remaining noodles and all meat mixture on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: olive nut sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, together.
Serve on plain sandwich bread.

title: chinese fried dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients except wonton skins together in a medium bowl.
Place dough wrapper on dumpling press, put filling in center, moisten edges with water and egg mixture and press closed to seal.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown or steam until meat is cooked.

title: microwavable peanut brittle(cook time:  9 minutes)
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir together sugar, syrup and salt.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Stir, then cook 4 minutes more.
Add margarine and vanilla; mix well.
Cook on High for 1 minute.
Add baking soda and stir quickly (mix will be foamy).
Immediately pour on lightly buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: stir and drop cookie(no sugar)
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with NutraSweet until covered.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: effie jo's coconut pecan cake
directions: Mix eggs, oil and water. Add cake mix. Mix well, then stir in the can of frosting. Grease and flour a Bundt pan and sprinkle 2 tablespoons powdered sugar in the pan. Chop 1/2 cup pecans and sprinkle in the pan. Pour batter over that and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put half of potatoes in the dish.
Make a sauce out of the other ingredients.
Put half of the sauce over the potatoes.
Use the other half of the potatoes on top and cover with the other half of the sauce mixture.
Bake, covered, for 50 minutes at 375°.

title: all-season jam
directions: Thaw berries and crush thoroughly.
Grate rind of one orange and add 1/2 teaspoon to berries.
Peel oranges and remove seeds, crush and add to berries.
Measure 1 1/2 cups of fruit mixture into large bowl.

title: pistachio tarte
directions: First Layer:
Mix the flour, butter, sugar and nuts all together, then press in nonstick 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 7 to 10 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool to room temperature.

title: tamale bites
directions: Combine cornbread mix, taco mix and salt with tomato sauce. Add cheese and egg.
Add ground beef.
Shape into balls, walnut size.
Bake 350° for 15 minutes.
Very good.

title: pepper jellied cream cheese
directions: Place cream cheese on serving plate and spoon a generous amount of pepper jelly on top.
Provide a small serving knife (butter knife) and serve with assorted crackers, Melba toast and bread sticks.

title: baked apricots
directions: Grease 9 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cover bottom with 1/2 of the apricots.
Crumble 1/2 of the crackers over apricots.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the sugar over the crackers.
Dot with 1/2 of the margarine.
Repeat and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: appetizer
directions: Cream ingredients together.
Spread mixture on tortillas. Roll up and refrigerate.
At serving, slice rolled tortillas and serve with your favorite salsa.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Add soup (undiluted).
Stir in brown sugar, mustard and ketchup.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt chocolate and peanut butter in top of double boiler. Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Pour in 8 x 8-inch pan lined with wax paper.
Put in refrigerator to chill.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: fish fillets
directions: In baking dish, microwave all ingredients, except fish, on High for 1 minute.
Add fish to dish.
Spoon sauce over.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 5 to 6 minutes, rotating once, if necessary, or until fish flakes with fork.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake until firm.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, cheese and seasoning mix together and spread in dish to form the bottom layer.
Dice individually the lettuce, tomatoes, peppers and onion, then layer in that order over the bottom layer.
Next, spread the Mozzarella cheese over the top. Serve immediately with nacho chips and salsa on the side.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put chicken, pickles and eggs through grinder.
Add turmeric. Thoroughly blend in enough mayonnaise to make smooth, creamy and easy to spread.
Makes approximately 1 quart.

title: garden brunch bake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease (or use nonstick cooking spray) a 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Place a layer of zucchini, tomatoes, onions (and meat) in dish.
Sprinkle with Parmesan and pepper.
Combine milk, biscuit mix and eggs.
Beat until smooth (about 1 minute) and pour over vegetables.
Bake about 30 minutes and let stand 5 minutes before cutting.
Top with salsa, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, chop up, add celery.
Mix other ingredients together and stir into chicken.
Add white grapes and pecans. Serve in a cantaloupe ring or on lettuce.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Mix honey, salt, pepper, vinegar and mustard with electric mixer.
Slowly add oil.
Mix until mixture thickens and oil disappears.
Add poppy seed and onion.
Yields 1 quart.

title: pineapple-peach jello salad
directions: Boil the pineapple with the juice.
Add jello and mix well. Remove from the burner and add the buttermilk and Cool Whip. After mixing all the ingredients, pour into a 2-quart dish.
Cover with foil and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar gradually; add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and beat.
Sift the flour, soda and salt together and add slowly to mixture, beating after each addition.
Pour into a greased 8 3/4 x 8 3/4-inch pan or may be baked in a loaf pan.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine chicken with all ingredients except tortilla strips. Warm tortilla strips in chicken broth.
Line casserole with half the tortilla strips.
Pour half of chicken mixture on top.
Repeat second layer and top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add egg yolks, cinnamon and water.
Then add flour, pecans and pineapple.
Beat egg whites and fold in last.
Bake at 325° for about 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Then, mix 1 cup powdered sugar and juice from pineapple and pour over cake while hot.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Sift flour, salt, soda and sugar. Add butter, milk and egg. Add to flour. Drop by teaspoon. Sprinkle with sugar. Preheat oven to 400° and bake 20 minutes.

title: stir-fried vegetables
directions: Turn on electric wok or use a large skillet.
Add 1 to 2 tablespoons of light oil.
Put all vegetables in wok or skillet. Add salt or seasoned salt, pepper, 1 teaspoon of sugar.
Stir vegetables for approximately 5 minutes (10 minutes if you like them softer).
Remove and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine cheese, soup, and milk. Microwave onion in butter until tender. Cook broccoli according to pkg. directions. Drain. Combine all ingredients. Divide between two well greased 1 1/2 qt. casserole dishes. Top with buttered bread crumbs. Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly (20-30 minutes). Can be frozen. If frozen leave crumbs off until ready to bake.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Moisten the cornstarch with 1/4 cup of water.
Boil together the remaining water and sugar.
Add the moistened cornstarch and cook for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly; add the grated rind and strained juice of the lemons, also the beaten egg yolks.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: heavenly bananas
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Peel the bananas and slice each one lengthwise.
Brown quickly over high heat.
Place half of banana slices on bottom of a buttered pie plate.
Cream the cheese until soft.
Add sugar and cinnamon, beating until light and smooth. Spread half of mixture on bananas.
Place the remaining bananas on top, then spread with remainder of the cream cheese mixture. Pour cream on top.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until almost all of the cream is absorbed and top is lightly brown.
(Do not allow all of the cream to be absorbed or will be too dry.)

title: bran muffin mix
directions: Pour boiling water over Nabisco 100% bran.
Let stand.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, buttermilk, salt and soda.
Fold in flour, Kellogg's All-Bran and then the 100% bran mixture.
Add raisins or dates if desired.

title: berry pudding squares
directions: Put half cake squares in a 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon pie filling over cake.
Top with remaining cake squares.
Combine pudding, milk and sour cream and beat until smooth.
Spoon over cake.
Chill several hours.
Cut into squares.
Makes 9 servings.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beef and onion until done. Drain off fat and add remaining ingredients.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan; add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Bring to a full boil and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Add oatmeal.
Stir well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let cool.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix cake mix with butter and 2 eggs.
Beat at medium speed for 1 minute.
Spread in bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: peach fizz
directions: Soften peach skins for easy peeling.
Use a small amount of water in the bottom of a bowl.
Add peaches.
Cover and steam for 1 to 2 minutes on Medium to High setting.

title: raggedy robins(cookies)
directions: Measure into a saucepan the sugar, cocoa, butter and cold milk.
Stir over medium heat and bring to a rolling boil.
Boil exactly 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Working quickly, drop onto wax paper with teaspoon.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: chicken wing appetizers
directions: Arrange wings in a single layer in a glass baking dish (9 x 13-inch).
Mix ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake in a 325° oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Mix together carrot, applesauce, oil, eggs, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and chopped nuts.
Add to first mixture.
Do not overmix.
Pour batter into a greased and floured loaf pan. Combine 5 tablespoons sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until pick comes out clean. Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: chicken capri
directions: Lay chicken in bottom of rectangular casserole dish.
Cover with Provolone cheese.
Pour entire bottle of dressing on top. Sprinkle bread crumbs to cover top of dish.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: curry soup
directions: Saute onion in butter; add flour.
Put all ingredients in blender and then heat slowly in a pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix broccoli, corn, egg and onion.
Put into a casserole dish. Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: yeast rolls(makes 36 rolls)
directions: Scald 1 cup milk.
Add shortening.
Cool.
Beat eggs and 1/2 cup sugar. Add salt, cool milk and shortening.
Add yeast dissolved in water.
Stir in flour.
Let rise for 4 hours. Refrigerate, then divide into 3 balls.
Spread soft butter on it. Cut into 12 wedges.
Roll each roll out side edge into point. Place on a cookie sheet.
Let rise for 4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in double boiler. Cook until thick. Pour into baked shell; top with beaten egg whites.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: homemade spaghetti sauce(makes 17 quarts)
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 1 hour. Add all the rest; boil another hour. Put in jars.

title: barbecue pork ribs
directions: Cover ribs with water; bring to a boil and simmer until almost done.
Line a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix all sauce ingredients together.
Put ribs in pan and cover with half the sauce.
Bake for 30 minutes; turn ribs over. Cover ribs with rest of sauce and bake 30 minutes more.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Boil chicken until tender and cut into cubes.
For sauce, mix together cream of chicken soup, broth and sour cream.
For the cracker mix, mix Ritz crackers, poppy seed and oleo.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Unmold.
Serve hot or serve cold.
For catsup topped loaf, spread 3 tablespoons catsup over top before baking.
Yields 8 servings.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
(Drain fat.)
Add tomato sauce, tomato paste and spices.
Let simmer.
Mix egg with cottage cheese; set aside.
Cook lasagne noodles until tender.
Drain well.

title: rainbow cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: cranberry compote
directions: Stir flour and sugar over fruit.

title: chocolate roll
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line jelly roll pan, 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch with foil or waxed paper. Grease.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt. Set aside.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast with 1 slice of bacon.
Grease bottom of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Cut dried beef in small pieces and spread over bottom of baking dish.
Lay chicken breasts on top, then cover with soup and sour cream mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 300° for 1 to 2 hours, until done.
Remove foil and bake for 15 to 30 minutes more.
Serve with rice and use sauce as gravy.
Serves 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Mix together soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, onions and egg. Put broccoli in a long baking dish that has been buttered. Pour mixture over top of broccoli, then sprinkle with cheese. Crumble up the Ritz crackers and put on top of cheese. Slice butter and put on top of crackers. Can be covered with plastic wrap and let sit overnight before cooking. Bake 350 degrees until brown and bubbly.

title: festive ham and cheese spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and soup mix until smooth. Stir in ham and cheese. Form into a ball or spoon into a plastic wrap-lined mold. Roll in parsley or sprinkle parsley on top. Refrigerate. Serve with crackers or party rye bread.

title: fried mushrooms
directions: Slice mushrooms as desired. Place in a bowl.
Add salt and hot sauce. Mix until all are coated well. Flour and fry on medium-high heat until golden brown.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix together cream cheese and pineapple.
Add oranges, bananas and cherries.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.
Add marshmallows before serving.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Let this cool completely. Beat until creamy the Crisco, margarine, sugar and vanilla. Combine the two mixtures and beat until it is the consistency of whipped cream.
Excellent on devil's food cake.

title: chicken liver pate
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; save fat.
Simmer chicken livers in stock until tender, about 15 minutes.
Put livers, 1/4 cup stock and remaining ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Pack in small crocks or jars.
Seal with layer of melted bacon fat or butter.
Refrigerate.
Shelf life 2 to 3 weeks if sealed.
May be frozen, but it becomes slightly crumbly.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.
Serve with crackers.
One of our favorites!

title: marinated sprouts
directions: Cook Brussels sprouts according to package directions; drain and cut large pieces in half.
Combine salad dressing, garlic, onion, parsley flakes and dill weed.
Pour over warm Brussels sprouts.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.
Drain; serve with cocktail picks.
Makes 2 cups, containing 13 calories each.

title: prudence island baked stuffed clams
directions: Wash and scrub quahogs well.
Place in pot to boil with enough water to cover.
Remove from shells and chop.
Reserve some quahog juice.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients well; pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and nuts.
Bake in preheated oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: quick, easy asparagus casserole
directions: In small casserole, put 1/2 of asparagus and spread 1/2 of soup over the top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese and cracker crumbs.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin loaf with caramel glaze
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Prepare and bake quick bread according to package directions.

title: chocolate cinnamon cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Melt butter.
Add cocoa and water.
Bring to a boil.
Add this to flour and sugar mixture. Add next four ingredients.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pepper biscuits
directions: Melt yeast in lukewarm water and mix well.
Let rise (cover) for at least 2 hours.
Bake in 400° or 500° oven.

title: humus
directions: Drain and mash the chickpeas well. Puree in blender. Beat oil and lemon juice and add to the chickpea mixture. Add salt, pepper and garlic to taste. Spread thinly on plate and make deep swirls. Dribble olive oil in the ruts. Decorate with chopped parsley, green olives and pickles. Serve with pita bread or crackers as an appetizer.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Mix well the night before.
Place half of the batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of the topping.
Add the rest of the batter and then the rest of the topping.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions; put in 4-quart pan.
Bring to a boil. Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from pot and drain.
Place back in pan and add sugar, vinegar, celery seed and mustard seed.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer 45 minutes.
Pour into clean hot jars and seal right away.
Makes up to 9 pints, depending on size of peppers and onions.

title: ground beef dinner
directions: Brown meat lightly in oil; add onion, green pepper, chili powder and salt.
Cook about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat; add tomatoes, beans and rice.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole and bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°. Sprinkle with cheese and olives; return to oven, uncovered, for 15 minutes.

title: trail mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl; mix gently.
Store in an airtight container.

title: bean salad
directions: Mix together vinegar, salad oil, salt, pepper and sugar.
Mix together beans, green pepper and onion.
Pour sauce over and refrigerate.

title: lazy day salad
directions: Drain all fruit and mix with pudding.
Add Cool Whip and put into deep dish.
Sprinkle with coconut and nuts.

title: mostaccioli with sausage
directions: Brown sausage, onion and pepper, then drain off fat.
Heat tomatoes, paste and water.
Add seasonings.
Stir in pasta, already cooked.
Pour all ingredients into a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: white sauce(this is an excellent sauce, good with any vegetable.)
directions: Mix flour, vegetable stock and milk together, then add melted oleo; heat to boiling or until thick (stirring constantly).
Add seasonings after sauce is cooked.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato candy
directions: Peel potatoes and mash in large mixing bowl.
Add sugar and vanilla gradually until mixture is consistency of dough.
Roll out on wax paper.
Spread generously with peanut butter.
Roll into log and chill for several hours or overnight.
Slice and store in refrigerator.
May be frozen.

title: five-bean soup(recipe includes diabetic exchanges)
directions: This tasty dish uses less sugar, salt and fat.

title: mrs. santa claus' nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

In a large bowl, mix the sugar, milk, Bisquick and egg. Beat hard for 30 seconds. Stir in nuts. Butter the bottom of a loaf pan. Pour batter into pan. Bake 45 to 50 minutes (until a toothpick stuck in the center of the bread comes out without any crumbs on it).

title: cookies while you sleep
directions: Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt; beat until stiff. Gradually add sugar; beat very thick.
Add almond and vanilla extracts.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Drop teaspoon of mix on cookie sheet.
Preheat oven to 350° for 15 minutes.
Put cookies in, close door and turn off oven.
Go to sleep and when you wake up, take out cookies.

title: clusters
directions: Combine the chocolate morsels, corn syrup and water in top of a double boiler.
Melt over hot (not boiling) water.
Remove from heat and stir in raisins and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Cool until firm.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: spinach rice pie(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray 9-inch pie pan with nonstick cooking spray. In large saucepan, heat milk until very hot but not boiling. Add all remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into sprayed pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mary beasley's blueberry muffins
directions: Mix with spoon. Dip batter into greased muffin pans. Bake at 400° to 425° until browned.

title: apple yambake
directions: Toss
apples
and
nuts
with
combined brown sugar and cinnamon.
Alternate layers of apples and yam in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Cover; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows over yams and apples; broil until lightly browned.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup; simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with sage if desired.

title: tex mex bake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread in a shallow baking pan. Top with ground beef followed by cheese.
Bake.
Serve with soft warmed tortillas.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: our favorite vinaigrette
directions: Measure mustard into a bowl.
Whisk in vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper and herbs to taste.
Continue to whisk mixture while slowly dribbling in olive oil until mixture thickens.
Adjust seasoning to taste.
Cover until ready to use.
(Vinaigrette is best if made just before it is to be used.)
If necessary, whisk again before serving.
Makes 1 cup.

title: sweet and sour apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine lemon juice, olive oil and half the garlic.
Rub chicken in this mixture.
Sprinkle with pepper. Arrange chicken in single layer in shallow pan.
Roast, uncovered, for 30 minutes.

title: tempura
directions: Mix together these ingredients and enough cold water to make batter thick enough to hold vegetables.
Beat batter until smooth.

title: stena's swedish pancakes
directions: Beat egg yolks with sugar, salt and melted butter.
Stir in flour and milk.
When ready to use, add well beaten egg whites. Melt a little butter in a pan.
Spoon a little batter in.
Bake until brown.
Makes 25 to 30 cakes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix together and cook in a hot skillet.
Makes about 6 medium pancakes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese soften.
Dice onions and ham; mix with cheese.
Form into ball.
Roll in walnuts (optional).
Chill and serve with crackers.

title: sausage roll
directions: Allow sausage and cheese to set out until almost at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients until completely smooth-textured mixture.
Form into a roll.

title: cranberry cream cheese mold
directions: Stir boiling water into gelatin in large bowl 2 minutes or until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water and cinnamon. Pour 2 cups of the gelatin into medium bowl.
Refrigerate about 1 1/2 hours or until thickened.
Reserve remaining 1 cup gelatin at room temperature.

title: frosted rice krispie bars
directions: Boil together granulated sugar and white Karo syrup in microwave 1 minute and 40 seconds.
Add peanut butter and vanilla. Add Rice Krispies.
Pat in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: layered salad
directions: Chop first five ingredients and layer in order in large bowl, lettuce on bottom.
Spread peas on top layer.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise together and spread on top like frosting.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top and top with bacon bits.
Serves 20.

title: beefaroni pot luck
directions: Using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch roasting pan, add enough oil to cover bottom of pan and heat on top of stove.
Add pepper strips and sliced onions.
Cook on medium heat.
Break up chopped meat and add to onions and peppers.
Meanwhile, cook macaroni until done (slightly firm).
When chopped meat is browned, add sauce.
Mix all together.
Let cook 5 to 10 minutes, turning heat down.
Drain macaroni and add to pan.
Mix together and cook through.

title: sherbet float punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid and juice; chill.
Add ginger ale and scoops of sherbet just before serving.

title: party dip
directions: Mix taco mix with refried beans.
Spread on large plate or platter.
On the bean mixture spread a layer at a time of the remaining ingredients in order given.
Serve with a variety of chips.

title: spinach lasagna
directions: Mix Ricotta cheese, egg whites, spices, spinach and Parmesan cheese.
Coat bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with thin layer of spaghetti sauce.

title: spinach and artichoke en casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a casserole.
Cook spinach and artichokes according to directions on the packages.
Drain well.

title: hawaiian dream cake
directions: Bake
cake as directed on package, except using pineapple liquid
and
additional
water to make up required liquid. Cool thoroughly.

title: peanut butter chiffon pie
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and butter; press firmly into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Cool.
Mix gelatin, 1/4 cup sugar and the salt in saucepan.
Add milk and yolks; cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.
Add peanut butter; stir until blended.
Chill.
Beat whites until foamy.
Gradually add 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff. Fold in peanut butter mixture, then fold in Cool Whip.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until firm (2 or 3 hours).
Garnish with chocolate syrup.

title: mmpossible taco pie
directions: Fry ground beef with onion; drain.
Add taco seasoning.
Spoon into an 8 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish (greased).
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Beat with wire whip until smooth.
Pour over meat mixture.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Take out and sprinkle cheese over top.
Put back in oven 2 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Remove the crusts from the bread; set aside.
Arrange bread slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with chicken.
Cover with the mushrooms and water chestnuts.
In a bowl, beat eggs; blend in milk, mayonnaise and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Arrange cheese on top.
Combine soups and pimientos; pour over cheese.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix ingredients and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until brown on top.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: german slaw
directions: Soak cabbage in cold water before shredding.
Mix cabbage, onion slices and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix salt, 2 teaspoons sugar, mustard and celery seed, vinegar and oil in saucepan.
Boil for 3 minutes and pour over cabbage mixture.
Cover and store overnight.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine brown sugar, butter and flour; set aside.
Peel and slice
each apple into about 12 wedges.
Place apples in a buttered 8	x 8-inch pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle
over
the apples.
Spread brown sugar mixture on top of apples.
Bake
30 minutes at 350°.	Delicious with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: Coat meat with flour and salt.
Combine soup, water, onion, bouillon, savory and garlic.
Stir in meat.
Cook covered on Medium 35 minutes.
Stir in carrots, cut up.
Cook on Medium 5 minutes. Add potatoes, cut up.
Cook on Medium 30 minutes.
Stir together cornstarch with 1/2 cup water.
Blend into meat mixture.
Cook uncovered on High until thickened and bubbly, about 3 minutes.

title: ham balls
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine ham, beef, eggs, milk and graham cracker
crumbs.
Shape
mixture
into
2-inch
balls. Place in 2 large, shallow roasting pans.

title: buttermilk pie 2
directions: Have butter soft. Add sugar; cream together well. Add flour and eggs; beat well. Stir in buttermilk and vanilla (dash of nutmeg if desired). Pour into unbaked pie shells. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. Place on wire rack to cool completely before cutting.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix and let set for a while.
Cook until thick.

title: fried cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal and salt.
Add boiling water to mix and stir. Drop by spoonful into hot oil in skillet and fry until golden and crispy.

title: spedini bread
directions: Slice bread longways or at 1-inch intervals almost through. Saute onion in butter; add mustard and poppy seed.
Spoon this mixture into cuts in loaf.
Insert Swiss slices.
Arrange bacon on top of loaf.
May be wrapped in foil and frozen at this point. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes (30 minutes if frozen) until cheese melts and bacon is crisp.

title: sunglasses chili
directions: Season
the
roast
with
garlic
salt and pepper, then brown in a large pan.
After browning, add water and cook for 1 hour. Brown the sausage in an iron skillet.
Remove sausage and
saute the
chopped onions and bell pepper with left over sausage
stock and 1/3 stick of butter.
Remove roast and cut into
cubes,
also remove
broth.

title: rice dressing(club member: lee higginbotham)
directions: Add all together in rice cooker and turn on. Must stir every 10 minutes. Add little water if it begins to stick before automatic bell rings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients except 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Bake in 1 1/2-quart buttered casserole dish at 325° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining Parmesan cheese and strips of pimento.
Serve warm with Doritos.

title: lee's fig cake
directions: Use Bundt pan and spray with Pam.
Combine ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Add milk and vanilla. Then add pecans.
Form into balls.
Melt chocolate and paraffin together in double boiler.
When melted, dip candy balls into mixture to coat and drain on wax paper.

title: hot tomato hamburger with rice
directions: Brown ground beef in hot fat, separating with fork as it cooks. Add green pepper strips and onions; continue to fry on medium heat for 5 minutes.
Drain excess fat.
Gently stir in seasoning, Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies, rice and reserved Ro-Tel liquid with water.
Cover, reduce heat to simmer and cook for about 15 minutes. Do not uncover or stir during last 15 minutes of cooking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mint pastries
directions: Dear Lord, I'm just an ordinary woman with a mean spirit today. Things haven't gone right from the time I got up.
You know how the children fussed at me because their school lunches weren't the kind they wanted, but Dear Lord, what else could I give them? It was all I had.

title: apple pecan muffins
directions: You will need 12 cupcake cups.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Pour 4 cups lukewarm water into bowl.
Dissolve 2 tablespoons yeast, then mix in 4 cups unsifted flour.
Let sponge sit covered with a towel in a warm place for 1 hour.

title: pfortchens 1
directions: Mix the first eight items together with 2 cups flour and beat well with beater.
Stir in the other 2 cups of flour with the raisins and butter.
Let raise for about 1/2 hour in warm place until double in size.
Use tablespoon dipped in hot oil then scoop up spoonful of dough size of small egg and drop into deep frypan containing at least two inches of hot oil.
Deep-fry for about two minutes.
When browned on one side, flip over.
Serve rolled in powdered sugar.

title: pizza muffins
directions: Cut muffins in half. Mix tomato paste, sugar and oregano; spread onto muffins. Place pepperoni, olives and cheese on muffins and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a medium size pot, add oil and mince the garlic.
Cook until golden.
Add sauce, using the sauce can.
Fill the can with water 1/4 of the way.
Pour into the pot.
Add fennel seed, onion, celery stick, bay leaves, cheese and sugar.
Stir.
Bring up to a boil and then simmer for 1 hour.
Stir and serve.

title: lobster newburg
directions: Melt butter; add flour.
Add milk gradually, stirring until thickened.
Add lobster and sherry.
Serves 4.
