title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Mix well; do not beat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Place first 6 ingredients in plastic bag and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning several times.
Place tortilla in oven wrapped in foil to warm.
Bring meat mixture to a hot temperature.
Place on tortilla and roll up.

title: chow-chow
directions: Sprinkle salt over vegetables; mix thoroughly. Let stand 3 to 4 hours; drain thoroughly. Press to remove liquid. Add sugar and spices to vinegar and simmer for 15 minutes. Add vegetables and heat to boiling. Pack relish, boiling hot, into sterilized jars, leaving 1/8 inch headspace. Adjust caps. Makes 8 pints.

title: washday cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix 1 cup of sugar, milk, flour, baking powder and salt; pour over butter.
Top with fruit.
Sprinkle with remaining 1 cup sugar.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: weenies in sauce
directions: Saute butter and onion together.
Slice hot dogs into little pieces and saute with the onion and butter.
After browning the hot dogs, pour in 1 can of tomato sauce plus 1 can water.
Add the spices and let simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: "dump" cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dump in the pineapple; spread around the pan.
Spread the cherries on top; sprinkle the cake mix on top of the fruits.
Add the nuts on top.
Place squares of margarine on top of them.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt.
Cook to hard ball stage or 248°.
(Cook at No. 7 on electric stove.)
Slowly pour syrup over egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat 1 minute on high speed; let cool 1 minute.
Alternate until mixture begins to change from glossy to dull in color.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Beat until candy holds shape.
Drop on waxed paper.
If mixture becomes too thick, add a drop of hot water.

title: austin's spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix together and heat on medium heat until tomatoes are slightly soft.

title: italian pork chops
directions: In large skillet, brown pork chops, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange in a casserole dish.
Slice peppers and onions. Put on top of pork chops.
Pour large can of tomato sauce over everything.
Sprinkle with oregano.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: turkey loaf
directions: In a bowl, place the ground turkey. Season with Mrs. Dash seasoning. Add bread crumbs and egg; mix together. Shape into a loaf.
Place in a pan and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Take out and pour the tomatoes over the loaf.
Put back in the oven for another 1/2 hour.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together
the
dry ingredients along with the green onions and peppers.
Blend
in the eggs; then add the milk and stir.
Add just
enough
buttermilk to get a mixture that will hold together when dropped from a melon ball scoop.
Drop into hot grease and fry until golden brown.

title: wonder chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mound dry ingredients and make 3 holes.
Pour oil, vinegar and vanilla into separate holes.
Pour the cold water over all.
Mix thoroughly with a fork until blended.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. This is great cake.
You mix, bake and serve from the same pan!

title: silly pie
directions: Beat
egg
whites
until
stiff.
Add
sugar and baking powder.
To
this
mixture
add 1 cup pecans, the crushed saltines and
the
vanilla.
Pour into greased pie plate (9-inch) and bake at
325° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Whip 1/2 pint cream.
Add 3/4 cup drained crushed pineapple.
Pour this on top of cooled pie.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in a well-greased casserole (2-quart size).
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter and stir until creamy.
Mix in cornflakes and make cookies.

title: pork stir-fry
directions: Cut pork into bite size pieces.
Brown in large skillet or wok.
Add frozen vegetables and seasonings.
Add a little water if necessary.
Cover and let steam about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve alone or with rice.

title: mexican chicken
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, place 1/2 bag of taco chips in a layer.
Put a layer of chunked chicken over chips.
In a saucepan, melt the cheese, then add the soup, onion and Ro-Tel tomatoes. When mixture is done and mixed well, pour over taco chips and chunked chicken.
Sprinkle taco chips over top.
Bake until heated throughout at 350°.

title: grasshopper dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in boiling water.
Add cold water and peppermint extract.
Measure 1 cup and chill until slightly thickened.
Pour remaining gelatin mixture into 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm and cut into cubes.

title: chocolate emeralds
directions: Combine 1/2 c. butter and cocoa in saucepan over low heat and stir until blended. Remove from heat and add 1/2 c. sugar, egg and vanilla. Stir in graham cracker crumbs. Mix well and press mixture into the bottom of a 13 x 9 inch pan. Next melt 1/2 c. butter and pour into a small mixing bowl. Add the creme de menthe and mix at low speed. While mixing, add 3 c. sugar until smooth. Spread this mixture over the first layer in the pan. Refrigerate entire dish for one hour. While the dish is chilling, combine 1/4 c. of butter and chocolate pieces into a saucepan over low heat. Stir until melted. Remove pan from the fridge and spread chocolate mixture over the mint layer. Return pan to fridge for 2 hours. Cut into small squares and store in fridge until ready to serve.

title: onion mushroom meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl combine all ingredients. In shallow baking pan shape into loaf.
Bake 45 minutes, or until done.

title: cheesy pretzels
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease cookie sheet.
Mix flour, milk, cheese, butter, baking powder, sugar and salt to a soft dough. Gently smooth the dough into a ball on floured board.
Knead 10 times.
Divide dough in half.
Roll half the dough into rectangle 12-inches long and 8-inches wide.
Mark and cut the rectangle lengthwise into 8 (1-inch) strips.
Fold each strip in half and seal.
Twist strip into pretzel shape.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients until light and fluffy. Mix and blend next 3 ingredients to sugar mixture. Fold in nuts and chocolate chips into mixture. Drop 2 inches apart from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: chocolate bit muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together three times. Cream shortening and sugar, add eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla. Fold in chocolate bits.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes in paper cups.
Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: spinach-artichoke casserole
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Add artichokes.
Saute onion in margarine and add with remaining ingredients.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: 1-2-3 chocolate cake(really rich and moist)
directions: Mix and sift first 2 ingredients.
Mix and bring to a boil next 3 ingredients; pour over dry ingredients.
Mix and add last 5 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes in a rectangular pan.

title: sweet or dinner rolls
directions: Melt yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Add milk to pudding mix and cook until thick; add oleo.
Let cool until lukewarm.
Add eggs, salt and yeast.
Mix in the flour. Place dough in well-greased bowl and let rise until double.
Knead down and let rise again.
Make into rolls as desired.
Let rise again.
Bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute margarine, chopped onion and chopped celery.
Mix this with all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes in large Pyrex dish.

title: lemon mousse
directions: Chill milk in small mixing bowl in freezer until crystals form around edges. Beat milk until thick. Add sugar in slowly, beating constantly. Add lemon juice and zest.

title: mock whipped cream frosting
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick.
Refrigerate for an hour or two.
Beat together the butter and sugar for 4 minutes.
Add milk and flour mixture.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Spread on cake or cupcakes. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Mix soup, sour cream and milk together.
Spray large Pyrex dish with Pam.
Place dry ingredients in 2 layers with 5 to 6 tortillas, chicken, onions, peppers and cheese in each layer. Pour soup mixture over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes. Serves 4 to 6.

title: preacher's punch
directions: Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Put all ingredients in a microwave bowl. Cook in microwave for 90 seconds. Stir.
Cook in 30 second intervals, stirring in between until all ingredients are melted.

title: white christmas candy
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler over simmering water, stirring constantly.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Add peanuts and pretzels; mix gently until coated.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar, margarine and vanilla.
Then fold in the whipped cream.
Spoon in crust and refrigerate. Can put grated chocolate on top.

title: english toffee
directions: Mix cracker crumbs, 1/4 cup butter and powdered sugar.
Spread 2/3 of mixture on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan.
Cream 1 cup butter with 1 1/3 cups sugar for 5 minutes, until light and fluffy. Combine chocolate, vanilla and 2 eggs or egg substitute.
Beat for 3 minutes; add to creamed butter and sugar.
Add 2 more eggs (or substitute) and dry milk.
Place in crumb lined pan; sprinkle remaining 1/3 of crumb mixture on top.
Chill 24 hours.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Blend dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat 5 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sugar roasted peanuts
directions: Combine all ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Boil until all water is out, stirring occasionally.
Put on a cookie sheet, separating the nuts as quickly as possible, spreading into one layer.
Bake at 325° until done or about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: nacho supreme
directions: Cook hamburger in onion until brown.
Add taco seasoning and cook to package directions.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Cut chicken into bite sized pieces.
Cook spinach according to package.
Heat oil in wok or skillet.
Place bread crumbs and basil in plastic bag with chicken pieces.
Shake to coat. Stir-fry chicken in oil until browned.
Spread drained, cooked spinach on top of chicken.
Cover with Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with lid until cheese is bubbly.

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs and cornmeal together add melted butter and milk. Beat well.
Add salt, and flavoring, mix well.
Last add whites of eggs, that have been beaten to a stiff mixture.
Drop into boiling shortening by spoonful and fry to golden brown.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, oil and eggs.
Beat well. Gradually add flour to make a stiff dough.
Knead lightly.
Put into greased bowl, cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Use as needed.
Knead daily until used up.

title: rancherettes
directions: Combine the dressing mix, savory, garlic and dill in a bowl. Add the oil and crackers. Place in a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes at 200° until golden.
Store in a covered container to keep fresh.

title: brownie cake
directions: Sift together sugar and flour; set aside.
Bring oleo, cocoa and water to a boil.
Add soda to buttermilk and combine with hot mixture.
Pour in the dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs and vanilla. Bake on greased and floured cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Frost while hot.

title: chicken and broccoli au gratin
directions: Melt
butter
in skillet.
Saute onions until transparent; remove
from heat.	Stir in flour, salt, curry powder and pepper. Drain
mushrooms,
reserving
liquid.
Add	water
to juice to make 1/2 cup liquid.
Gradually add to flour mixture in
skillet. Blend
in
evaporated
milk
until	smooth.
Add mushrooms;
cook and stir over medium heat until sauce begins to thicken.
Arrange broccoli spears and chicken on bottom of a 13 x
9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over; top with cheese. Bake at
for
20 minutes
or until bubbly around edges. Cool 15 minutes before serving.
Serves six persons.

title: baked beans
directions: Put ingredients in pot; stir and cook on medium-low heat for 1 hour. Great for cookouts!!!

title: beef noodle casserole
directions: Choose stew meat; cook in 3 tablespoons oil.
Add onions and cook for 2 hours.
Then add salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce, flour, ketchup and vinegar.
Pour 2 cups boiling water over mixture.
Cook noodles.
Now alternating in layers the noodles and meat mixture, place in casserole dish and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: paula's punch
directions: Combine juices; carefully pour in soda.
Chill with ice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake per directions in pizza pan.

title: oat loaf
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Add 4 1/2 cups rolled oats. Continue to cook 1 minute.
Put mixture into a nonstick bread pan and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with peanut gravy.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: tuna salad
directions: Drain tuna well and flake with a fork.
Place all ingredients in a small bowl and mix well.
Serve on lettuce with salad crackers.

title: microwave fried chicken
directions: In
shallow
baking
dish, mix egg white and water.
In another
shallow
dish,
mix
together
bread crumbs, paprika, salt,
garlic
powder, pepper and bay leaf.
Dip chicken first in egg
water	mixture
and then in bread crumbs, dredging to coat. Place
chicken on round glass dish with large pieces to the outside.
Place butter in one cup glass measuring cup and microwave
on
High
seconds
or
until melted.
Pour over chicken.
Microwave
chicken
uncovered on High for 5 minutes. Rotate
a quarter turn and microwave on High 5 minutes.
Cover chicken with waxed paper;
rotate a quarter turn and microwave 5 minutes more.
Remove from oven; let stand covered about 10 minutes.
Return to oven for additional cooking if fork cannot be inserted
in
chicken with ease when testing for doneness. Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna fish pie
directions: Bring to boil 2 cups milk.
Add flour mixed with 1/2 cup milk. Add salt, tuna and butter.
Cook until thick.
Pour into deep baking dish and add biscuits on top.
Bake at 350° until biscuits are brown.

title: southern style biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add shortening. Work until mealy.
Add soda to buttermilk and beat well.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture, roll out and cut.
Turn in well-greased pan and bake 12 to 15 minutes in very hot oven at 475°.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, milk, baking powder and salt.
Melt margarine in bottom of pan (13 x 9-inch), then pour batter in.
Pour fruit in center of batter.
Bake in a 400° oven about 30 minutes.

title: easy fruit dip
directions: Beat cream cheese and marshmallow cream at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Add juice and peel.
Serve with slices of fresh fruit.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: my mom's bread pudding
directions: Combine milk and eggs.
Pour over bread cubes.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch greased round baking dish.
Bake at 350° approximately 45 minutes.

title: steak san marco
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Place in large frypan with oil.
Cover with onion soup mix, tomatoes, spices and wine/vinegar.
Cook on simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serve with potatoes, rice or noodles.
Wonderful way to tenderize in an inexpensive cut of meat! You'll love the aroma as it cooks.

title: corn light bread
directions: Melt
and dissolve the sugar, salt and margarine in the scalded
milk.
Dissolve
the yeast in the 1/2 cup warm water. Combine
the
flour
and
meal in a large bowl.
To the flour-meal,
add
the milk mixture, yeast and eggs.
Stir until well blended.
Knead
on
a
lightly floured board until smooth and easy
to
handle.
This
will not take long.
Cut dough into 2 parts
and shape into loaves.
Place into 2 buttered loaf pans and let
rise
in
a
warm spot out of drafts until double in size. Bake
at
350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Brush with melted butter when almost done.

title: crock-pot spaghetti
directions: Brown the ground beef. Add the remaining ingredients, except spaghetti, and cook in crock-pot on high 3 to 4 hours or low all day. The last hour of cooking, add the noodles. Stir only a couple of times during the last hour (overstirring makes it mushy).

title: baby food bars
directions: Mix eggs, salad oil, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and vanilla. Add baby food and flour.
Bake in large jelly roll pan for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool, then frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: leg of lamb in oven(cosciotto d'agnello al forno)
directions: Preheat oven.
Wash
leg
of
lamb thoroughly; pat dry. Make 4 small slits
around lamb.
Insert cloves of garlic into leg.
Rub olive oil all over leg of lamb.
Place in baking pan with rack. Sprinkle salt
and
pepper to taste.
Cook at 450° for 15 minutes and then cover
and cook at 350° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Slice lamb and arrange on warm platter.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: swiss cheese salad
directions: Combine ingredients with Mustard Vinaigrette Dressing.

title: best carrot cake
directions: Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup.
Level off with knife. Mix all ingredients in large bowl.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: easy punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add any color food coloring you desire.
Add drops until you get desired color.
Serve chilled. Serves 30.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Place milk in sauce pan.
Mix together, salt, mustard, vinegar, have ready.
Bring milk to steam stage, do not boil.
Add cheese to milk and stir with a wooden spoon until it melts.
Add vinegar mixture, pimento, and pepper.
Let cool, place in a jar and refrigerate.

title: buttered carrots
directions: Cover carrots with cold water and cook until tender.
Skin and cut; place in microwave dish.
Add water (enough to cover bottom of dish).
Add oleo, sugar and salt.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.

title: pan-braised celery
directions: Put butter in saucepan, then celery.
Cook covered until celery sizzles.
Reduce heat.
Braise 4 to 5 minutes.
Add a few extra drops of water, if necessary. Cook only until crisp-tender. Season with salt.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine beans, milk, soup and 1/2 can onion rings; pour into 1 1/2
quart
casserole; bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes. Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy pizzas
directions: Spread small amount of sauce on buns. Sprinkle with cheese and toppings. Broil until cheese is bubbly. Fix as many as desired.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to directions (until tender).
Do not overcook.
Drain.
Add tomato (diced up), and cucumber and pepper (in small chunks).
Pour all dressing over mixture and toss. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Serve the same day.

title: apple brownies
directions: Mix together apples and desired amount of walnuts.
Set aside.

title: moira's candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until the outside skin peels off, and then peel them.
Slice potatoes into 1/4 in. slices and layer the bottom of a casserole dish.
Slice butter into pieces and sprinkle 1 c. to 1 1/2 c. of sugar.
Repeat layers until gone.
Bake at 375 to 425 degrees until syrupy.
Top with marshmallows.

title: pretzel delight
directions: Mix pretzels and margarine.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Cool.

title: nanny's peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Drop on ungreased cookie sheet by teaspoon.
Press crisscross with fork on top of each cookie.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 to 5 dozen cookies.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Add all ingredients at once and mix together. Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.

title: german slaw
directions: Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over above and mix.

title: layered cranberry-apple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin and sugar in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add cranberry-apple drink.
Chill 1 3/4 cup of mixture until partially set (keep remainder at room temperature).
Fold in cranberry sauce.
Pour into a 7 to 8 cup ring mold; chill until almost firm. Chill remaining gelatin until partially set.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: bubble solution
directions: Mix together and use right away or store it.
The longer it is stored, the better it becomes.
The corn syrup makes the bubble sturdier.
Use coat hangers for holders.
Wrap string around the hanger to make bigger bubbles.
Experiment using odd shapes.
It is fun!
Cut off the bottom of a large t-shirt and dip into the bubble solution; slowly open it up and slowly walk and watch a huge bubble form!

title: eggplant a la chance
directions: Brown eggplant in olive oil on both sides.
Sprinkle with salt and garlic salt.
In greased casserole, alternate layers of eggplant, pepperoni, Provolone and spaghetti sauce.
top with sauce and sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° about 20 minutes until warm through.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Lightly oil Dutch oven.
Put pie filling into bottom of Dutch oven.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of pie filling.
Pour can of pop on top of cake mix.
Stir pop into mix, but not into pie filling. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at about 350°.

title: mom's barbecue
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion until browned.
Add all the other ingredients and simmer for about 20 minutes or until thickened.
Stir in the ham and heat through.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: veggie rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (1/2 bag of cheese in and save 1/2 for top).
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add ground beef, salt and pepper. Heat through, but not browning.
Spread half shredded cabbage in 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with meat mixture.
Top with remaining cabbage.
Pour tomato soup over the top.
Cover.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
For change, I add 1 cup of instant rice in meat mixture. Works in slow pot.
Good.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs and salad oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, 1 cup chopped nuts and bananas. Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Spread frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with 1 cup chopped pecans.
(May be baked 1 hour in a greased and floured tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.)

title: 6-week bran muffins
directions: Add soda to boiling water; let cool.
Cream the shortening and add sugar, then add eggs one at a time.
Stir in buttermilk, flour and salt.
Add water-soda mixture.
Stir in all-bran, bran flakes, dates and nuts.
Store in covered container in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks.
Bake as needed.
Spoon into muffin tins without stirring.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°, less for small muffins.

title: king ranch chicken(student favorite)
directions: Mix tomatoes and soups.
Cook chicken and chop.
Alternate layers of tortillas, chopped chicken, cheese, chopped onions and the soup mixture.
Top with shredded cheese and bake at 350° until heated and the cheese is melted.

title: mini pizzas
directions: On greased baking sheet, flatten biscuits to 4-inch circles. Top with pizza sauce and toppings.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are slightly brown.

title: homemade waffles
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order they are
written.
Beat very good.
Add melted margarine.
Fold in egg whites.

title: scrumptious muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Prepare miniature tin with liners or grease with butter and flour.
Combine ice cream and flour in medium bowl and stir until wooden spoon is just moistened.
(Do not overmix.)
Fill liners 3/4 full.
Bake about 20 minutes or until tester comes out clean.
Makes 12 miniature muffins.

title: shrimp harpin
directions: Cook shrimp in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Place in a 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and salad oil.

title: swiss green beans(6 servings)
directions: Melt butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper, sugar and onion. Add sour cream gradually.
Fold in green beans and heat thoroughly.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine cereal and grated cheese; sprinkle over beans.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix and knead until real hard.
Let rise until double.
Roll out in biscuits.
Let rise.
Cook until done.
Butter tops.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chuck wagon beans
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In Dutch oven or large pan, fry bacon until crisp; drain fat and set aside.
In same pan, cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water.
Stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture and bacon pieces. (Save about half of bacon to crumble on top of mixture.)
Cover; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Serve with hot corn bread or biscuits.
Makes 12 servings of 1 cup each.

title: bread pudding with whiskey sauce
directions: Break bread into small pieces and place in a shallow bowl. Add half and half and milk.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Crush mixture with hands until blended.
Add eggs and next 7 ingredients, stirring well.
Pour melted butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish; tilt dish to coat evenly.
Spoon pudding mixture into dish. Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until pudding is very firm. Remove from oven.
Let cool.
Combine 1/2 cup shredded coconut and 1/2 cup chopped pecans; stir well.
To serve, cut pudding into squares.
Place each square in an ovenproof dish.
Place dishes on baking sheet.
Pour Whiskey Sauce evenly over squares, and sprinkle evenly with coconut mixture.
Broil 6 inches from heat until sauce is bubbly and coconut is lightly browned.
Serves 15.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Cream 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine.
Add pretzels.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Add Cool Whip, mix and spread over pretzel crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and let partially set. Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: bean and potato casserole
directions: Brown your beef and drain.
Place in casserole dish.
Mix beans and soup in and stir (don't add water to soup).
Place potatoes on top and bake at 350° for 20 minutes, just until heated through. Also great with cheese on top.

title: raspberry cocktail
directions: Mash currants and strain.
Pour juice over well picked over fine raspberries.
Chill well.
Serve in glasses very carefully so that raspberries may be preserved whole.
If desired, a little powdered sugar may be placed on top when serving.
Serves 6.

title: butterscotch buns
directions: Place frozen bread balls in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle on top.
Sprinkle butterscotch pudding on top.
Melt margarine; mix in brown sugar and pour over top.

title: quicke italiano
directions: Mix milk, biscuit mix, eggs, butter and pepper in blender for 15 seconds.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
In small skillet, cook pepperoni, green pepper, onion and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Stir in oregano.
Add pepperoni mixture into pan (with biscuit mixture) and then add 1 cup of Mozzarella to mixture. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup of Mozzarella onto top of quiche and bake for 2 minutes longer.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients well.
Add onion and eggs.
Stir in beer, approximately 3/4 can, until right consistency.
With spoon, drop into deep fryer and cook until golden brown.
Serves 2 to 3 dozen.

title: homemade chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken until tender in water with seasoning, celery and onion. Remove chicken; cool and cut into small pieces and return to broth. Add bouillon cubes; bring broth to boil and add noodles. (Water may need to be added to the broth.) After noodles are cooked, add the cream of celery soup and heat through.

title: "fit for company chicken"(or 3 meat dinner)
directions: Slice the 4 breasts in half.
Roll the 8 pieces of chicken with the 1/2 slices of bacon; 2 half slices per breast in either direction.,
Place atop a dried beef lined baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Combine soups and sour cream; pour over the top of rolled chicken breasts. Cover with remaining slices of dried beef. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Serve over rice or with mashed potatoes.

title: cinco de mayo fiesta bean dip
directions: In medium saucepan, combine refried beans, Ro-Tel tomatoes and chiles and sour cream.
Stir over medium heat until hot.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chopped tomato, onions and olives.
Pour into serving dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: american chop suey or chow mein
directions: Cook for 1 minute.

title: left over vegetables
directions: Melt butter in large skillet or fry bacon.
Add croutons. Brown and season as desired.
Add tomatoes.
Add leftover vegetables.
Heat thoroughly and sprinkle with grated cheese. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: honey orange sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and heat 5 minutes, but do not boil. Serve on ice cream, waffles, pancakes, hot rolls, biscuits, toast, etc.

title: dawnay's peanut clusters
directions: Melt both chocolates together, then stir in peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Bake or boil chicken; cut into bite size pieces.
Saute onions and mushrooms in butter and garlic until done.
Cook rice per directions and stir in mushroom soup.
Mix chicken and sauteed mushrooms and onions.
Line bottom of casserole dish with rice mixture.
Spread chicken mixture on rice.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy pasta salad
directions: In a large bowl combine pasta, vegetables and turkey.
In food processor or blender puree remaining ingredients; pour over pasta mixture.
Toss to coat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: quick swedish meatballs
directions: Combine meat,
cheese,	soup
mix,
salt, nutmeg, bread crumbs and 1/2
cup
milk.
Shape	into
about 40 small balls. Brown lightly in	skillet.
Cover
and
cook 20 to 25 minutes. Blend in flour into 2
cups	milk and 1/2 cup of the grease to make gravy.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream butter with vanilla.
Add salt and gradually add confectioners (10x) sugar, beating thoroughly after each addition. Stir in milk and beat until frosting is of spreading consistency.

title: shirley's original pineapple and cream cheese spread
directions: Mix above ingredients together and spread onto sandwiches.

title: chicken supper
directions: Combine onions, celery and chicken broth in saucepan. Simmer 20 minutes. Combine in 2-quart casserole the soup, sour cream, chicken, mushrooms, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and cooked vegetables. Mix well. Drop biscuits by teaspoon into casserole. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown. Sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: sangria
directions: Thaw lemonade, but do NOT dilute. Combine with wine and lemon juice. Add soda slowly. Garnish with thinly sliced oranges and lemon. Serves 12.

title: cherry chill salad
directions: Mix and chill in refrigerator.

title: a different carrot cake
directions: Combine liquid mixture and add dry ingredients.
Bake in well-greased and floured 9 x 13 pan for 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: meat balls
directions: Soak bread in milk, squeeze and shred.
Add to bread: the meat, eggs, parsley, chives, lemon rind, butter, half of both cheeses, salt and pepper.
Mix very well.
Make balls about 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Combine salt pork and olive oil in skillet, heat and add onions and garlic.
Cook until brown.
Add meat balls and brown.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add balls to sauce and continue cooking for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with remaining cheeses.
Serve over angel hair pasta.

title: chicken pie
directions: Debone cooked chicken and put in casserole dish.
Mix broth and soup. Pour over chicken.
Mix margarine, flour and buttermilk. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 425° about 40 minutes in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
(I bake it at 400° for 1 hour.)
Serves 8.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Layer as follows: pineapple, coconut, brown sugar and cake mix.
Cut up margarine and layer on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle nuts on top of margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: great-grandmother edith mcatee's fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla.
Stir constantly.
Test with the soft ball in cold water method.
When done, cool in pan in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Beat until firm.
Pour onto a greased platter.

title: oven fried fish fillets
directions: Coat fillets with mayonnaise.
Combine bread crumbs, parsley and paprika.
Dredge coated fillets in bread crumb mixture.
Place fillets on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.
Bake in preheated 450° oven for 12 minutes or until fillets flake easily with fork.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Mix cake according to box directions. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan. Punch holes in cake with fork and pour can milk on top, then pour pineapple and juice on cake. Sprinkle on pecans. Let cool. Spread with Cool Whip. Sprinkle with coconut. Keep refrigerated.

title: salmon casserole special
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot olive oil until soft.
Add next 7 ingredients and simmer 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: brunch ham and broccoli bake
directions: Place 4 slices bread in a lightly greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle
ham
and broccoli over bread; top with remaining bread
slices.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients, stirring well;
pour
over
bread.
Sprinkle
with
cheese and paprika. Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and golden
brown.
Serve immediately.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: carrie's beaver house cookies
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a rapid boil; take off heat. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto wax paper.
Let cool 45 minutes.
Ready to eat.

title: linguine with white clam sauce
directions: Drain clam juice from clams; reserve.
Saute onion and garlic in oil and margarine in large skillet until tender, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Add reserved clam juice, oregano, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil over high heat.
Cook until reduced to one cup, about 5 minutes.

title: green rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on package.
Add soup and Cheez Whiz to hot rice.
Saute chopped onion in margarine.
Pour boiling water over frozen broccoli and drain.
Add broccoli to sauteed onion. Stir into rice.
Pour in casserole dish and cook in oven until it bubbles at 350°.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Set aside.

title: vegas hot rolls from mirage hotel
directions: Mix yeast into milk.
Mix dry ingredients and add to yeast and milk.
Mix good; put in icebox 4 hours before baking.
Make into rolls.
One hour before baking, let rise; dot with butter.
Bake on cookie sheet at 425° for about 30 minutes.

title: banana cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine oats, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl with mixer at medium speed, beat peanut butter and margarine until smooth. Beat in sugars until blended.
Beat in banana, egg and vanilla. Stir in flour mixture.
Drop dough by one-fourth cupfuls, about 5 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheets.
With spatula, spread dough into 3 1/2-inch circles.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.
Let cool on cookie sheets for 4 minutes. Remove from cookie sheets; cool completely on a wire rack.
If desired, pipe a stars or stripes frosting design, using plain piping, onto each cookie.
Store in a tightly-covered container. Makes about 24 cookies.

title: hoover's chocolate cake(that's patsy, not j. edgar)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except boiling water, in a mixing bowl.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Add boiling water and mix in.
Pour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 layer pans.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix cornbread mix, corn and milk.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Saute chopped onion in margarine until translucent.
Add sour cream, salt and 1/4 cup cheese.
Pour over cornbread mixture and top with other 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham and cheese roll
directions: Roll crescent rolls on greased sheets until making one large square.
Place all ingredients on rolls and jelly roll until all are sealed.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add Bisquick, margarine and sugar and beat together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
No crust needed!

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown sausage in a large skillet. Remove sausage from skillet and drain. Add onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until lightly browned. Add rice.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Stir in sausage, ham, tomatoes, chicken broth and seasonings. Bring to a boil.
Pour into 4-quart casserole. Bake, covered, in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally. Place shrimp on top and bake, covered, for 10 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs, gradually adding sugar until well mixed.
Add the vegetable oil and beat.

Mix together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon and baking powder, then add to the egg-sugar-oil mixture together with the zucchini in small amounts, alternating first the dry and then the zucchini mixture.
Add nuts, raisins and vanilla.
Have ready 2 greased and floured loaf pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for 55 minutes or until loaves test done.
Remove and allow to rest on cake racks for about 10 minutes before turning out.
Bread cuts better when cool.
It may be iced with a light confectioners sugar-water glaze.
May be frozen for up to 6 months.

title: fools toffee
directions: In saucepan over medium-high heat, blend butter and brown sugar.
Heat to boiling and boil 4 minutes.
Cover a cookie sheet (or jelly-roll pan) with foil and butter lightly.
Place single layer of crackers on foil close together.
Pour butter mixture over crackers, spreading evenly.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Allow to soften, then spread evenly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until cool. Cut into squares with a knife or pizza cutter.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Can be kept 1 to 2 weeks.
Also can be frozen.

title: living waters salad
directions: Dissolve lemon gelatin in 1 cup hot water in top of double boiler.
Add marshmallows and stir to melt.
Remove from heat and add 1 cup drained pineapple juice and cream cheese.
Beat until well blended and stir in pineapple.
Cool slightly.
Fold in whipped cream and mayonnaise; chill until thickened.
Pour into long pan and chill until firm.

title: peanut butter kiss cookies
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Add brown and white sugar. Beating at medium speed
until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beating well.
Combine flour, baking soda, and salt to creamed mixture; mix well.
Then shape dough into 1-inch balls and roll in additional sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 8 minutes.
While cookies are still hot from the oven, press a chocolate kiss into the top of each cookie.

title: applesauce drop cookies
directions: Sift flour; measure and sift again with the soda, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Cream the shortening and gradually add the sugar.
Beat until creamy, then add the egg and mix thoroughly. Add the sifted dry ingredients to the shortening mixture alternately with the applesauce.
Add the raisins and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon onto a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add flour a little at a time to mix. Mixture will be crumbly.
Spread onto greased cookie sheet. Sprinkle with sugar decorations to cover.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until edges get golden brown.
Let cool.
Cut into 4 x 2-inch strips (approximately).
Yields 15 to 20 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients. Cook in double boiler, stirring often, until thickened. Alternate layers of crackers and sliced bananas and pudding mixture.

title: spaghetti and meat balls(for crock-pot)
directions: Mix all ingredients in crock-pot and cook on low heat for about 6 hours.
Stir often.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together sugar, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini and dry ingredients.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Place in blender, mayonnaise, catsup, dehydrated onion, sweet relish and hard-boiled eggs. When cool, add to the blender. Blend at lowest speed for only seconds, until the eggs are chopped. Stir and refrigerate (covered). Serve over lettuce wedges.

title: pecan tarts
directions: Combine flour and 1 stick margarine with softened cream cheese. Mix well until dough consistency.
Chill for one hour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place with fingertip into tart pan.
Press with finger.
Set aside.

title: pan-roasted chicken and vegetables
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
In large roasting pan, (17 x 11 1/2-inch), combine potatoes, onion, garlic, oil, salt and pepper and rosemary; toss to coat.

title: old fashioned dumplings
directions: Combine flour, baking
powder
and
salt.
Add	chicken broth and
oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened. Turn dough
onto floured surface and form a ball.
Roll dough to
a thickness
of
1/16-inch.
Cut
into 5 x 1-inch strips. Drop dumplings into boiling broth;
cover and cook 15 minutes or until dumplings are tender.

title: family favorite chicken
directions: Brown chicken in margarine.
Saute onion.
Set aside.
Combine dry chicken noodle soup with all rice, rosemary and 2 cups water. Bring to a boil and put in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Top with browned chicken and onion.
Cover.

title: quick and easy peanut butter brownie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine brownie mix, flour, oil, water and eggs in large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in peanut butter chips. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand a few minutes before removing from cookie sheet.
Cool completely before serving them to the kids!

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin in a bowl.
Sift dry ingredients and add to bowl.
Mix in 2/3 cup water.
Fill soup can 2/3 full for individual loaves or 9 x 5-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bishop's cake
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add nuts and fruit last.
Bake in moderate oven at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Roll cubed beef in flour and brown slowly in a heavy pan.
Add water and next 10 ingredients to meat and simmer at least 2 to 3 hours.
Add carrots, potatoes and celery.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Some water may need to be added when vegetables are added to meat.

title: taco ring
directions: Mix hamburger and taco seasoning according to package directions! On greased cookie sheet or pizza stone, separate and lay crescents in a triangle ring overlapping thick sides. Roll dough flat with tips toward outside. Scoop hamburger mixture on inner crescents and add cheese on top. Pull top of crescents over hamburger mixture to form ring. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grandma's jam cookies
directions: Blend together Crisco, sugar, salt, vanilla and egg.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in flour.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Make a small dent in center and fill with jam.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill 1 hour.
Roll out dough and cut into shapes.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: tumbleweeds
directions: Combine peanuts and potato sticks in a bowl and set aside. In a microwave, heat butterscotch chips and peanut butter at 70% power for 1-2 minutes or until melted, stirring every 30 seconds. Add to the peanut mixture, stirring to coat evenly.
Drop by rounded tablespoons onto waxed paper lined baking sheets. Refrigerate until set, about 5 minutes.
Store in an air tight container. Makes about 4 1/2 dozen.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in lightly buttered casserole and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: whata sugar cookie
directions: Place German's sweet chocolate, chocolate morsels and marshmallow cream in the large bowl of an electric mixer.
Combine the sugar, milk, butter and salt in a heavy 3 or 4-quart saucepan. Bring to a boil over high heat, stirring constantly.
When the mixture comes to a boil, lower the heat to medium and set a time for six minutes.
Keep the mixture boiling steadily and stir constantly during this time to prevent scorching.
At the end of six minutes, pour the boiling syrup over the chocolate and marshmallow cream.
Beat until the chocolate is melted and the ingredients are well blended.
Fold in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a lightly buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Let the fudge cool at room temperature for 24 hours before cutting.
Cut into 1-inch square pieces and pack in airtight containers.

title: gumdrop cookie bars
directions: Beat eggs well in mixing bowl.
Add water, salt, sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Sift flour, baking powder and cinnamon together.
Cut gumdrops finely into flour mixture.
Mix all together.
Bake in greased shallow 10 x 15-inch pan at 275° for 50 minutes.
Cut into squares while warm and cover with powdered sugar.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix in large bowl.
Save 1/2 of M&M's for decorations.
Yields 2 to 3 dozen.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken cut into small pieces in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Pour soups and sour cream mixed over chicken. Put cracker crumbs over this and melt the oleo and pour over all. Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.
tags: cream of chicken soup with mushrooms

title: farmhouse cookies
directions: Mix as listed to a soft dough.
Roll out on flour surface.

title: squash pickles
directions: Put a layer of squash and a layer of onions in a large bowl. Sprinkle each layer with salt.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain off excess liquid.
Heat other ingredients and pour over vegetables. Bring to a boil.
Spoon into jars and seal.
Chill at least 24 hours before serving.
This makes about 2 quarts of pickles.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Mix together in food processor or blender.

title: cottage potatoes
directions: Mix all in large bowl.
Pour into baking dish; sprinkle corn flake crumbs over top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: play dough
directions: Cook over medium heat (except coloring) until mixture pulls away from sides of pan and becomes like play dough consistency; add coloring.
Knead until cool.
Keeps 3 months unrefrigerated if kept in airtight containers.

title: peanut cookies(very good for christmas)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg.
Sift together flour and soda.
Add flour mixture and oatmeal to shortening mixture.
Add corn flakes.
Add peanuts.
Bake on a greased cookie sheet.
(They do not spread but make them small.)
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: good for you chili
directions: Put all ingredients together in 4 or 5 quart pot.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered 30 to 35 minutes until bulgar is tender.
Serve with the following garnishes:
low fat sour cream, plain low fat yogurt, shredded reduced fat Cheddar cheese or sliced scallions.
Serves 6. Per serving:
228 calories; 11 g. protein; 45 g. carbohydrate; 2 g. fat; 0 mg. cholesterol; 946 mg. sodium; 12 g. fiber.

title: chocolate lunch box bars
directions: Cream sugar and butter until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, chocolate and nuts.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in boiling water until tender; mash. Combine potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and 1/2 cup butter; beat at medium speed until smooth.
Spoon into buttered casserole dish.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix corn meal, sour cream, eggs and oil.
Beat well.
Combine meal and baking powder.
Stir well.
Pour into greased 10-inch iron skillet.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until brown.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Drain fruit and mix all together.
Put in refrigerator to chill.

title: hawaiian kabobs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Pour mixture into shallow dish.
Add chicken, tossing gently to coat.
Cover and marinate at least 1 hour in the refrigerator, stirring mixture occasionally.

title: hot and spicy wings
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle chicken with lemon pepper and garlic salt.
Roast, covered, in oven for 30 minutes.
Remove cover, add 5 ounces of hot sauce and simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle 5 ounces of Tabasco over wings and keep warm until ready to serve.
Wings may be brushed with a tablespoon of margarine.
Dip in Blue cheese dressing.
Delicious!

title: easy fudgy bars
directions: Cook pudding with milk according to directions, bringing just to a boil to thicken.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cake mix.
Spread in 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan, sprayed with Pam.
Sprinkle top with chocolate chips and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: With scissors, cut 1 pound orange slices in 1/2 cup flour (not included in the 2 cups).
Mix first three ingredients well and then dry ingredients and the rest.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 10 minutes at 350°.

title: green pepper steak
directions: Cut steaks into strips.
Sprinkle with garlic salt and meat tenderizer.
Saute until outside is brown.
Add Worcestershire sauce and soy sauce.
Slice onion and peppers.
Add to steak.
Add water.
Cook, covered, for 20 minutes on medium heat.

title: beef and potato bake
directions: In 1 1/2-quart baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper. Press to form shell.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: sarah's praline grahams
directions: Separate crackers into 4 sections.
Arrange on cookie pan with sides touching.
Bring to a boil the butter, sugar and pecans. Cook for 3 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour and spread over the graham crackers.
Bake 12 minutes at 300°.
Remove from pan and cool on waxed paper.
Yield:
3 1/2 dozen.

title: festive tossed salad
directions: Chill spinach and red lettuce in large salad bowl.
Arrange on top the red onion, Bleu cheese, mandarin oranges and pine nuts. Toss with dressing of your choice.
Serves 12.

title: steak fondue marinade
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Combine other ingredients and pour over steak.
Marinate several hours or overnight. Cook in hot oil for 5 minutes or until done.

title: root beer angel food cake
directions: Put cake mix into bowl and substitute root beer for water. Follow mixing instructions and baking instructions on label.
tags: Betty Crocker white angel food cake mix

title: texas potatoes
directions: Chop potatoes into small pieces (cube size).
Spread in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix the other 3 ingredients together and pour over potatoes.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Cover with foil when baking.

title: broccoli balls(appetizer)
directions: Mix together the oleo, onion, pepper, garlic salt, Parmesan cheese, stuffing mix and eggs.
Add the broccoli.
Chill and roll into balls (the size of walnuts).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: swedish rice pudding
directions: Put milk and rice in top of double boiler.
Cover and cook over hot water (low heat) until rice is tender.
Stir and test from time to time. Beat until blended the eggs, sugar and flavoring.
Add small amount of rice and milk mixture.
Then return all to top of double boiler, mixing well.
Let remain on heat for 2 to 3 minutes longer (165°).
Cover and cool.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzel sticks, melted butter and sugar; press into 13
x 9-inch
baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.	Let cool completely.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all but last 3 ingredients, then mix them in separate bowl until crumbly.
Sprinkle on apples. Bake, uncovered, until brown, for 30 minutes.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Pour melted oleo over and mix. Put 1/2 of the mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put vanilla ice cream over crumbs and spread remaining mixture on top.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into squares and serve with chocolate sauce.

title: slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients; flatten slaw in bowl.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes to chill.

title: 1-pot hamburger goulash
directions: Cook hamburger, onion and garlic.
Add next 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Stir in pasta and seasonings and reduce heat. Simmer, stirring occasionally, until pasta is done and goulash is no longer watery, about 20 minutes.

title: vidalia onion dip
directions: Stir ingredients together and bake at 350° until bubbly on top, about 1 hour or more. Good and easy.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken and broccoli separately.
Place in 8 x 13-inch pan broccoli, then cut up chicken.
Pour soup mixture on top. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes, or until bubbly.
Serve with rice.

title: coconut topped oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and set aside.
Mix flour with soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Cream margarine. Gradually add white and brown sugar, blending until mixture is mealy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until light and fluffy. Stir in oats, then flour mixture and blend thoroughly.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook, cool and debone the chicken the day before, reserving broth.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Place meat in baking dish; refrigerate until the next day.
Chill broth in bowl; separate from chicken.
Remove cold fat from broth and heat.
Mix together 1 cup water and cornstarch to make paste; add to broth. Cook until gravy thickens, then add food coloring and Kitchen Bouquet.
Add chicken and peas; mix well.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, peanut butter and chocolate chips together.
Pour over Crispix and coat well.
Put powdered sugar in large bag; add Crispix mixture and shake and turn to coat well.
Pour out onto cookie sheet and cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: beef tenderloin steaks with gorgonzola
directions: Let meat rest 10 minutes before beginning dinner preparation. Place a large, flat griddle or skillet over high heat. When hot, using a pair of tongs and a folded paper towel, wipe the cooking surface with oil and place steaks on hot pan. Caramelize the steaks, 2 minutes on each side. Reduce heat to moderate. Season meat with salt and pepper and cook 4-5 minutes longer on each side.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and water together to 250° or to hard ball stage.
Add butter and peanuts; continue cooking until syrup is golden brown and quite brittle when put in cold water.
Stir constantly to keep peanuts from sticking or burning.
Remove from heat; stir in vanilla and soda.
Stir quickly until it foams up. Pour out on well oiled surface.
When it has cooled, turn over and stretch thin.

title: creme anglaise(vanilla custard sauce)
directions: In a bowl, beat together the yolks and the sugar until the mixture is light and forms a ribbon when the beater is lifted. Add the half and half, scalded, in a stream, stirring.
Transfer the custard to a heavy saucepan and cook it over moderately low heat, stirring
until it thickens, but do not let it boil. Remove the pan from the heat and stir in the vanilla.
Strain the custard through a fine sieve into a metal bowl set in a bowl of ice.
Let it cool, stirring occasionally, and chill it, covered.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: spiced red cabbage(rode kool)
directions: Remove the outer leaves of the cabbage.
Cut the cabbage in halves. Remove the core.
Wash and shred cabbage very thinly.

Put a little butter or margarine in a saucepan and 1 cup of water. Add the red cabbage, cloves, peeled, cored and sliced apples and simmer the vegetables with a tight fitting lid on the pan for 3/4 hour.
Add the rest of the butter or margarine, sugar and some vinegar and simmer for another 5 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and marshmallow cream together with mixer. Sprinkle in some strawberry jello for color.
You can also add 1 tsp. vanilla flavoring, if desired.
Serve with fresh fruits of your choice.

title: chocolate caramel delights
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, 1 cup of sugar and 1/2 cup butter at medium speed until blended.
Pat firmly into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Evenly arrange pecans on top.
Mix remaining butter and sugar over medium heat until bubbly, stirring often. Pour evenly over crust and bake for 18 to 22 minutes. Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
Slightly swirl as they melt.
Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Melt oleo and add half with all other ingredients except Ritz crackers.
Put in 8 x 8 x 2-inch casserole.
Mix crumbled crackers with other half of melted oleo and put on top.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes.
Don't cover casserole for 25 minutes, then lay a piece of foil over top.

title: k's strawberry meringue pie
directions: Beat egg whites and baking powder until frothy and soft peaks form.
Add sugar gradually, beating until whites are stiff and glossy.
Add vanilla.
Fold in finely crushed cracker crumbs (from the 12 soda crackers) and the coarsely chopped pecans.
Spread in buttered 9 or 10-inch pie plate, building up sides to form shell. Bake in 225°
oven for 35 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces; put aside.
Mix milk, sour cream, sugar and Cool Whip together.
Mix strawberries and glaze together.
Alternate layers of cake pieces, whip mixture and strawberry mixture in a glass bowl.

title: fruit cake
directions: Dredge the nuts and fruit with all the flour and baking powder.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dredged fruit, nuts and flavoring.
Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: granola
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add blended liquid.
Mix well; pour in large pan (heavy) and spread evenly.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Turn off oven; add nuts and raisins and allow mixture to cool in oven.
When cooled, put in a tightly covered container.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Serve with meat or fresh fruit.
One-half or one-third of recipe may be made.

title: "better than dessert" sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine
potatoes,
sugar,
milk, 1/3 cup melted margarine, vanilla and eggs;
mix well.
Put in greased baking dish 11 x 13-inch or equivalent.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In medium saucepan mix 1 1/2 cups water, 3 tablespoons cornstarch and 1/2 cup cold water and begin heating.
Boil 1 cup water and add.
Bring all to a boil for a few minutes.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Cool completely.
Place fresh, sliced strawberries in baked shell and chill.
Ice with heavy cream. Enjoy!

title: no-bake fruit squares
directions: Grind together fruit and nuts.
Mix in enough juice to hold together.
Press into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill overnight.
Top with confectioners sugar.
Makes 24.

title: old fashion fudge
directions: Spray 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with vegetable spray.
In 2-quart saucepan, mix sugar, salt, cocoa, corn syrup and milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cocoa and sugar are dissolved.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234° on a candy thermometer, or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a soft ball which flattens when removed from water.
Remove from
heat; add margarine.
Cool mixture to 115° without stirring; bottom of pan will be lukewarm.
Add vanilla. Beat vigorously for 5 minutes with wooden spoon until candy is thick and no longer glossy.
Mixture will hold its shape when dropped from spoon.
Quickly stir in nuts.
Spread mixture evenly in pan.
Cool until firm.
Cut into 1-inch squares.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all together and enjoy.

title: barbecued spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat slowly until crumbly but not hard.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to meat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve on split rolls.

title: how to make cookies according to a four-year-old
directions: Roll it with a roller, outer.
Flatten the dough.
Put it in the oven to cook it.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Mix apples and candy until well blended.
Gently stir in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate 1 hour or until ready to serve.
Garnish with apple slices and additional chopped candy bars, if desired.
Makes 20 servings.

title: marbled pumpkin cake
directions: Combine pumpkin and cinnamon in medium bowl.
Combine cake mix, eggs, sour cream, sugar, oil and water in large mixer bowl. Beat on low speed until moistened.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Refrigerate to blend flavors.
Serve cold.

title: hot cider punch
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Bring to a boil and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add sherry.
Do not boil after sherry has been added.
Add orange and lemon slices.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix pudding and milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
Chop peanut butter cups into fourths and add to mix.
Pour into graham cracker crust and freeze.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt butter on low until melted, then add chocolate chips. Add sugar, mix well. Beat eggs well then add to mixture. Add chopped pecans pour into pie shells. Bake 350° for 45 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: stir-fried beef and vegetables
directions: Partially freeze meat.
Slice meat very thinly across the grain into bite size strips.
Dissolve the instant beef bouillon granules in the boiling water.
Add soy sauce, set aside.
Preheat a wok or large skillet over high heat; add oil.
Stir-fry garlic in hot oil for 30 seconds.
Add onion, carrots, celery and mushrooms. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Add half the meat to hot wok or skillet; stir-fry 2 minutes.
Remove meat.
Stir-fry remaining meat 2 minutes.
Return all meat to wok.
Stir soy mixture; stir into meat.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in cooked vegetables and the spinach.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Serve the beef-vegetable mixture immediately.
Makes 4 servings.

title: alyssa's norwegian lefse
directions: Peel and boil potatoes.
Mash and add salt, butter and milk while still hot.
Cool and add sugar and enough flour to easily roll out.
Flour board and roll out a spoonful of dough as thin as possible (thinner than a pie crust).
Cut in 6 to 8-inch circles. Bake on ungreased griddle on top of stove until lightly browned on both sides.
Keep lefse soft between several dampened towels until ready to serve.
Spread with butter and brown or white sugar.

title: picnic potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes enough to remove the skins.
Dice and pour the dressing over them.
Chill.
Add other ingredients, using equal parts mayonnaise and sour cream, tasting for salt.
Chill well.

title: braised green beans
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until golden.
Add remaining ingredients.
Juices should just cover beans in pan.
If not, add a little more water.
Cover. Cook over low heat for 45 minutes or until fork-tender.
Serve with pan juices.
Yields 4 servings.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 1-inch apart on greased cookie sheets.
Press with wet spatula to 1/8-inch thickness.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes, or until light brown and crisp.
Remove to racks to cool.
Store loosely covered in cool place.
Makes about 60 cookies (5 dozen).

title: taco salad
directions: Cut up vegetables; put in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Fry and crumble beef in skillet; drain excess fat. Add meat and cheese to vegetables.
Add chips and mix.
Serve with chips and taco sauce.

title: cheesy macaroni and beef casserole
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper, drain.
Add macaroni, barbecue sauce, juice or tomato. Pour into shallow 10 x 10-inch baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake covered at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven until melted.
Serves 6.

title: seven layer
directions: Pour butter into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Add ingredients in layers as listed (do not stir).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: ice cream pound cake
directions: Whip butter until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat good.
Gradually add flour to butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time, beat good after each egg, then add ice cream.
Bake in preheated oven at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla together.
Beat in eggs and chocolate.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend half of the sifted mixture into the creamed mixture.
Blend in milk, remaining sifted ingredients and walnuts. Chill at least 3 hours.
Roll into 1-inch balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Put on greased sheet 2 to 3 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: never fail biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water; add oil.
Mix soda with buttermilk, then add to yeast mixture.
Sift flour and mix well with rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: crunchy casserole
directions: Place as many pork chops as you want in a baking dish in a single layer.
Put brown sugar on them thickly, then pour chili sauce over the top to cover and salt and pepper as desired.
Place two slices of lemon on each pork chop. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour or until tender.
Most everybody will want seconds!

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: miss sallie shackelford's meringues
directions: Personal Note:
I usually add 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar and 1 teaspoon white vinegar.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Bring broccoli to a boil and cook for 5 minutes.
While broccoli is cooking, mix 2 cans of soup with one cup of rice and two cups of water.
Put soup mixture in a casserole dish and spread evenly.
Lay broccoli on top of soup mixture.
Lay chicken breasts on top of broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with aluminum foil and punch several holes in the foil.
Bake at 375° approximately one hour.
When meat is done, sprinkle cheese over chicken and return to oven (uncovered) for 5 minutes.

title: nut crust
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Press over bottom and sides of greased 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool.

title: tourquere pie
directions: Cut into serving pieces top or botton round.
Cut about 1/2-inch thick.
Dredge in flour seasoned to taste with salt and pepper.
Have heavy skillet over medium-low heat just enough fat to keep meat from sticking.
Brown steak on both sides, still on medium-low heat, allowing plenty of time for browning.
Pour of any excess fat.
Add small amount of water.
Cover tightly and simmer until fork-tender.
Serve with natural gravy, or if thickened gravy is desired, blend a little flour with cold water and stir
into liquid after meat has been removed to platter. Stir constantly over low heat until gravy is desired thickness and flour mixture well cooked.
Taste and correct seasoning.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
Mix all together.
Put in baking dish(es).
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in 350° oven.
Can add 1/2 to 1 cup chicken broth for moisture, if needed.
Serves 15, but can make 1/2 recipe to serve 8 or 2/3 recipe to serve 10.

title: apricot nectar cake(a goldie oldie cake recipe)
directions: Blend cake mix with jello in mixer or by hand until well blended. Then add Wesson oil and apricot nectar and blend well. Then add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition. Cook in a tube pan at 300° for 1 hour. Grease and flour (and can put wax paper in the bottom of the pan).

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Mix together:
soups, olives, salsa, milk or broth.
Cut up tortillas into approximately 1-inch squares.
Spread 1/2 of soup mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Strew 1/2 cut up tortillas on top.
Add sliced chicken, 1/2 of grated cheese; add rest of tortillas, then rest of soup mixture, then rest of cheese. Let stand overnight in refrigerator, if possible.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: hot slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook for 20 minutes from the time that mixture starts to boil.
Stir often.
Put in jars and seal tightly.

title: golden pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 2 loaf type bread pans at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Combine ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: tasty treat
directions: Melt the chocolate chips.
Add the noodles and peanuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on baking sheet and chill. Yum!

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches or 2 loaf pans, 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inches.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl; beat on medium speed 1/2 minute.
Pour into pan(s); bake 55 to 65 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan(s). Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: ike cake
directions: Beat egg well.
Add fruit.
Sift together flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add to fruit and egg.
Put in square pan.

title: mango salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and chill. Serve as a relish for grilled fish or as a dip for chips.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt stick of butter.
Mix all wet ingredients in one bowl. Mix all dry ingredients in one bowl.
Combine two bowls.
Drop cookies on an ungreased pan.
Bake 350°
for 5 - 10 minutes or longer depending on size of cookies and texture (soft cookies or crunchy cookies).

title: chicken and rice
directions: In saucepan bring the chicken broth and butter to a boil, then add the rice and boil for 10 minutes.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Top with Miracle Whip.
Then pour the rice mixture over the chicken; spread the rice around the chicken and top with mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, milk and butter.
Bring to full boil until soft ball stage, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, marshmallow cream and peanut butter.
Stir until smooth. Pour into buttered 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: easy curried chicken
directions: Cut chicken breast halves into 8 pieces each. In cup, mix curry powder, bouillon, sugar and salt.
In nonstick skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion until golden brown.
Add chicken and curry powder mixture and cook until chicken just loses its pink color throughout, about 3 to 5 minutes. Stir in raisins and 3/4 cup water; heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.

title: best hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt, eggs and sugar.
Mix. Blend vegetable oil into mixture.
Pour mixture into a large bowl and begin adding flour.
Knead dough for 5 minutes.
When dough is smooth and satiny, place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until doubled in bulk.
Punch down and let rest for 10 minutes. Shape dough into rolls.
Let rise until doubled. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: pineapple custard pie
directions: In saucepan, blend sugar with cornstarch.
Add pineapple (including juice).
Cook, stirring constantly, until thick.
Set aside and let cool.
In a mixing bowl, blend cream cheese, sugar, and salt (preferably with electric mixer).
Add eggs, one at a time; stir well after each.
Add milk and vanilla.

title: apple bread
directions: In a bowl, cream together sugar and lard.
Add eggs, sour milk and cream.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix. Batter will be thick.
Blend in apples and nuts. Bake in greased and floured bread pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
This is a very moist bread.

title: poor person's cake
directions: Put raisins, nutmeg, cinnamon, honey, molasses and oil in water and boil for 3 minutes.
When cooled, add dry ingredients. Mix well and pour into
a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Good plain or with lemon sauce, ice cream or whipped cream.

title: good salad
directions: Put vegetables in layers, lettuce on bottom, reserving some for top layer.

title: sherry cheese sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, over high heat, combine milk, salt, mustard, pepper and nutmeg.
Bring to boil.
In a small bowl, combine cornstarch and sherry; stir until well blended.
Stir cornstarch mixture into saucepan mixture.
Reduce heat to low and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and stir in cheese.
Serve over vegetables.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels on very low heat. Stir completely, then add salted peanuts and chow mein noodles and stir. Put on cookie sheet covered with wax paper in clusters and refrigerate.

title: salt substitute
directions: Blend well.
Makes about 1 cup seasoning.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, onion, carrots and celery in chicken broth. Add corn and seasonings.
Make white sauce from butter, flour and milk.
Add to cooked vegetables.
Add cheese.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Toss with following dressing:

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off excess fat.
Combine with the rest of the ingredients and simmer on stove for about 2 hours. May also be cooked in crock-pot on low for about 4 hours or more.

title: german potato salad with sour cream
directions: Slice potatoes while still warm.
If new are used, slice in their jackets.
Older ones should be peeled.
Mix sugar, salt, mustard, pepper and vinegar.
Add sour cream and cucumber to mix. Pour over potatoes and toss lightly until all potatoes are coated. Place in serving dish and sprinkle with paprika.
Serve warm or cold.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Saute vegetable in oil; add soups and Rotel tomatoes. Cook until blended. Layer in baking dish, tortillas, sauce, chicken, and cheese; repeat layers ending with cheese on top. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: easy casserole
directions: Brown beef in a skillet or microwave.
Drain.
Stir in the soup, spaghetti and vegetables.
Transfer to an ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Sprinkle with cheese and let stand for a few minutes until melted.

title: jordan marsh blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Blend well. Add dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 to 3/4 full.
Sprinkle tops of muffins with sugar before baking. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: best ever roast beef
directions: Mix gravy, mushrooms, dressing, soup mix, salt and pepper. Pour over meat.
Cover and bake 3 hours at 325°.
Refrigerate overnight.
Slice meat, then put back in gravy, cover and reheat for 1 hour at 300°.

title: praline peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches with cooking spray.
Mix cracker crumbs, pecans, brown sugar and butter.
Press evenly in bottom of pan.
Arrange peaches on crust; sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.
Mix Bisquick, granulated sugar and milk; pour over peaches.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes until golden. Serve warm.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar. Cover tightly and shake vigorously. Yields 1 cup.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook whole chicken until tender and debone; spray Pam in bottom of casserole and spread chicken pieces over bottom. Combine broth and soup; pour over chicken.
Mix butter, milk and flour; pour on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is golden brown.

title: baked ham sandwiches
directions: Mix top 5 ingredients and spread on buns.
Pile with sliced ham and a Swiss cheese slice.
Wrap in foil and bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until hot and cheese melted.

title: cucumber side salad
directions: Put all ingredients in small bowl; stir good.
Set in refrigerator until meal time.
Drain off liquid.
Serves 2.

title: jack in the box juice
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Serves 4.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, then top with 2 cups of crushed Ritz crackers and 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Bake 1 hour at 150°.

title: bread and blueberries(great for brunch)
directions: Toss bread cubes with butter, sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle berries with lemon juice and brown sugar.
Spread alternate layers of bread mixture and berry mixture in 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream or plain.

title: perfect poached fish
directions: Place in individual baking dish and sprinkle with seasonings. Pour around fish.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
When milk starts to boil, the fish is done perfectly.

title: layered mexican bean dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Mix Miracle Whip, sour cream and taco seasoning together.
Spread over bean dip.
Sprinkle on shredded cheese; add chopped tomatoes and chopped green onions.
Refrigerate 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken-asparagus stir-fry
directions: In small bowl, combine cornstarch, sherry, soy sauce, and broth.
Set aside.
Heat oil.
Add garlic and chicken.
Cook for 1 minute.
Lift and set aside.
Add mushrooms, onions, and asparagus and stir-fry for 1 minute.
Add chicken, garlic mixture, and broth mixture.
Cook until broth thickens.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef; drain thoroughly.
Add cumin, chili powder, garlic powder, red pepper, salt, pepper and tomatoes; heat through.

title: chicken cordon bleu(serving size:  4.  preparation time:  2:00)
directions: Cut each chicken breast in half; remove tendons.
One at a time, place breast halves between two sheets of waxed paper and pound flat.
