Combine minced ham and grated cheese with hands.
Form into four rolls to fit in middle of a flattened breast half (about 3 inches long).
Place a roll on each breast half and fold breast half around it, beginning with one long side, then short sides, finishing with a long side, like an envelope.
Press edges together and roll each piece as it is finished in a sheet of waxed paper while you finish with other preparations.
Season flour with salt and pepper.
Beat egg lightly with 1 teaspoon water.

title: fruited dressing balls
directions: Prepare stuffing as per directions on box.
Medium chop the prunes and apricots.
Add to mixture and shape into balls.
Place on baking sheet
and bake in a moderate oven at 325° about 20 to 30 minutes, until lightly toasted.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring to a boil the oleo, sugar and Karo syrup.
Boil for 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from heat; add the soda and vanilla.
Mixture will foam up.
In large pan, pour mixture over popped corn.
One cup pecans or peanuts can be added, if you wish.
Stir until kernels of corn are well coated.
Bake 1 hour at 250°.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Pour on newspaper to cool.
Store in a tight jar.

title: choco pink cuplets
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening, vanilla and eggs, beating after each egg.
Sift together flour, cocoa and salt.
Set aside. Combine baking soda and water.
Add flour and water mixtures alternately to creamed butter and sugar.
Mix well.

title: pietraconne pickled poultry
directions: Your poultry needs to be cooked and sliced in thin bite-size pieces.
You can use leftover chicken or turkey.
Place the poultry in a large, deep Pyrex casserole dish that has a lid.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter together.
Mix popcorn, peanuts and M&M's with marshmallow mixture.
Pack well into a large tube pan.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate.
Remove from pan and cut in slices.

title: quick strawberry dessert
directions: Break cake in pieces and place on bottom and sides of round glass bowl.
Dissolve pudding in milk.
Add ice cream.
Pour over cake in bottom of bowl.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add frozen berries and stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour into glass bowl.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: lazy man's chili rellenos
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Beat yolks lightly with a fork; add flour and salt and mix until smooth.
Fold in egg whites until well blended.
Turn 1/2 mixture into well-greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with chilies and cheese.
Top with remaining egg mixture.
Bake at 325° about 25 minutes.
Top with salsa and sour cream.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Broccoli, cauliflower, tomatoes, carrots, radishes, peppers, cucumbers and black or green olives may be used.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate a few hours before serving.

title: hunter's chicken
directions: Dredge chicken in flour.
Saute onion and garlic in olive oil until softened.
Add chicken.
Cook until browned on both sides. Add all other ingredients.
Reduce heat.
Cover pan and simmer 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: potato bean soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook and stir celery, carrots and garlic in hot margarine over medium heat for 4 minutes or until tender. Stir in broth, potatoes and dill.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Simmer, covered, for 20 to 25 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli (unsalted); drain and set aside.
Beat eggs.
Add to the remaining ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Fold in broccoli.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all beans and peas.
Chop onion, pepper and celery very fine.
Combine all and marinate 24 hours.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: zucchini and green chili quiche
directions: Crust:
Mix flour and salt.
Measure oil, milk and water in same cup (but don't stir).
Pour all at once into flour; stir until mixed.
Press into smooth ball.
Cut in halves; flatten slightly.
Press one half between 2 sheets waxed paper, approximately 12-inches square.
Roll out gently to edges of paper.
Peel off top paper.
If dough tears, mend without moistening.
Lift paper and pastry by top corners.
Place paper side up in 9-inch deep dish pie pan. Peel off paper and fit pastry into pan.
Repeat for second pan.

title: glue for papier-mache
directions: Dissolve flour	in
cold water.
Add hot water and boil over low
heat,	stirring
constantly.
Add cold water to make right consistency for use.
Add salt and cloves to preserve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix chopped vegetables and sauerkraut together in a bowl.

title: squash patties
directions: Combine all ingredients except oil and mix well. Drop mixture by tablespoon into hot oil. Fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Drain off 1 can of corn.
Add milk to the drained liquid to measure 1 cup.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine beaten egg, milk mixture and corn.
Add to dry ingredients.
Mix just until flour is moistened.
Drop batter by tablespoon into deep, hot fat (375°).
Fry until golden brown, about 3 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Serve with warm maple syrup.
Makes about 18 fritters (feeds 3 to 4).
Double recipe for more.

title: hamburger foil dinner
directions: Place all ingredients on a square piece of aluminum foil. Seal foil and place in oven at 375° for about 1 hour.
When potatoes are done, the meal is done.

title: barbecue
directions: Put meat in crock-pot.
Cook until tender enough to whip apart with a fork.
Add other ingredients and turn on low.
Cook about 1 hour.
Stir often.

title: baked brie
directions: Smother baby Brie with apricot jam and wrap in puff pastry. Cook at 400° for 20 minutes and then let it set at room temperature for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Boil sugar, cinnamon and milk, stirring constantly until mixture reaches a soft-ball stage.
Remove from heat and add 2 cups pecans and vanilla.
Stir until all nuts are well coated. Drop individually on waxed paper.

title: caribbean diet drink
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender until ice is completely liquified.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onions in small amount of hot fat until tender but not brown.
Add meat and seasonings, brown lightly.
Add green beans and soup.
Pour into casserole dish.
Top with creamed potatoes and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream puff dessert
directions: Bring water and oleo to a boil.
Remove from heat and add flour.
Stir until it leaves sides of pan and forms into a ball. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet pan and spread mixture.
Bake in 400° oven for 25 minutes.
(This will rise in different shapes but will be covered with topping.) Let cool.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: This is such a large cake that the best thing to do is find a good baker or bakery and have them do it for you.
Chocolate seems to be the favorite. Have it frosted with white frosting and decorate with red roses.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Fry chicken in large skillet until almost done.
Add onion and garlic to chicken.
Put chopped broccoli and mushroom with chicken and steam for 5 minutes.
Serve with rice and season with soy sauce.

title: friendship cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine; add unbeaten egg.
Blend well. Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add vanilla to milk and add it alternately, flour mixture with cream mixture, starting and ending with flour.
Mix well and drop dough be teaspoonful onto sifted powdered sugar.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375° on center rack.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cover and marinate overnight.

title: roast turkey
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Place turkey in roaster.
Place ingredients around the turkey.
Season turkey with salt and pepper.
Place cover over roaster.
Cook for 1 hour.
Turn oven off, but do not open oven door until next morning.
Remove turkey from oven.

title: addison brownies
directions: Before beginning, put 1 stick of margarine in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt in oven.
Mix together sugar, cocoa and eggs.
Add vanilla and flour.
Stir together while adding melted margarine. Pour batter in a 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: hot crab spread
directions: Blend milk and cream cheese.
Mix remaining, except almonds. Put in ovenproof dish and sprinkle top with almonds.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles.
Serve with crackers.

title: banana and raspberry shake
directions: Add ingredients in a blender.
Blend on mix for 2 minutes.

title: beef tips and rice
directions: Brown stew meat in butter.
Add salt and pepper, onion salt and garlic salt.
Pour on 1/2 cup water and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and cook until tender.
When done, make a gravy using the flour and 1/2 cup water.
Pour gravy over beef.
Serve over rice.

title: split pea soup
directions: Heat water and peas to boiling in a heavy saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes and remove from heat.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour. Stir in ham, onion, salt and pepper into peas.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat, cover and simmer until peas are tender, about 1 hour. Skim fat, if necessary.
Remove ham, trim fat and bone from ham. Cut ham into 1/2-inch pieces.
Stir ham, carrots and celery into soup.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables are tender, about 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into jello mold or pan.
Let sit in refrigerator 2 to 3 hours.

title: "no need to knead" rolls
directions: Mix well and shape into rolls.
Put rolls into greased round cake pans.
Cover and let rise 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake rolls 15 to 20 minutes.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients
and serve with raw vegetables such as carrots, celery, broccoli, cauliflower or green peppers.

title: overnight french toast casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add brown sugar and cook until syrupy.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread and egg mixture.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: silver lake fish soup with seashells
directions: Saute onions and garlic in the oil in a large kettle over low heat for 5 minutes.
Add tomato paste, bouillon, oregano, bay leaves, pepper, dill weed and parsley and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and add fish.
Cook slowly on low heat, covered, until fish is just fork-tender, about 10 minutes.
Add the sherry and seashell pasta and cook over medium heat, uncovered, until pasta is just tender, about 10 minutes.
Remove from the heat.
Serve with crackers, Cheddar cheese and sliced cucumbers.

title: tangy texas salsa
directions: Peel, section and dice grapefruit and orange, removing all membrane.
Place in a bowl; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
Yields about 5 cups.

title: chorizo and rice-guatemala
directions: Grill, poach or fry the sausage links until fully cooked. Simmer in tomato sauce for 30-45 minutes. Meanwhile, prepare rice and mix the vegetables into it. Serve the sausage over the rice and veggies.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Put all ingredients in large mixing bowl and beat with mixer for 2 to 3 minutes. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in bowl.
Add oil and carrots.
Add 1 egg at a time, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the shortening and margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds. Add about half of the flour, the brown sugar, sugar, eggs, vanilla and baking soda.
Beat mixture until thoroughly combined.
Beat in the remaining flour.
Stir in chocolate pieces and, if desired, nuts.

title: fruit cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together.
Add dry mixture to fruit and nuts. Toss mixture with hands to coat evenly.

title: greg's homemade hot dog chili
directions: Simmer the meat, onion and salt in water about 20 minutes. Add tomato juice, sugar and chili powder; cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Do not drain the meat.
Use lean meat and it makes a good flavor.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Grease pie pan and sprinkle with bacon, cheese and onion. Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over ingredients in pie pan and bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Mix all ingredients, except fruit.
Grease baking dish with butter.
Put fruit on bottom and pour mixture over fruit.
If you use apples, put 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1 teaspoon apple spice in flour, sugar and milk mixture.
You can use fresh fruits, if you want.
Bake at 350° until nice and brown, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: crescent rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Separate crescent rolls.
Place deboned chicken on each triangle and roll up, starting at large end. Place in a lightly buttered casserole dish and bake for 5 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Roll steak in flour and salt.
Brown in 1/4 cup fat.
Add onion and vegetables.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: no fry french fried potatoes
directions: Wash and cut potatoes for fries.
Line cookie sheet with aluminum foil.
Spray with cooking spray.
Lay potatoes in single layer and spray them.
Bake in a 350° oven until brown.
Stir once so potatoes will brown evenly.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the eggs, sugar and corn syrup.
Stir in the salt and vanilla.
Stir in the nuts.

Turn the mixture into a 9-inch pie pan lined with pie dough and bake in a hot oven at 450° for 10 minutes. Reduce the heat to 350° and continue to bake for 30 minutes longer or until a silver knife inserted in the center of the filling comes out clean.

title: cherry macaroon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Pour pie filling into the unbaked pie shell.
Beat together egg and evaporated milk.
Add sugar, flour, salt, almond extract and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in coconut.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes or until puffed and light brown.
Cool before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together and bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: grandma's special squash pie
directions: Combine sugar,
flour and salt.
Add to squash; stir in egg, milk
and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping, if desired.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in flour 1 cup at a time.
Divide dough into four equal pieces.
Put each piece in round 8-inch pan; prick dough with fork.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 hour or until pale brown.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cut into wedges.
Sprinkle with sugar.
(4 pans)

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Chop cabbage coarsely.
Place in bottom of greased casserole (1 1/2-quart or 9 x 13-inch oblong pan).
Brown meat with onion. Pour off fat.
Stir in rice.
Place meat mixture on top of cabbage.
Mix tomato, water, Worcestershire and seasonings, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over ingredients to cover.
Cover dish and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: watergate salad(as dessert)
directions: Empty pineapple with juice in mixing bowl.
Fill can with small marshmallows and mix.
Add pudding mix and Cool Whip.
Mix and put into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
Will keep longer.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Put in bowl.
Add all ingredients.
Add Italian dressing and Parmesan cheese and mix well.

title: raspberry fudge brownies
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs, butter, Nestle Choco Bake and vanilla extract; beat until creamy.
Add flour, baking powder and soda, salt and mix well.
Add nuts.
Spread into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread while still hot a jar of raspberry preserves or fruit spread.
Let cool completely.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onions, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Place meat balls in ungreased baking dish, 8 x 8 x 2-inch.
Stir together remaining ingredients; pour over meat balls.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes, uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients well and roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: meat loaf supreme
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in loaf pan, shaping into loaves.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Let stand a few minutes before slicing.
This is a large recipe and will serve about 8 or 10 people.

title: silly putty
directions: Mix starch into glue.
Stir until mixture is the correct consistency.
Can be made in smaller amounts as long as proportions remain the same.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.
If sticky, add more liquid starch and stir.

title: marinated chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in a large shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; stir well and pour over chicken.
Cover and refrigerate chicken for 2 hours.
Remove chicken from marinade. Grill over hot coals about 8 minutes on each side, using marinade for basting.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grated sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well, making sure sugar has dissolved. Pour mixture into 8 x 10 baking dish and cook in 350° for 30 minutes.
This seems to set from outside to center, so remove from oven and stir.
Return to oven and cook 15 minutes longer.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine margarine, sweetener and peanut butter and blend well.
Combine egg, nonfat milk and vanilla; add to first mixture.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together; add, blending well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet (or heavy-duty aluminum foil).
Flatten with tines of fork dipped in water.
Bake 10 minutes.
Yield: 4 dozen cookies.
Twenty-four packets artificial sweetener = 1 cup sugar.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients together and pour into 8 x 8-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon (mixed together).
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Can be served topped with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: *Save broth from cooked chicken.

title: pickled onions(found in an old recipe box.)
directions: "Never use iodized salt for making pickles!"

title: fudge sheet cake
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and resift with sugar and salt.
Place water, cocoa and margarine in saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over flour and sugar mixture.
In another bowl place eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add to other mixture and mix well.
Bake in greased and floured shallow pan at 350° for 20 minutes.	Start making icing for the last minutes the cake is baking.

title: coconut pie
directions: Place sugar and flour in saucepan and mix well.
Separate eggs.
Use 4 whites for meringue; use 5 yolks and other white in custard.
Add oleo and milk.
Cook until thick.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Cool.
Place in baked shell and top with meringue.

title: brown sugar candy
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage, or until it spins a thread.
Cool and beat.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a greased shallow pan.

title: cranberry stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In skillet, cook celery and onion in margarine or butter.

title: beef and noodle casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in garlic, oregano and tomato sauce.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer sauce while cooking egg noodles according to package instructions.
When noodles are done, drain and stir in sour cream.
In greased baking dish, layer noodle mixture, sauce and cheese until dish is full.
End with layer of cheese on top.
Bake at 400° until cheese melts and casserole is bubbly.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs, then previously sifted dry ingredients alternately with the syrup and water.
Add one cup chopped nuts if desired.
Beat enough to mix thoroughly.
Pour into a well greased 12 1/2 x 8 x 2-inch pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: dressing
directions: Combine crumbled corn bread, bread cubes, pepper and sage. Put just enough shortening to lightly brown celery and onion.
Add to bread mixture; add eggs and water, tossing lightly to combine (use 1/2 cup water for more moist).
Stuff lightly into neck region and body of turkey.
Roast according to turkey size.
Bake any remaining dressing in uncovered dish during last 30 minutes of roasting.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: *One package mix, 1/2 cup mayo and 1/2 cup milk.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°F.
Grease a loaf pan, set aside.

title: legumes gone wild
directions: Take minced garlic, onion and water chestnuts and cook (in butter spray) in a nonstick skillet about 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and add all remaining ingredients, except lemon juice. Return to burner and cook on low until everything is heated.
Top with lemon or lime juice.
This can also be eaten cold or about room temperature.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix and cream together the cream cheese and confectioners sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread on Cool Whip.

title: orange jello salad dessert
directions: Mix together cottage cheese and orange Jell-O.
Then add pineapple and mandarin oranges to mixture. Mix well.
Gently blend in Cool Whip.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs; add other ingredients.
Put soda in boiling water.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Mix apple juice, cornstarch and spices; heat until thick. Pour mixture over sliced apples in 1 crust and top with other crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
(Mixture can be baked in glass bakeware without crusts.)

title: cinnamon candy
directions: Mix syrup with sugar.
Boil fast until spins a thread and cracks in ice water.
Add coloring.
Pour into lightly greased pan and let cool.
Mark into squares, then break into blocks.

title: stewed apples with cider
directions: Peel apples and cut into 1/2-inch slices.
Saute apples in butter in skillet.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Add cider, lemon juice and salt.
Simmer, uncovered, until tender.
Add spices, if desired.

title: crisp-tart cole slaw
directions: Mix together cabbage, onion and green pepper.
Sprinkle with salt.
Pour 1 cup boiling water over all.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Drain and toss with pimento, celery seed, mustard seed, vinegar, oil and sugar.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Soften cream cheese and beat in all other ingredients well. Put in graham cracker crusts.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen individually.
Makes 3 pies.

title: wilted lettuce salad
directions: Mix together lettuce, onion, eggs and bacon.
Heat bacon drippings until warm.
Mix rest ingredients and add to bacon drippings.
Warm together.
Pour over salad and serve.

title: bacon canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix first three ingredients.
Spread on bread.
Bake on a cookie sheet for 4 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Cook bacon on High in microwave for 5 to 7 minutes until brown.
Set aside to cool.
Cook potatoes with 1/4 cup of water, covered, in microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Mix together vinegar, sugar and salt; set aside.
Put lettuce, tomato and onion in large salad bowl.
Put in cooked potatoes.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salt and 2 tablespoons of bacon grease in microwave until hot.
Pour over salad; toss to coat. Crumple bacon on top.
Serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hush puppies
directions: Add dry ingredients in a small deep bowl.
Mix well and add onions.
Mix again.
Add egg and milk.
Mix well. Let set and rise for 20 minutes.
Deep fry in fat.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Combine ground beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl and mix well.
Shape into balls using a tablespoon.
Put into a baking dish.
Mix tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and water in a bowl.
Pour over the meatballs.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: easy oven barbecue steak
directions: Cut steak into serving size portions.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with sauce.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours. Do not open.
Serve with rice or mashed potatoes.

title: scrod ala jane
directions: Preheat broiler.
Lightly grease a shallow baking dish (large enough to hold fish in single layer).
Place scrod in dish, sprinkle with basil and lemon juice.
Broil until half cooked, 6 to 7 minutes.
Remove from broiler and heat oven to 350°.
Pour half and half over the fish and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Continue cooking in oven for about 15 minutes, or until fish is cooked through.
While fish is baking, heat butter in medium-size skillet and cook the onion and green pepper until tender.
Serve with sauteed onion and green pepper, topped with crumbled bacon.

title: peanut butter popcorn
directions: Put sugar and syrup into a saucepan and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add peanut butter and stir until melted.
Pour quickly over popped popcorn and toss until popcorn is well coated. Enjoy.

title: banana-orange juice
directions: Empty orange juice into blender.
Add 1 can of water.
Blend. Add banana.
Blend again; then add 2 more cans of water.
Blend. Note:
If blender does not hold all 3 cans of water, just add 1 or 2 cans to blender and finish with third can in pitcher.
It's oh so tasty.
We also sometimes add strawberries.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine shortening, sugar and eggs.
Mix with flour and soda. Add vanilla and bananas.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour. Freezes well also.

title: salmon loaf "pudding"
directions: Combine milk, rice, onion, salt, pepper, sugar, lemon juice, salmon and parsley.
Mix well.
Beat eggs well and add to mixture. Pour into buttered casserole or oblong cake pan.
Bake at 250° for 35 minutes or until firm and brown on top.
Pour melted butter on top.
Serve hot or cold.

title: gingerbread
directions: Sift flour once; measure and sift again with salt, soda and spices.
Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg and molasses; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and hot water alternately.
Beat until smooth.
Start with dry ingredients and end with dry ingredients.
Pour into well-greased pan (10 x 14-inch).
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: quick banana bread
directions: Place cream cheese and eggs into mixing bowl.
Blend on low for 2 minutes.
Add bananas; blend on low speed for 1 minute.
Add yellow cake mix and nuts.
Mix until blended.
Divide batter evenly into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool slightly.
Remove from pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: simply delicious chocolate cake
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake at 365°
for 25 to 30 minutes in small round baking tin.

title: sausage chowder
directions: Brown sausage and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients and put into crock-pot for 4 hours on high or until potatoes are done.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat eggs; add milk and Bisquick with wire whisk or hand beater for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges and serve.
Makes 6 servings. Oven temperature:

title: kolbassi
directions: Put kolbassi in small roaster.
Mix other ingredients and pour over.
Bake at about 375° an hour or more.

title: chili
directions: Brown the ground beef and onion.
Drain.
Combine all ingredients. Add ground beef and onion.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: ruby fruit punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to boil.
Let cool.
Add and stir grape, lemonade and orange juice.
Place in freezer overnight until slushy.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large mixer bowl, beat egg yolks; stir in sweetened condensed milk, lime juice and green food coloring, if desired.
Pour into prepared crust.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours.
Top with whipped topping.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rhubarb crumb cake from alaska
directions: Spread cut up rhubarb in 10 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle sugar evenly over fruit.
Add 1/2 package strawberry jello evenly. Now sprinkle Jiffy cake mix (white) over mixture.
Add 1 cup boiling water.
Add cut up butter or margarine and bake at 350° until done, 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: corn relish
directions: Cut vegetables fine.
Mix all together; boil for 20 minutes. Put into small, sterilized jars and seal.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar and melted butter.
Sprinkle on bottom of greased 9-inch spring-form pan. Cook and stir contents of vanilla pudding
with 1/2 cup sugar and milk.
Bring to full boil.
Remove from heat and cover.
Beat cream cheese; beat in egg yolks, lemon juice, salt and pudding. Beat 3 egg whites to peaks; fold into cheese mixture.
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes, until set in center.
Cool.

title: peanut butter cups in a pan
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt chips in microwave (5 minutes on 50%).
Pour chocolate evenly over peanut butter mixture.
Chill until firm.
Remove from refrigerator and let warm to room temperature so the chocolate will not crumble when cut.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: celery casserole
directions: Boil celery in salt water for 7 minutes.
Drain.
Mix cooked celery, soup and water chestnuts in casserole dish.
Mash crackers and brown with almonds in oleo.
Sprinkle browned crackers and almonds over first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.

title: waldorf original salad
directions: Put apple, celery and walnuts in a bowl.
Add mayonnaise and lemon juice immediately to prevent apple from darkening.
Serves 4.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers very fine. Melt margarine. In large bowl, mix all ingredients. Line bottom of tube pan with waxed paper and grease sides of pan with margarine. Mold into tube pan and pack down. Put into refrigerator for about 2 hours before you remove from pan. Must be stored in refrigerator.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat to a rolling boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and peanut butter.
Stir until melted then add oats and stir until mixed.
Spoon onto cookie sheets covered with wax paper.
Will set in a half hour.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate (irish) potato cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar together until creamy, then add mashed potatoes, melted chocolate, egg yolks (beaten), milk, flour, baking powder, vanilla, nuts and whites of eggs, beaten stiffly. Mix carefully and bake in a moderate oven (350°).

title: tuna ball
directions: Combine all ingredients and make into a ball.
Chill 1 hour. Roll in chopped nuts, if desired.

title: wanda's potato supreme
directions: Peel and quarter potatoes, then put into 2-quart pot.
Add seasoning, then add flour.
Shake together in pot.
Add dressing and butter, then cover with water.
Cover and cook on very low heat.
Stir occasionally until potatoes are done.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and stir over moderate heat until sugar dissolves and mixture comes to a boil.
Boil to 238° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and allow to cool until 110°, about 1 hour.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture just begins to lose its gloss.
Quickly stir in nuts and cherries.
Turn into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan. Cool and cut.

title: asparagus quiche
directions: Bake pie shell for 10 minutes.
Steam asparagus until tender and chop into slices.
Saute bacon until crisp; drain.
Saute mushrooms and onion in small amount of bacon grease.
Layer bacon, asparagus, mushrooms and onions in bottom of pie crust.
Beat together eggs, half and half and salt.
Pour egg mixture over top of other ingredients.
Decorate the top of the quiche with asparagus tops.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean.
Cool slightly before serving.
Serves 8.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: In crock-pot, on low to medium heat, heat cubed cheese.
Add salsa; cover.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Add to crock-pot. Stir together.
When melted, add Tabasco sauce.
Stir well.
Heat 3 minutes more, then start dipping chips!

title: glorified gingerbread cake
directions: Mix together flour, white sugar and soft oleo; take out 3/4 cup for crumb top.
Then to the rest add egg, vanilla, sour milk, soda, cinnamon and flour.
Put in greased and floured pan.
Put on crumb top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: prune bars
directions: Mix the above ingredients until crumbly.
Put half in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread with filling.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Open cans of chilies and rinse off seeds.
Open chilies to be flat and put aside.
Grate cheese and put aside.
Beat egg whites until white and stiff.
Add 1/3 cup milk and beat into eggs. Sprinkle in flour and beat in.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Mix all together and let rise double. Dump out on floured paper and knead until fluffy.
Roll out like pie crust.
Spread melted margarine on dough.
Roll up and cut into buns about 1/2-inch thick.
Put in greased pan and let rise again. Bake at about 350°.
Top with icing made from powdered sugar and a little margarine
while hot.

title: gulf shrimp stir-fry
directions: In wok or large skillet, cook cleaned shrimp in oil for 2 minutes.
Add onion, green peppers, celery, garlic, 1/2 cup broth and pepper.
Cover; steam for 2 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in remaining broth and soy sauce.
Stir into shrimp.
Add tomatoes; cook, stirring, 2 minutes or until sauce is clear and thickened. Serve over rice.
Serves 6.
Enjoy!

title: goldenrod green beans
directions: Chop egg whites.
Mash the egg yolks.
Heat the beans.
Make a cream sauce of butter, flour, salt, pepper and milk.
Remove from heat, stir in mayonnaise and egg whites.
Drain the beans, cover with sauce.
Garnish with mashed egg yolks.
Serves 4.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 400° until brown.

title: prune cake
directions: You will need 8 (1 pint size) wide-mouth jars with lids and rings for sealing.
You will also need 8 wax paper circles cut to fit inside canning jars (smaller than flat lid).

title: peanut butter pie
directions: In double boiler, cook first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add next 3 ingredients and cook until thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and add last 3 ingredients.
Beat until creamy.
Chill filling and then fill pie shells and top with Cool Whip.
Makes 3 pies.

title: herbed cheese dip
directions: Mix thoroughly, cover and refrigerate at least overnight.

title: papa's favorite fluffy lemon cookies
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and food coloring, if desired. Drop by teaspoon into sugar and roll until covered.
Place on greased cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sam's congealed salad
directions: Empty Cool Whip in a large bowl.
Pour in jello; stir while pouring.
After thoroughly mixed, pour in cottage cheese and sour cream.
Stir to mix well.
Let pineapple and oranges drain well. Put them into the mixture and stir well.
Refrigerate.

title: fresh salsa
directions: Chop up equal amounts of tomatoes, onions and green peppers to make a gallon.
Add jalapeno peppers, sugar and banana pepper with the olive oil and salt.

title: barbara's fruit trifle
directions: Crumble
cake
into
bite
size
pieces.
Mix glaze and fruit. Mix Cool Whip, sour cream and sugar.
Place a layer of cake, then fruit and then cream mixture.
Keep layering until all is used. Top with a little fruit.

title: triple orange salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and pineapple. Measure and add enough water to juice to make 3 1/2 cups. Heat to boiling. Add gelatin. Stir until dissolved. Cool slightly. Add frozen orange juice and stir until melted. Add drained fruit. Chill.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together in a large bowl.
Mix well and pour into 2 bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester comes out clean.

title: crusty pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla and flour.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour 10 minutes at 325 degrees.

title: diet catsup
directions: Combine in saucepan.
Bring to boil and then simmer to about half (stir often while cooking).
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: blackberry tarte
directions: Combine crumbs, melted butter and 1 cup sugar.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs and cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar together until smooth.
Add vanilla; spread over crust.
Bake at 250° for 25 minutes.
Cool, spread pie filling lightly over top with fork, until evenly covered.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fruity pizza(great dessert)
directions: Cut cookie dough into 1/8-inch slices.
Arrange dough slices, slightly overlapping, on foil-lined 14-inch pizza pan or 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Press edges to seal.
Bake at 375° fo 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool; remove from foil onto serving plate.
Fold whipped topping into sour cream; spread over crust.
Arrange fruit on whipped topping.
Chill.
Cut into wedges or square pieces.

title: bran blueberry muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine bran cereal, buttermilk, honey and oil and add beaten eggs.
Let stand 10 minutes.
In a second bowl, combine flour, oat or wheat bran, baking powder, soda and salt. Mix and add to cereal mixture; stir just until moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Spoon batter into muffin tins sprayed with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 400° oven or until a wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool in pan minutes, then remove from pan on rack to cool.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in salt water until tender; drain. Combine sour cream and soup and add to squash.
Melt margarine and combine with herb stuffing mix.
Put half in bottom of casserole dish, then add squash.
Top with other half of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: alison's ham, raisins and pasta
directions: Saute ham, garlic, olive oil and butter for several minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add the raisins, walnuts and parsley. Saute for another 3 minutes and then toss with drained pasta. Makes 6 servings.

title: governor's casserole
directions: Cook cauliflower and broccoli until slightly underdone. Drain.
Place in 4-quart casserole and sprinkle with chopped ham.

title: company beef casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add tomatoes, onions, green pepper, salt, pepper, steak sauce and ketchup.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook macaroni as usual, then put into casserole dish.
Add mushroom soup and meat mixture to macaroni; mix together.
Put grated cheese on top.
Cook approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: onion rice
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add cold water and butter in heavy saucepan.
Turn heat high; when mixture boils, reduce heat to medium-low.
Stir once with fork.
Cover tightly and simmer 12 to 15 minutes, or until all liquid is absorbed.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: golden crowns
directions: Combine
first 4
ingredients
and
cool
to
lukewarm. Soften the yeast in
the
lukewarm
mixture.
Add and mix well the eggs and flour.	Let
rise
until
double
in
bulk. Punch down. Shape into small rolls the size of a walnut. Roll in the melted butter, then in
the sugar, raisins, nuts and cinnamon. I
put
them
in an	angel food pan in rings until full.
Let rise, then bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green peppers, celery, cauliflower, green onions and bacon bits. Top with 2 cups Miracle Whip.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup sugar over Miracle Whip. Top with a layer of grated Cheddar cheese, about 1 pound.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Toss 30 minutes before serving.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in large pan.
Drain.
Chop and fry onion in butter.
Add to hamburger.
Add stewed tomatoes (blended in blender), tomato sauce, chili powder, sugar, seasoning salt, salt and pepper and water.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: finger paint base
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and flour.
If using food color, add color to water and then to mix.
If using powdered paint, add to dry mix, then add water.

title: chicken pockets
directions: Combine cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Add chicken, pimento, salt, pepper, and milk.
Separate rolls into 6 rectangles.
Spoon mixture into rolls evenly.
Pull up corners and twist dough tightly at the top.
Melt last tablespoon of butter and brush on all pockets.
Roll in croutons or sprinkle on top. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for 25 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a shallow casserole dish that has been lightly buttered.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: caramels
directions: Pour sugar, syrup and 1/2 cream into huge pan.
Bring to a boil.
Just before boiling, add baking soda.
Add rest of cream slowly.
Cok until candy thermometer reaches 243°.

title: mashed potato cookies
directions: Beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla together (use electric mixer).
Then add biscuit mix and instant potatoes.
Bake at 250° to 300°, depending on your oven, for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cook tomatoes until boiling.
Add sugar and margarine.
Heat until sugar is dissolved.
Tear bread into pieces and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Cook in greased baking dish at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: italian rice pie
directions: Mix all together and stir well.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 to 1 1/4 hours until done.

title: guacamole rotel dip
directions: Cook ground beef until done.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, melt milk and cubed cheese together.
Stir constantly.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Stir.
Pour cheese mixture and beef into large Tupperware bowl.
Add chili powder, sour cream and guacamole. Stir.
Garnish with jalapenos.

title: ice pick cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, oil and 3/4 cup water.
Beat with electric mixer 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes.

title: no crust fudge pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, and butter.
Add flour, cocoa and salt. Stir in vanilla and nuts. Pour into buttered 8-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
(Better to underbake.)
Cut into wedges.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: basic herbal oil and vinegar dressing
directions: *Use any combination of basil, parsley, sweet marjoram, chives or thyme or use 1 tablespoon dried herbs.

title: low-salt, low-calorie vegetable soup
directions: This soup is ready in minutes.

title: banana walnut loaf
directions: Mix sugar, shortening and eggs; beat hard until light.
Add mashed banana.
Sift flour with baking powder, salt and soda. Stir into creamed mixture, beating until smooth.
Then add the walnuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes or until loaf tests done.
Cool on rack. Recipe makes one loaf!

title: sherbet punch
directions: Soften sherbet. Add by large scoops to punch bowl. Pour chilled 7-Up over the sherbet and serve.

title: aunt penny's chili
directions: Cook beef, onion and green pepper in skillet until soft and brown.
Add pork and beans, catsup and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Add a little water if too dry.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice & boil carrots in salt water until tender. Drain & cool. Alternate layers: carrots, pepper, onion. Mix Marinade well, beating. Pour over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate.

title: never fail drop cookies
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients, then add flour. Drop on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Coconut or nuts may be added if desired.

title: better than anything cake
directions: Bake German chocolate cake according to cake mix.
Cool.
Poke large holes (pencil size) all over.

title: jambalaya
directions: In a large Dutch oven, melt butter.

Saute onion in butter for 2 to 3 minutes or until tender. Stir in remaining ingredients. Blend well. Cover and simmer for 20 to 30 minutes until rice is tender and liquid has been absorbed, stirring occasionally. Remove bay leaf and serve.

title: rehearsal dinner chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Wrap each breast section in a slice of chipped beef, then wrap with bacon.
Lay them in an oblong baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Mix sour cream, soup and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake covered 90 minutes. Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Serve with white rice and green beans almondine.

title: mushroom bisque
directions: In a heavy 4-quart pot, melt margarine over moderate heat. Stir in flour.
Cook about 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in chicken broth until smooth.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Bring mixture to a simmer.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes over moderate heat.
Stir in milk, cream and spices.
Heat until warm.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine onion and broth; bring to a boil.
Add potatoes and return to boil.
Reduce heat; simmer until potatoes are tender. Cut cheese into chunks and stir into potatoes.
When cheese melts, add flakes.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put turkey mixture into buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.
Serve with rice and a salad.

title: play clay
directions: Combine the water and colored cooking oil.
Add this water mixture to flour and salt.
The clay should be the consistency of biscuits or pie dough.
When not being used, store in plastic bag or sealed container in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carolina coleslaw
directions: With a sharp knife, slice each quarter cabbage very fine. Combine with green pepper and onion.

title: tiny taters
directions: Preheat the oven to 400°. Coat a large rimmed baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray. Using your hands, roll the mashed potatoes into small nuggets. Flatten each end and place on the cookie sheet. Brush the top and sides of each with the egg yolks. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown. Serve immediately. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oxtail soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; bring to boil.
Skim froth.
Add other ingredients, simmer 2 hours and serve hot.
Noodles are less flabby is added in the last hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Cook chicken in oil; drain.
Add vegetables, broth and salt; bring to a boil.
Mix cornstarch and soy sauce together and in the mix to thicken.
Sprinkle with cashews.

title: family peanut pound cake
directions: Sift
the

flour, baking powder and salt together twice. Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
To the butter mixture

vanilla and butternut flavoring and then the	eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each addition.

and heat in a 200° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
