(325°) for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool for 15 minutes on a rack and then remove from pan.
Frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: tennessee cheddar soup
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until soft.
Add flour and mix until smooth.
Add chicken stock.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cheese; cook 10 minutes longer. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Heat to serving temperature.
Makes 2 quarts, approximately 12 servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together broccoli and onion.
Add crisp bacon, raisins and sunflower seeds.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; add to vegetable mixture.
Chill for 3 hours.

title: pumpkin custard cups
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat milk in heavy 1-quart saucepan until hot, but not boiling.
Mix pumpkin, brown sugar, 2 tablespoons syrup, cinnamon, ginger, eggs and egg whites in a large bowl until smooth.
Beat in hot milk.
Divide evenly among 6 ungreased 10-ounce custard cups.
Place cups in rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, on oven rack.
Pour very hot water into pan to within 1-inch of tops of cups.

title: quick luscious coconut cake
directions: Mix cake mix with eggs, buttermilk and soda.
Bake in two layers until done.
Split with thread into 4 layers.
Fill and frost with frosting which is made by whipping sour cream until it is double in bulk.
Add sugar and whip thoroughly until dissolved. Fold in Cool Whip.
Fold in 1 1/2 packages of thawed coconut. Fill and stack layers and frost sides and top.
Then sprinkle with remaining 1/2 package coconut.

title: chicken piccata
directions: Beat egg with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip chicken in egg mixture and then in flour mixture.
Brown chicken in skillet in margarine.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Add remaining lemon juice.
Pour into skillet. Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the sugar, milk, eggs and oil.
Blend dry ingredients into cream mixture.
Add vanilla, food coloring and vinegar. Grease and flour three 8-inch cake pans.
Cook for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: save your sugar bars
directions: Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with a mixture of flour and salt and garlic powder.
Brown quickly in oil in a large skillet.
Place browned pork chops in crock-pot.
Add soup plus 1/2 can of water.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, mix with other ingredients.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with 1 1/2 package Ritz crackers.
Crumbled with melted butter.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy chicken
directions: Saute chicken breasts in frypan with butter and sprinkle of garlic powder.
Brown both sides.
Mix soup with 3/4 can of water. Pour over chicken.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
The last minute before serving, add the sour cream.
Great served over wide noodles.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and oil.
Add eggs and bananas.
Sift dry ingredients together; stir into banana mixture.
Add alternately with milk and about 3 tablespoons water (cold).
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Let refrigerated pie crusts stand at room temperature according to package directions. Cook frozen vegetables according to package directions; drain. In a medium saucepan, cook onion and mushrooms in hot butter or margarine until tender. Stir in the flour, herb, salt and pepper. Add broth and the 3/4 cup

milk all at once. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in the chicken or turkey, parsley, pimiento and vegetables; cook and stir until bubbly. Pour chicken mixture into six 10-ounce individual casseroles.

title: vienna tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Blend cream cheese, butter and flour until smooth.
Chill in refrigerator 30 minutes.
Roll into 12 small balls and place in 12 greased miniature muffin cups.
Punch a hole in each ball of dough and fill with 3/4 teaspoon preserves. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Carefully remove tarts from tins with a smooth knife.

title: fresh fruit dip
directions: Have both at room temperature.
Mix together with hand mixer. Use as a dip for chunks of fresh pineapple, banana, grapes, apple, strawberries, etc.
Also good served on top of a dish of fresh fruit salad.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in pan. Saut green chilies in butter. While hot, add corn (drained) and cream cheese. Add salt and pepper to taste. Can substitute garlic salt for regular salt.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Put potatoes in dish.
Mix other ingredients together and put on top. Add crackers on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or longer.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef, celery and onion. Drain grease. Mix with vegetables. Add soup, potatoes flakes, pepper and garlic powder. Place in pan and cover with tater tots. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: pound cake deluxe
directions: Beat egg whites and add 6 tablespoons of original sugar; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks, two at a time. Alternate flour with cream; fold in beaten egg whites.
Add vanila. Bake in stem pan 1 hour 35 minutes in 300° oven.

title: mulberry jelly
directions: Cook berries in water for about 1 hour.
Strain out the juice. Add 1 pint of sugar to each pint of juice and bring to boil, then add Sure-Jell to thicken.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: majestic layered salad
directions: In 2 1/2-quart salad bowl, layer spinach, mushrooms, onions and peas.
Combine mayo, sugar and curry powder.
Spread over salad to seal.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Top with bacon before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: raisin pie
directions: Wash raisins first; simmer in the 1 cup of water for 10 minutes.
Add salt and sugar; cook until sugar is dissolved.
Beat egg yolks.
Mix cornstarch and milk to raisins and stir.
Cook until thickened.
Pour into 2 baked 9-inch pie shells.

title: mama's chocolate cake
directions: Cook until it thickens egg, chocolate and milk. Remove from stove and add sugar, butter, sour milk, soda, vanilla and flour. Mix carefully by hand. Pour in a greased 9 x 9 pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Cut in squares and put on real whipping cream (like we had on the farm) on top and enjoy.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add alternately, while blending, the whipping cream and flour.
Add vanilla.
Blend well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
This makes a large, moist cake.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium bowl, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn dough out onto well-floured surface and knead 15 to 20 times.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with a 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place biscuits on a lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in blender.
Add dry mix.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 big loaves.

title: chinese chicken
directions: In large pan, boil chicken (enough water to cover chicken), sprinkle of soy sauce, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken and cut into small pieces.
Put cut up pieces of chicken back into boiling chicken broth and add 1 can chicken broth and frozen vegetables.
Drain watercress and bean sprouts.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Take flour and water, shake to form a gravy.
Keep stirring, when thickened, remove from heat and serve over rice or noodles.
Sprinkle top with soy sauce, if desired.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage until transparent and drain.
In large greased casserole dish, layer crushed crackers with layer of cabbage.
Put pats of butter on top and salt and pepper to taste.
Pour milk over casserole until crackers are soaked.
Bake in low oven (275° to 300°) for 1 1/2 hours.
If you want top brown, uncover for last 15 minutes and turn the oven up.

title: broccoli and cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan. Stir in flour, salt and pepper to create a paste. Heat milk in a large saucepan. Add broccoli, onions and butter paste to milk and cook until vegetables are tender and the soup is thickened. Add cheese and heat until melted. Do not scald milk; cook over medium heat. Tastes great with slice of homemade bread. Serves 8.

title: crock pot beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in crock pot on low for 8 to 10 hours.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: These taste much like fried eggplant.
Slice tomatoes 1/2-inch thick. Dry the slices. Dip in the eggs, then in bread crumbs. Salt and pepper.
Fry in heavy skillet over moderate fire.
They cook quickly.

title: chunky barbecue beef
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Brown meat in skillet with vegetable spray. Add remaining ingredients. Mix; pour into 2-quart casserole. Cover. Bake 2 hours. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: eclair cake
directions: Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Line with graham crackers. Mix pudding with milk at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Place second layer of crackers over pudding.
Pour rest of pudding over crackers.
Place another layer of crackers over pudding. Refrigerate for 12 hours.
Two hours before serving, ice with Pillsbury frosting.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together water, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until thickened and add the strawberry jello and food coloring.
Let cool and pour over berries in cooled pie shell.

title: never fail nut roll
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine walnuts, milk, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 1 egg and 1/2 cup butter; mix well. Cook over medium heat until thick. Set aside. Allow to cool and lukewarm before spreading on dough.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken in 1 can of chicken broth, drain and debone.
Mix with soup, mixed vegetables and 1 cup of broth.
Top with topping.

title: buttermilk-coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for about 30 or 45 minutes or until pie is done.

title: date cookies
directions: Combine water with dates, cinnamon, shortening and nutmeg. Boil for 3 minutes and cool.
Add eggs, soda, salt, 2 tablespoons water and sweetener.
Mix flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Add to cooled mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen cookies. Carbohydrate 13 g, protein 1 g, fat 3 g, calories 74.
One cookie = 1 bread exchange.

title: cherry squares
directions: Use jelly roll pan.
Mix ingredients well.
Reserve small amount of dough.
Roll large portion and place on shallow cooking sheet.
Fill with 2 to 4 cans cherry pie filling (or you favorite flavor.)
Use remaining dough for strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 12.

title: spicy cheese dip
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Remove and drain off fat.
In saucepan, heat soup, stirring until smooth.
Add tomatoes and sausage.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Serve with taco chips.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple and keep syrup.
Mix sugar, gelatin and salt. Add hot water to syrup to make 3/4 cup liquid and add to sugar mixture.
Heat until sugar and gelatin dissolve.
Chill until partially set (weak jelly).
Add pineapple and shredded cheese. Fold in whipping cream.
Turn into 1-quart mold Chill until firm.

title: zucchini bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Trim ends of zucchini.
Cook, covered, in boiling salted water 5 to 8 minutes; drain.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out centers; chop.
Cook onion in margarine until tender.
Combine with chopped zucchini, tomato, seasonings, cheese and bacon; fill zucchini.
Arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: saucy apple swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan. In a small bowl, combine sugar and cinnamon; set aside. In a large bowl, blend cake mix, applesauce and eggs until moistened. Beat 2 minutes at high speed. Pour 1/2 of batter into prepared pan. Sprinkle with sugar mixture. Cover with remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool upright in pan 25 minutes. Turn onto serving plate and cool completely. Dust with powdered sugar.

title: polish potato casserole
directions: Simply alternate layers of sliced potato and onion; season each layer.
Top with butter, dill and parsley.
Pour milk over top.
Bake 45 minutes in oven or 20 minutes in microwave.
May be served with sour cream and extra dill.

title: ramen cole slaw
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Toast almonds 5 to 10 minutes. Remove from oven. Toss all ingredients in a large bowl. Keep chilled.

title: crunchy cole slaw
directions: Combine all and toss thoroughly just before serving.

title: ritz cracker salad
directions: Place 1/2 crumbs in an 8-inch pan.
Melt the butter and mix with the powdered sugar, Cool Whip, condensed milk and 6 ounces juice.
Pour mixture over crumbs and top with remaining crumbs. Chill.

title: kansas dirt
directions: Put half the crushed cookies in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Cream together cream cheese, butter and powdered sugar. Add milk, pudding, vanilla and Cool Whip.
Blend well.
Pour mixture over crushed cookies and top with other half.
Freeze or refrigerate until firm.
Serves 8 to 12.

title: baked ribs and sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut ribs into small pieces.
In large frypan, brown ribs.
Drain fat.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: baked apples-microwave
directions: Wash and core apples.
Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish or individual custard cups.
Fill center of each apple with 1 tablespoon sugar, 1 teaspoon butter and a few seedless raisins, if desired.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cook 5 minutes on High, uncovered.
Let stand several minutes.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: Cut orange slices in small bits; mix with 1/4 cup of the flour.
Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add oats, coconut and candy mix.
Bake in a 375° oven until delicately browned.

title: taco pie
directions: Grease square baking dish.
Cook ground beef and onion until beef is browned; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix and pour in dish. Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth, about 1 minute.
Pour into dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted (2 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Garnish with lettuce and tomato.

title: tarragon vegetable omelet
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook carrots, covered, in boiling water for 5 minutes. Add broccoli.
Cover and cook about 10 minutes more or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain.

title: homemade french onion soup
directions: *You may dilute canned bouillon with 2 cups of water.

title: rolls
directions: Measure into a bowl the warm water.
Add and stir yeast.
Stir in sugar, salt, shortening and egg.
Mix in flour.
Place, greased side up, in a greased bowl.
Cover with damp cloth and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: chop suey casserole
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Mix in other ingredients except noodles.
Top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: triple treats candy
directions: Melt morsels and shortening over hot (not boiling) water. Stir until melted and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Pour half of the chocolate into an 8-inch greased, foil lined square pan. Spread evenly.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).
Return remaining chocolate to low heat.
Melt caramels and margarine with water over low heat, stirring until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Pour into the chocolate lined pan.
Spread evenly. Refrigerate about 15 minutes. Top with remaining chocolate mixture.
Spread evenly to caramel filling. Return to refrigerator and chill until firm (about 1 hour).
Cut into pieces and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: heavenly apple salad
directions: Combine lime jello and hot water.
Dissolve marshmallows, then add cold water and chill.
Add apples, pineapple and nuts.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: In large mixing bowl, mix pumpkin, Eagle Brand milk, eggs, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and ginger.
Mix all ingredients good. Pour into pie shells and cook in preheated oven at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Take out and let cool before serving.

title: ham and noodle casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
When blended, pour in milk and cook until a creamy sauce forms.
Stir constantly.
Add ham and pour over noodles.
Place in a shallow, buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake 20 minutes in a moderate oven (about 350°).

title: beef jerky
directions: Cut meat in 3/4-inch wide strips with grain.
Dissolve salt in warm water and then add remaining ingredients.
Soak meat in mixture about 2 hours, turning strips of meat frequently so that each piece is drenched with mixture.
Place strips of meat on paper towels for a few minutes.
Then place strips of meat on oven rack.
Turn heat on to 120° to 130° and cook at this temperature for 8 to 9 hours with oven door slightly cracked open.
After cooking, turn off heat, open oven door and let air dry for 8 more hours.
Package jerky in bags or jars.

title: fiesta bread
directions: Mix the ingredients and spread on French bread.
Cut lengthwise.
Run under broiler for a few minutes or wrap in foil and heat in preheated oven or barbecue pit.

title: pumpkin cheese cake
directions: Press graham cracker crust in spring-form pan.
In large bowl with mixer, combine cream cheese, eggs and 3/4 cup of sugar until smooth.
Add almond extract and salt.
Pour 2 cups of mixture into crust.
To remaining cream cheese mixture, blend in pumpkin, cinnamon, nutmeg and remaining sugar.
Pour pumpkin mixture over cream cheese mixture.
With knife, gently swirl to marble.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or unti cake is almost set.
Center will still be soft.
Cool completely.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients, adding bananas and nuts last.
Pour into a loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve with cream cheese.

title: stuffed tomatoes with shrimp salad
directions: Chop eggs finely.
Mix with onions, mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Chop shrimp in large pieces and mix in.
Place clean lettuce leaf on saucer.
Place tomato, cut across 4 times, not all the way through.
Open tomato and fill with mixture.
Serves 4.

title: fresh peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Sift dry ingredients into mixing bowl. Combine milk, egg and butter.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Fold in peaches.
Spoon batter into greased muffin tin and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Take Brown-in-Bag and shake flour in bag.
Place all meat, potatoes and carrots in bag.
Then take all seasonings and place on meat, potatoes and carrots.
Close bag; tie.
Slit 3 or 4 holes on top of bag.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: thor's roadkill chili
directions: In a large kettle, brown meat in oil.
Add onions, garlic, pepper, chili powder and beer.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and beans; simmer, stirring occasionally, for 15 minutes. Place crushed dried chili peppers on 8-inch square of cheesecloth 3 layers thick and tie at top with string.
Submerge bag in chili; stir and let simmer for 15 minutes more.
Remove bag.
(If you want really hot chili, put on rubber gloves and squeeze juice from bag into chili.
Warning: The more you squeeze, the hotter it gets!)

title: gingerbread boys
directions: Cream sugar, salt and shortening.
Stir in egg, molasses and vinegar.
Beat well.
Sift together dry ingredients; stir into molasses mix.
Chill about 3 hours.
On a lightly floured board, roll to 1/8 inch.
Cut with gingerbread boy cutter (or draw pattern).
Place 1 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Use raisins for eyes and buttons.
Bake about 6 minutes at 375°.
Cool slightly.
Frost, if desired.

title: vegetarian lasagne
directions: Spread mixture evenly over noodles in casserole pan.
Top with sauce.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: sweet sour green beans
directions: Cook beans until just tender; drain and measure (1/4 cup liquid) or water.
Fry diced bacon until brown.
Add onion, sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper, beans and water; cook about 5 minutes or until hot through.

title: orange raisin cake
directions: Grind orange and raisins and set aside.
Cream sugar and Crisco and beat in egg.
Sift flour and salt; stir soda into milk. Add alternately to sugar mixture.
Stir in 3/4 of orange mixture and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: golden pheasant punch
directions: Mix.
Put cream soda in just before serving.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Brown sausage in large pot.
Add celery and cook 10 minutes. Drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except green peppers. Cover and boil 20 minutes.
Add green pepper and cook until tender.
Serve with warm Italian bread.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Put cheese and soup in double boiler until cheese melts. Put broccoli in a buttered casserole. Pour cheese and soup mixture over. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top. Bake at 375° until bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle stuffing on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: old-timey school yeast rolls
directions: Melt Crisco in 1/4 cup water; let cool.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Mix dry ingredients together, then add Crisco mixture.
Add yeast mixture and mix well.
Fold in eggs and knead thoroughly.
Let rise until mixture is double in bulk; punch down and then let rise again.
Make into rolls.
Let rise and bake at 400° until golden brown.
Always keep the dough warm.

title: cajun baked catfish
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Dredge catfish in cornmeal mixture; place fillets, skin sides down, on a greased baking pan. Sprinkle Cajun seasoning and lemon pepper over fillets; drizzle with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden and fish flakes with a fork.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, for 20 to 30 minutes or until sauce reaches desired consistency, stirring occasionally. Use as a basting sauce when grilling hamburgers or chicken and/or use as a condiment.
Store in the refrigerator.
Yields about 1 1/3 cups.

title: refrigerator potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes with salt; mash.
Add cream cheese, onion salt, salt and pepper to taste and margarine.
Beat until fluffy.
Cool, cover and refrigerate.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: italian tortillas(vegetarian)
directions: Mix 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, spinach, corn, Ricotta and egg. Place 1/2 cup mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll tightly; arrange seam side down in greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix tomatoes, tomato sauce and basil; spoon over filled tortillas. Sprinkle with remaining Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cantonese pork
directions: Brown pork in oil.
Drain on paper towel.
Place all ingredients into covered pot and cook 1 to 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.
Serve over hot rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Blend cheese, butter and cayenne pepper thoroughly.
Add flour and mix until no flour shows.
Chill thoroughly.
Shape into balls 1-inch in diameter.
Bake at 450° until puffed and brown.
May bake frozen.

title: magic lemon meringue pie
directions: In a medium size mixing bowl, blend milk, lemon juice, egg yolks and vanilla until slightly thickened.
Fill pie shell.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into sprayed casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: teaballs
directions: Beat well until fluffy.
Put on an ungreased cookie sheet with spoon.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown at 325°.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: spoon bread
directions: Stir meal into 2 cups milk.
Let come to a boil, making a mush.
Add remainder of milk, eggs (well beaten), salt, baking powder and butter.
Pour into a 1 1/2 to 2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: mexican bean bake
directions: Spray 8 x 8-inch baking dish with cooking spray.
Mix first 4 ingredients.
Top with salsa and shredded cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes or until set.
Top with lettuce, tomato and yogurt.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut up cabbage and onion; place in baking dish.
Brown hamburger meat and place on top of cabbage and onion.
Pour can of tomato soup on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Amounts depend on how many will be served.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients.
If too dry, add little milk to make dough "drip".
In large 4-quart pan boil water.
Drop by teaspoonful into water and boil 5 minutes.
Great served with fried cabbage, spaghetti sauce or gravies.

title: cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter.
Press in bottom of 9-inch spring pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 300°.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth.
Pour over crumb mixture.
Bake for 1 hour or until center is firm.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: apricot glazed ham
directions: Place ham on rack in a shallow roasting pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 325° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until meat thermometer registers 140°.

title: snappy cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese. Fluff in mixer. Fold in Cheddar cheese. Chill overnight. Mold into two small or one large ball. Roll in chopped pecans or bright green parsley flakes.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch, cinnamon and nutmeg and add salt and water.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add lemon juice. Pack sliced apples in hot jars.
Fill with syrup.
Water bath quarts, 20 minutes or pressure cook 5 pounds for 10 minutes.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Mix ingredients and place in rolls; fold corners of rolls to make a bundle. Roll in butter, then into bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and salt together in a small bowl.
Add to butter and sugar mixture.
Add chocolate chips and pecans. Bake at 300°.
Use a small cookie scoop or small ice cream scoop to form cookies.
Bake until light brown.

title: skillet granola
directions: Melt margarine in electric skillet; set at 350° or stove top skillet set on high.
Add sugar, salt and water.
Mix well.
Add oats.
Stir in skillet for 7 to 10 minutes until brown.

title: pork tenderloin with gravy
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 5 ingredients until blended. Set aside. In a large skillet, brown pork in oil on all sides. Stir in gravy mixture, mushrooms and onions. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer until meat is done. Serve over rice. Makes 2 servings.

title: beef -n- cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese in oven at 250°. Brown ground beef, onion and garlic. Drain. Add salsa to beef and let simmer 10 minutes. Add 2 cans of tomatoes to melted cheese. Add beef to cheese mixture. Let it sit in oven about 5 minutes. Serve with nacho chips.

title: trifle(sugar-free)
directions: Use a large glass clear bowl (punch bowl).
Layer 1/2 angel food cake (broken into small pieces), 8 ounces strawberries, 1 banana (sliced).
Repeat layers.
Dilute Jell-O with boiling water and lemon juice.
Cool a little before pouring over layers in bowl. Mix vanilla pudding according to directions on package.
Spread over cake and Jell-O mixture.
Whip the whipped topping or use lite Cool Whip and spread over pudding layer.
Let set in refrigerator until firm.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Dip corn tortillas in enchilada sauce.
Make layer in large flat dish.
Brown beef, season to taste and drain.
Add chili and soup.
Mix well.
Spread 1/3 of meat mixture over tortillas. Sprinkle 1/3 of onion and grated cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until heated.

title: hot percolator punch
directions: Put all ingredients in bottom of pot and put spices in percolator basket.

title: green bean casserole deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In bowl combine beans, soup, milk, 1/2 cup French fried onion rings, 1/2 jar bacon bits and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onion rings and bacon bits.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: meatballs(party style)
directions: Have meat ground together 2 or 3 times.
Crumble bread and add milk.
Stir to blend until it is of paste like consistency. Combine with meat in mixing bowl and add seasonings and eggs.
Beat and stir with wooden spoon until stiff.
Dip out rounded teaspoonfuls and roll between hands into 1-inch balls.
Place on waxed paper for about 1/2 hour to dry.
Brown balls in 1/2-inch hot shortening.
Put in single layer in baking dish.
Add bouillon and bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven or until most of the broth is absorbed.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate rolls into triangles and make crust in large pan. Top with sausage and hash browns.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper together.
Pour over sausage and potatoes.
Top with cheeses.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve in pizza wedges.

title: microwave tuna medley
directions: Combine carrots, celery and onion in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover.
Microwave at High 3 to 4 1/2 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, tuna, peas, soy sauce and seasonings. Cover.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes or until thoroughly heated, stirring after half the cooking time.
Stir in two-thirds of the potatoes.
Microwave 30 to 60 seconds.
Sprinkle remaining potatoes and cashews over top.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Have ingredients at room temperature.
Mix well.
Remove crusts from loaf sandwich bread.
Butter each slice.
Put two slices together as for a sandwich.
Cut into three pieces (sticks).
Cover top and sides of each stick with the cheese mixture.
Place on cookie sheet 1-inch apart and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vanilla wafer cheese cakes
directions: You will need foil cupcake cups.

title: ajide gallina(chicken with yellow hot pepper)
directions: In a 5-quart Dutch oven, place chicken and fill with water. Boil until chicken is white and falling off bone.
Remove chicken and reserve water.
Remove skin and bones from chicken and shred chicken.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix milk and pudding; beat until thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Line vanilla wafers in bowl.
Top with layer of bananas.
Add a layer of pudding mixture.
Repeat until all pudding is used.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: broccoli and cavatelli
directions: Cook chopped broccoli until soft.
Cook cavatelli according to package directions.
Set aside.
Heat olive oil; lightly brown crushed garlic, then add broccoli and heat through.
Add cavatelli and toss with broccoli.
Top with grated Parmesan cheese and sit down and enjoy!!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients to soft boil.
Take off.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir (with mixer).

title: spiced peaches
directions: Boil sugar, vinegar and peach juice.
Use any size jars you wish.
Put peaches	in
jars; add cloves.
Pour juice over peaches.

title: salad
directions: Break lettuce up and lay out on platter.
Cut up celery and onion and layer over lettuce.
Mix sour cream and sugar.
Drizzle over lettuce.
Mix salad dressing and vinegar; drizzle over lettuce.
Sprinkle with frozen peas, bacon bits and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put in a pot over medium heat margarine and sugar.
Stir up over low heat continuously.
Add flour and stir.
Add salt and peaches and stir.
Add brandy; stir for 5 minutes.
Put in greased glass dish.

title: golden cornbread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients; add liquid ingredients and stir until well mixed.
Bake in greased 8-inch square pan at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes until browned.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Do not preheat oven!

title: baked corn
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for about 1 hour.

title: banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat the oven to 425°.
Mix the dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix the milk, bananas, egg whites and oil in a bowl or blender.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix.
Line the muffin pan with paper baking cups and fill them with batter.
Bake for 17 minutes.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: chili
directions: In a heavy pot, melt butter.
Crumble meat into pot.
Cook a few minutes until meat is no longer pink.
Remove.
To the pot, add onion and pepper.
Cook a few minutes, stirring, until vegetables are soft.
Add meat.
Stir to combine.
Add remaining ingredients. Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cook, stirring occasionally, at least 45 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Blend cream cheese, eggs and confectioners sugar.
Mix well. Pour over the first layer.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes until crust is brown.

title: spiced tea
directions: Put the spices
in
a
bag
and
boil with the sugar 20 minutes.
Add tea to the 12 cups boiling water and let stand 4 to 5 minutes.
Add
the
juices
and
the
syrup made from the sugar and spices to the tea.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix well and freeze.
Use pan or muffin tin with paper cups.

title: fruit juicy iced tea(orange spice)
directions: Heat ingredients on low heat in a saucepan for 20 minutes. Strain, chill and serve over ice.
Each 6-ounce serving contains 35 calories.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
May be made a day ahead of use.

title: pinon de amarillos
directions: Stir-fry garlic in oil.
Add peppers, onion, coriander, cilantro, tomato sauce and sazon.
Add meat and season well; cook 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Fry plantains, cut in pieces. Grease an 8 x 12 x 2-inch pan and place plantains in bottom.
Add meat mixture, spread evenly and press down.
Add grated cheese, then green beans.
Make another layer of plantains.
Beat egg whites; add yolks to sugar.
Cover the dish with this meringue. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
To brown, place under broiler for 5 minutes.
Cut and eat.
Makes about 10 portions.

title: lentil-rice stew
directions: Melt margarine in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add onions and celery and cook until tender, about 10 minutes. Add water, if necessary, to prevent drying.
Reduce heat to low. Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add small amounts of water while cooking if more liquid is desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: brown rice
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour rice into baking dish.
Pour melted butter over this, then add the beef consomme.
Top with the mushrooms.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate pudding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put pudding and baking mix in a bowl and mix together.
Add oil and egg.
Mix until a "ball" forms. Take a small spoonful of dough and shape it into a 1/2-inch ball. Place ball on ungreased cookie sheet.
Repeat, placing balls 2 inches apart.
Press your thumb into the middle of each ball to make a thumbprint.
Put a candy in each thumbprint.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 8 minutes or until light brown and set.
Remove and place on racks to cool.

title: beans, beans, beans
directions: Brown separately, onions, bacon and hamburger.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook in crock-pot 1/2 to 1 hour or in a 350° oven.

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and margarine to rolling boil. Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at one time.
Continue beating until smooth; drop dough by teaspoon (or use pastry tube) 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until golden.

title: pinch sticky rolls
directions: Pinch off walnut size balls from first loaf.
Place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix margarine, sugar, milk and pudding. Pour half over first loaf.
Pinch off second loaf and place on top of first.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and nuts.

title: four seasons pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water.
Boil 1 minute or until clear.
Stir gelatin into syrup and cool.
Place fruit in baked pie shell.
Pour cooled syrup over the fruit and chill 2 hours before serving.

title: microwave parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Dip breasts in butter.
Mix bread crumbs and Parmesan together.
Coat breasts and place in dish.
Sprinkle lemon juice over, then garlic, salt and paprika.
Cover.
Microwave on High for 4 minutes; turn bowl 1/4 turn and cook 4 more minutes.

title: eggplant, zucchini parmigiana
directions: In electric skillet bring 1/2-inch water to boil.
Add zucchini and eggplant, boil 4 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Divide zucchini and eggplant between 2 baking dishes or casseroles.
Spoon cottage cheese atop and divide sauce evenly over each dish. Sprinkle with Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.

title: never-fail pie crust
directions: Add salt to flour; mix, then cut in lard until crumbly.
*Put egg in bowl, add vinegar and water and beat with beater.
Add to flour ingredients and mix.
Yield:
two (2-crust) pies.

title: salsa
directions: Chop up ramps, garlic, jalapeno pepper, tomatoes, green onions and green pepper.
Add Accent, salt and pepper to taste.
Add diced tomatoes; mix and let set with a cover on it.
The longer it sits the better it gets.
Serve with chips.

title: mex-chicken and rice soup
directions: Heat all together.
Do not add water.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in top of double boiler.
Cook over medium-high heat; beat until sauce thickens, time will vary, about 15 minutes.
The longer cooked the thicker the sauce.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Bake pie crusts lightly.
Slice all vegetables except mushrooms and steam.
Drain and add mushrooms.
Line crusts with Swiss cheese.
Fill crusts with vegetables.
Add egg mixture, divide between the 2 pies.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cover with sliced tomatoes and add Cheddar cheese.
Bake for another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries, sugar and marshmallows.
Cover and chill overnight.
Add apples and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers well. Take fork and scrape down sides of cucumbers (no need to peel cucumbers).
Slice cucumbers to make 3 cups.
Add the cucumbers to the onion, green pepper and salt. Cover with cold water and let stand 2 hours or longer. Drain and rinse.

title: lemon and vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine half and half, 1/3 cup sugar and vanilla bean in medium saucepan. Scald. Scrape in vanilla bean seeds. Discard bean. In bowl, whisk egg yolks with remaining 1/3 cup sugar until doubled in volume. Gradually whisk in half and half mixture. Return to heat in saucepan and stir over medium heat until custard thickens, about 3 to 4 minutes. Do not boil. Transfer to bowl and chill. Before freezing, add lemon juice and pinch of salt. Process in ice cream freezer.

title: rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir once and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: mama dub fruit cake
directions: Prepare tube cake pan with heavy brown paper and grease good. Set aside about 1 cup of flour of the 3 cups measured.
Reserve the raisins, cherries, preserves and nuts.
Mix other ingredients to a good batter.
Dredge raisins, cherries, preserves, nuts and flour you have reserved together.
Add this to the batter.
Bake at 200° until done, about 6 hours.

title: mississippi potatoes(8 to 10 servings)
directions: Toss potatoes with mayonnaise, salt, pepper, diced cheese and onions.
Place mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with crumbled bacon and chives.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Mix flour, sugar and juice together.
Pour over pineapple.
Add cheese and mix well.
Put in a buttered 2-quart dish.
Melt 1/4 cup butter and add enough cracker crumbs to soak up all the butter.
Top pineapple with cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, vanilla, salt and well beaten eggs. Put this in custard cups or 2 pie shells and bake at 400° until a knife comes out clean.

title: guacamole - tomato salad
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Scoop out centers and chop centers finely.
Turn tomatoes upside-down to drain; set aside.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In LARGE glass bowl, cream butter, sugar and milk. Place in microwave and cook on full power (HIGH) for 9 minutes. Do not stir. Remove from microwave and stir in chips, marshmallow cream and vanilla. Pour into greased 9 x 12 or smaller pan.

title: cranberry salad mold holiday
directions: Please read this before you start!
I find that a can of cranberries (1 pound can, whole) will do the same thing as raw. Crush them and be sure that you do not put any more juice than 3 cups.
I use the cranberry juice to make the 3 cups, adding it to the water and the pineapple juice.
Cut down or leave out the sugar.

title: deli  pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. In large bowl combine olives, green pepper, pepperoni, cheese, pimento and dressing. Add pasta and toss well. Chill.

title: sally's salad
directions: Make marinade of sugar, vinegar, oil, mustard, poppy and pepper.
Stir over heat to dissolve sugar.
Cool.

title: buttermilk spice cake
directions: Beat egg whites, set aside.
In bowl, mix all dry ingredients together and set aside.
In large bowl mix butter, sugar and egg yolks well.
Add flour mixture to the ingredients, alternating with buttermilk.
Add flour mixture last.
Stir in egg whites with folding motion.
Put in angel food cake greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes or more if needed.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Heat oil to 350°.
Add noodles.
Cook 5 seconds until puffed and crisp.
Drain.
Whisk next 7 ingredients.
Add oil gradually. Heat 1/2 of this mixture over high heat.
Add chicken and saute until done, about 5 minutes.
Transfer to bowl and refrigerate until well chilled, 1 hour or more.
Combine noodles, chicken and rest of ingredients.
Toss with enough of remaining dressing to season to taste.
Divide on six salad plates and serve.

title: red cabbage with diced apples
directions: Cook all of the ingredients, except the sweetener, in a covered
saucepan
for 20 minutes, or until cabbage is tender. Add sweetener.

title: swedish tea ring
directions: Light the oven; get out utensils and ingredients.
Remove blocks and toy autos from table.
Grease pan; crack nuts.
Measure 2 cups of flour; remove Johnny's hands from flour.
Wash flour off him.
Re-measure flour.
Put flour, baking powder and salt in sifter.
Get dustpan and brush.
Clean up pieces of bowl Johnny knocked on flour.
Get another bowl.
Answer doorbell.
Return to the kitchen.
Remove Johnny's hand from bowl again.
Wash Johnny again.
Answer phone.
Return.
Remove 1/4-inch of salt from greased pan.
Look for Johnny.
Grease another pan.
Answer phone. Return to kitchen and find Johnny.
Remove his hands from bowl. Pick up greased pan and find layer of nut shells in it.
Head for Johnny, who flees, knocking bowl off table.
Wash floor, table, walls, dishes, pans and Johnny.
Call bakery and lie down.

title: peach dessert
directions: Layer the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish with the angel food cake.
Mix French vanilla instant pudding, sour cream and milk.
Pour over cake.
Put the pie filling over the pudding. Then put the Cool Whip on top.
Cover and refrigerate until ready to serve.
Can be cut in half for an 8-inch square dish.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs; beat after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to mixture. Place flour in a large bowl.
Add dates, candy and candied cherries.
Stir and coat each piece; add flour mixture and coconut to creamed mixture.
This makes a stiff dough.
Put in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours or until straw comes out dry.
Mix 1 cup fresh orange juice with 2 cups confectioners sugar.
Pour over cake.

title: teriyaki turkey
directions: You will also need a plastic bag.

title: apricot nectar
directions: In saucepan, mix all ingredients except ginger ale; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Simmer gently 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Strain and chill.

title: indian fry bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add enough warm water so dough can be mixed.
Turn out on floured board and knead until not sticky.
Put bowl over dough and let rest for 15 minutes.
Take small orange size pieces of dough and pat into 1/2-inch thick circle.
Stretch a little more and deep fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: baked fish florentine
directions: Arrange catfish fillets in a casserole dish with skin side down.
Pour melted margarine over fillets.
Season both sides with salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Cover fillets with spinach and sprinkle with lemon juice over spinach.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with Cheddar cheese; bake 10 more minutes. Delicious!!!

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a 3-quart saucepan, combine broccoli and minced onion and bring to a boil.
Boil 30 seconds.
Reduce heat and stir in creamed soups and using a wire whisk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Remove about 1cup of soup and mix cornstarch until smooth.
Pour slowly into hot soup mixture and stir until soup thickens.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix ingredients with salt and pepper to taste.
Toss together 1 package Pepperidge Farm corn bread stuffing mix and 1 stick melted margarine; reserve half of mixture.
Line casserole with other half.
Add squash mixture.
Cover over with reserved stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf topped with piquant sauce
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk.
Add meat, eggs, onion, green pepper and seasonings; mix well.
Form into individual loaves or form one loaf in 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch pan, which has been greased.
Cover with Piquant Sauce (recipe follows) and spread over top of meat loaf.
Bake for 1 hour in a moderate 350° oven for a large loaf and bake for 45 minutes with small individual loaves.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix shortening and peanut butter.
Beat in sugars and egg.
Mix in flour.
Roll into balls.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet, then flatten with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crawfish casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery and peppers in oleo until transparent. Add soups, pimento and crawfish; simmer 10 to 13 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, green onions, parsley and cooked rice.
Stir well. Place in a 12-inch dish.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients, oats and chocolate bits. Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: joy's delight
directions: Mix together and pour into baked pie shell and refrigerate.

title: oven baked french toast
directions: Pour melted butter into large pan, large enough for all 8 slices. Swirl the butter to coat the pan. Mix sugar and cinnamon together. Sprinkle over butter. Beat eggs with orange juice and dip each slice of bread for 15 seconds on each side. Lay in pan. Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: jalapeno squares
directions: Spray medium size casserole dish with Pam.
Spread chopped jalapenos in dish.
Sprinkle cheese over jalapenos.
Beat eggs well and pour over top.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown at 350°.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: fruit dip
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and cream cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Serve with fresh strawberries, grapes, kiwi, pineapple, mandarin orange slices, apples, etc.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Put prepared turnips in a pot with water to cover and the salt.
Cook until well done, about 1/2 hour.
Drain well.
Mash. Add milk, sugar and butter; continue mixing.
Pour into buttered, oven-proof casserole.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes or until browned on top.
Serves 8.

title: no bake cookies(healthy kind)
directions: Put the first 4 ingredients on medium heat.
Cook until it starts to boil.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir well, drop on wax paper by teaspoons to cool.

title: heath bar coffee cake
directions: Blend flour, butter and both sugars.
Take out 1/2 cup and reserve.
To the rest, add buttermilk, soda, egg and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into a greased 10 x 14 x 2-inch cake pan.
Take crushed Heath bar and nuts.
Add the 1/2 cup reserved mixture and sprinkle over top of batter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados well. Add onion, salt, pepper and Tabasco (a few dashes). Seed and squeeze excess juice out of the tomato and add it and the garlic. Mix well and squeeze at least a teaspoon lemon over the dip and blend again. Do not use mayonnaise in this recipe. It complicates the natural flavor. Also, if not enough salt is used, it will be bland.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Beat well the margarine, molasses, sugar, eggs and spices. Sift together the flour and soda and add to the other ingredients. Refrigerate dough for several hours.
Make into small balls and roll in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Separate eggs (reserve whites for meringue); put egg yolks in double boiler or heavy saucepan.
Stir until smooth; add sugar, 2 tablespoons water and 5 tablespoons flour.
Continue to stir until smooth; add evaporated milk, water and coconut.
Stir until well blended.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Stir often while cooking.
Add vanilla; mix and pour into baked pie shell.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Mix together the first 6 ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in the nuts and cherries.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Place strawberries in bowl.
Sprinkle sugar over berries. Berries should marinate 3 to 4 hours.
Drain juice into top of double boiler.
Add enough water to make 2 cups liquid.
Blend cornstarch with 1/4 cup of liquid.
Blend into juice.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Add lemon juice and food coloring.
Fold in strawberries.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill abut 1 hour.
Top with whipped topping or ice cream.
Yields 6 large servings.

title: broccoli-hamburger rolls
directions: Cut ends of rolls and hollow out.
Cook broccoli as directed. Cook hamburger meat and onion; add cheese, broccoli and seasonings.
Fill hulled out rolls with meat mixture and put end back on rolls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler.
Stir in sugar gradually until well blended.
Add milk and salt.
Cook for 5 to 6 minutes until slightly thickened.
Serve over ice cream, pudding or cake.
(You can substitute 9 tablespoons of cocoa and 3 tablespoons of margarine for the chocolate squares.)

title: date balls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and cook until bubbly.
Stir in chopped nuts and Rice Krispies.
When cool enough to handle, form into balls and roll in coconut.

title: enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Chop onions and green peppers; saute in pot.
Add all canned tomatoes and salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1 tablespoon chili powder.
Cook; simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: lemony steamed fish
directions: Center each fillet on 12-inch squares of aluminum foil. Sprinkle with onion, parsley, dill weed, paprika and salt.
Add pepper and lemon juice.
Fold foil over each fillet to make packet.
Pleat seams to securely enclose. Place on a cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 370° for 30 minutes.

title: low-fat tuna salad
directions: Combine all ingredients together in bowl; chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce or stuffed on a tomato or on bread.
Fat: 0.8 g. Serves 8.

title: corn bake
directions: Melt the margarine in a large casserole, then add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Serve hot.

title: cinnamon butter
directions: Combine the ingredients and mix well with an electric mixer. Store in refrigerator.

title: shrimp oriental
directions: Add to Chinese vegetables, cover pan and steam 2 to 3 minutes until vegies are tender-crisp.
Serve rice on heated plates topped with vegies and shrimp with sauce spooned over all.
Makes 6 servings, 225 calories per serving.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar.
Blend in eggs, one at a time; add vanilla.
Stir in flour and nuts and mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gift eggnog
directions: Beat eggs in a mixer 3 to 4 minutes on high. Place sugar and flour in the top of a double boiler. Add eggs and half the milk. Cook over hot water until thick. Remove pan from heat. Slowly stir in remaining milk and vanilla. Cool. Pour into 1-quart glass jar or bottle. Store in refrigerator until ready to use.

title: cheesy veggie casserole
directions: Melt 1/2
margarine and cheese until smooth.
Thaw frozen vegetables and place in large casserole or baking pan.
Pour cheese mixture over them.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over top and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening thoroughly.
Mix soda with buttermilk.
Add molasses and blend.
Add sugar mixture, alternating with flour and salt.
Store in covered bowl in refrigerator overnight.
Drop from tablespoon on cookie sheet 2-inches apart.
Flatten slightly.
Brush with beaten egg yolk. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.
Makes 7 to 8 dozen.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a large pan, mix the ingredients.
(Cream sugar and margarine first.
Save the rolled oats until last.)
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, check at 30 minutes, as ovens are different.

title: old fashioned chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, salt, cocoa, milk and corn syrup.
Cook stirring occasionally until a little in cold water forms a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and peanut butter and let cool until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat with spoon until no longer glossy.
Add nuts if you like.
Put into buttered pan and cut.

title: idiot cookies
directions: Stirring constantly, heat sugar, milk and cocoa on high heat until it reaches a fast, rolling boil.
Reduce heat to maintain a slow, rolling boil for 3 minutes, while stirring constantly. After 3 minutes, remove from heat and add peanut butter, butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Mix thoroughly and drop on wax paper. Allow to cool.

title: recipe for friendship
directions: Mix well and serve generously daily.

title: meatballs napoli
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, celery, egg, seasoning and 3 tablespoons spaghetti sauce; mix thoroughly.
Form into 12 meatballs.
Place on greased shallow baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile blend cornstarch with broth and remaining spaghetti sauce.
Add green beans and simmer about 2 minutes.
Pour over meatballs; continue baking about 10 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna ball
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with cream cheese and roll into ball.
Refrigerate.
Great on crackers.

title: santa fe soup
directions: Brown meat and onion until tender. Add all other ingredients and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: orange jello
directions: Mix Jell-O, pudding and water.
Microwave 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Refrigerate overnight.
Next day, mix with hand mixer until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and oranges.
Chill.

title: mix in pie plate pie crust
directions: Sift flour, sugar and salt into pie plate.
Make a well in middle.
Combine cooking oil and cold milk.
Mix with fork in measuring cup until cloudy.
Pour over flour mixture and mix with fork until blended.
With hands, press into shape, covering rim. Pinch dough into fluting for edging.
Prick bottom and sides. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Can also be used for 1 crust baked pie such as pumpkin.

title: stuffed crab
directions: In a medium-sized skillet, saute onion and shallots in butter. Add bread crumbs and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Add bay leaves, salt, pepper, cayenne, crabmeat and parsley; mix thoroughly and heat through.
Remove from heat and remove bay leaves.
Pack stuffing into 4 crab shells and cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake in a shallow baking dish for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: elderberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together; let set 10 minutes.
Pour into deep-dish pie crust.
Add top crust or lattice topping.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: haystack
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler.
Add peanuts and chow mein noodles.
Stir together.
Drop on wax paper.
Allow to cool.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except 2 tablespoons of the butter and the bread crumbs.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Combine bread cubes and the remaining butter. Sprinkle over top of the casserole and bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries; add sugar.
Let stand.
Prepare jello according to package directions, using only 6 cups water.
When partially set, add other ingredients.
If you like orange, grind a bit of rind with the orange and cranberries.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish or mold and let set until solid.

title: fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in an unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° until done, approximately 35 minutes.

title: boom boom soup
directions: In saucepan with boiling water, add dash of salt and oil, then add macaroni and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
When done, pour into strainer and drain.
Heat tomato soup in a saucepan with milk and mix well.
Add macaroni to soup and pour into bowls.
This is good like this or top with your choice of shredded cheese.

title: no mix cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling into greased 14 x 10-inch pan.
Pour crushed pineapple and juice over the pie filling.
Cover with coconut and pecans.
Spread cake mix (dry) over mixture.
Place pats of butter over entire top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until browned.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream. Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: millie's potluck dessert
directions: To banana cream pudding mix, add crushed pineapple (including juice).
Add Mandarin oranges, drained, marshmallows, lemon juice and bananas.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Chopped nuts or shredded coconut can also be added.
Use a 9 x 13 pan.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Pistachio pudding is also good and gives a prettier color to the dessert.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix together the dry ingredients and the onion.
Add the egg and beat vigorously.
Stir in the milk and form into small patties, either round or finger-shaped.
Drop into deep, hot fat and cook until they are deep brown.
Serve at once.

title: jane's rice
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cook rice.
Simmer celery, bell pepper and onion in butter.
Mix all ingredients together and heat thoroughly.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease a 1 1/2 qt. casserole dish.
Drain the tomatoes and save the juice.
Mix tomatoes, torn bread slices, onion, sugar, red pepper, salt, and half of the melted butter. Add some reserved juice if the mixture looks dry.
Pour remaining butter over mixture and bake 30 - 40 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Place in a small casserole and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Wash and peel potatoes and onions.
Dice the potatoes and onions and place in a large saucepan of water.
Add garlic powder, parsley, salt and pepper to the saucepan.
Cook until tender.
Do not drain water.
Use the blender to blend about 2 cups of the soup and return to the saucepan.
(This is done to thicken the soup.)
Add cheese and continue to cook over low heat until the cheese is melted.
Add wine or sherry just before serving. Garnish soup with bacon bits, green onions and extra grated cheese, if desired.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together Veg-All, mayonnaise and Cheddar cheese.
Spread in baking dish.
Crush the tube of Ritz crackers.
Melt
the butter and drip over entire casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: In small saucepan, combine brown sugar and 4 tablespoons butter.
Melt and stir to combine.
Spread on bottom of 9-inch round x 3-inch deep cake pan.
Arrange peaches over brown sugar in concentrated circles.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
In large bowl, beat remaining butter with sugar until creamy.
Beat egg yolks.
Alternately beat in flour mixture with milk and vanilla until well blended.
In small bowl, beat egg whites to stiff peaks.
Fold egg whites into batter.
Spread over peach slices.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Turn cake onto plate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; add pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into flat dish and refrigerator until set. Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over jello.
Sprinkle with nuts.

title: boston lettuce salad
directions: Wash lettuce, break up and chill.
Add chopped green onions, bacon pieces, cheese and sesame seed.
Add just enough Mozzarella cheese and sesame seed to sprinkle on top.

title: lemon nut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time.
Add dissolved soda and flavoring, along with 4 cups of flour.
Blend well.
Stir in nuts and raisins, mixed with the reserved cup of flour.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add to the batter-nut mix.
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 275° to 300° for 2 hours, until done.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown meats separately and drain well.
Return to large skillet, and add remaining ingredients.
Stir constantly over low heat until cheese melts.
Spread on slices of bread.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, remove from cookie sheet and store in plastic bags in freezer.
To serve, bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
These are delicious open-face sandwiches.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 8 x 8-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350°
for 30 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Beat eggs; add melted butter, sugar, lemon juice and flavoring. Stir and pour mixture into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: florida orange pie
directions: Combine orange juice, orange sections, rind, sugar and cornstarch.
Cook on low heat until clear.
Add a little hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture and cook about 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat.
Blend in lemon juice and margarine.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Be sure filling and shells are both hot or both cold.
Cover with meringue.
Bake at 350° until meringue is lightly browned.

title: orange tarte
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a loaf pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Stir until thick.
Add pineapple chunks, pepper and onion.
Cook 3 minutes more and serve.

title: mom's lemon meringue pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Add water and cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Cook and place over low heat for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Beat egg yolks slightly and add a little hot mixture. Stir and pour back.
Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, oleo and grated peel.
Cool to room temperature without stirring. Pour into baked shell and top with meringue.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Beat well and chill. Serve with chips, large Fritos or crackers.

title: chicken lo mein
directions: Saute oil, garlic and onion until onion is almost transparent and tender.
Add chicken cubes, celery slices and carrot slices. Stir-fry.

title: small mints
directions: Cook sugar, water and syrup in 2-quart saucepan; stir until sugar dissolves.
Cook to thread stage (232°) without stirring. Add cream of tartar; beat with wire whip until creamy.
Add a few drops flavored oil and food coloring.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper, forming patties (keep pan over hot water).
Store tightly covered.
Makes about 60.

title: the chewy oatmeal cookie
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Grease baking sheet with Crisco.

Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat with mixer until well blended. Combine oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon. Mix into creamed mixture until blended. Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop rounded tablespoons of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Cool 2 minutes on sheet, then remove. Makes about 2 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: good day french toast
directions: In shallow bowl, combine Egg Beaters, milk, cinnamon and vanilla.
In skillet or griddle, over medium heat, allow pan to get hot.
Put bread slices in egg mixture and turn them so they are soaked.
Spray cooking surface and place bread slices on griddle.
Brown about 2 to 4 minutes on each side.
Respray cooking surface each time you turn or add bread slices.
Keep in 150° warm oven until all are done.

title: ranger joe cookies
directions: Mix shortening or margarine, granulated sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla well.
Mix flour, salt, soda, salt and baking powder together.
Add the well mixed dry ingredients to sugar mixture.
When thoroughly combined, add Rice Krispies, oatmeal, coconut, nuts and raisins or chocolate chips (for variation, use butterscotch chips).
Dough will be very stiff.
Bake in moderate oven about 10 minutes.
Do not overbake if you like chewy cookies!

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans in water or boil briskly in water for 1 hour; cover and let stand 1 hour.
Add meats, chopped vegetables and all seasonings.
Cook 2 to 3 hours.
Mash 1/4 of the beans and leave the rest whole.
The mashed mixture should look shiny and thick. Re-combine with whole beans.
Serve over rice.

title: eggplant del monico
directions: Combine all ingredients together and sprinkle with toasted bread crumbs. Place in casserole dish and cook for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut oat drop cookies
directions: Sift flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Stir in oats, cream, shortening and butter.
Add eggs, sugars and vanilla. Cream until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients; add pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Chill dough.
Shape tablespoons of dough into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Can use small pretzels to dip.
